<book code="PSA" style="id">- unfoldingWord Literal -</book>
<para style="h">Psalms</para>
<para style="toc1">Psalms</para>
<para style="toc2">Psalms</para>
<para style="mt1">Psalms</para>
<chapter number="1" style="c" sid="PSA 1"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 1:1"/>Happy is the man who walks not in the advice of the wicked {ones}, and stands not in the pathway of sinners, and sits not in the seat of scoffers,<verse eid="PSA 1:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 1:2"/>but in the instruction of Yahweh {is} his delight, and in his instruction he meditates day and night.<verse eid="PSA 1:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 1:3"/>And he is like a tree set to grow on streams of water, which gives its fruit in its season, and its leaf does not wither, and he makes successful all that he does.<verse eid="PSA 1:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 1:4"/>Not so the wicked {ones}! But {they are} like the chaff that wind chases away.<verse eid="PSA 1:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 1:5"/>Thus the wicked {ones} will not stand in the judgment, nor sinners in the congregation of the righteous {ones}.<verse eid="PSA 1:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 1:6"/>For Yahweh knows the way of the righteous {ones}, but the way of the wicked {ones} will perish.<verse eid="PSA 1:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 1"/>
<chapter number="2" style="c" sid="PSA 2"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 2:1"/>Why do nations conspire and peoples plot futilely?<verse eid="PSA 2:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 2:2"/>The kings of the earth take their stand, and the rulers conspire together against Yahweh and against his anointed,<verse eid="PSA 2:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 2:3"/>“Let us tear apart their bonds and cast their cords away from us.”<verse eid="PSA 2:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 2:4"/>He who is sitting in the heavens laughs; the Lord mocks them.<verse eid="PSA 2:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 2:5"/>Then he will speak to them in his anger and terrify them in his fury,<verse eid="PSA 2:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 2:6"/>“I myself have poured out my king on Zion, the mountain of my holiness.”<verse eid="PSA 2:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 2:7"/>I will describe a decree of Yahweh. He said to me, “You are my son! Today I have begotten you.<verse eid="PSA 2:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 2:8"/>Ask from me, and I will give nations {as} your inheritance and the extremities of the earth {as} your possession.<verse eid="PSA 2:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 2:9"/>You will break them with an iron rod; like a jar of a potter, you will smash them to pieces.”<verse eid="PSA 2:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 2:10"/>And now kings, act prudently; be admonished, rulers of the earth.<verse eid="PSA 2:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 2:11"/>Serve Yahweh with fear and rejoice with trembling.<verse eid="PSA 2:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 2:12"/>Kiss the son, lest he be angry and you perish in the way, for his anger burns for just a moment. Happy are all seekers of refuge in him.<verse eid="PSA 2:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 2"/>
<chapter number="3" style="c" sid="PSA 3"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 3:1"/>Yahweh, how many my oppressors have become! The risers against me are many.<verse eid="PSA 3:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 3:2"/>{There are} many sayers about me, “There is no salvation for him in God.” Selah<verse eid="PSA 3:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 3:3"/>But you, Yahweh, are a shield behind me, my glory, and the lifter up of my head.<verse eid="PSA 3:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 3:4"/>{With} my voice I call to Yahweh, and he answered me from the hill of his holiness. Selah<verse eid="PSA 3:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 3:5"/>I laid myself down and slept. I awoke, for Yahweh protects me.<verse eid="PSA 3:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 3:6"/>I will not fear the multitudes of people who stand against me round about.<verse eid="PSA 3:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 3:7"/>Rise up, Yahweh! Save me, my God! For you hit all my enemies on the cheek; the teeth of the wicked you break.<verse eid="PSA 3:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 3:8"/>Salvation {is} of Yahweh. Your blessing {is} on your people. Selah<verse eid="PSA 3:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 3"/>
<chapter number="4" style="c" sid="PSA 4"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 4:1"/>Answer me when I call, God of my righteousness, in distress you relieve me. Be gracious {to} me and hear my prayer.<verse eid="PSA 4:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 4:2"/>Son of man, until when {will} my glory become shame? {Until when} will you love futility, {until when} will you seek falsehood? Selah<verse eid="PSA 4:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 4:3"/>But know that Yahweh has set apart the covenantally faithful for himself. Yahweh hears when I call to him.<verse eid="PSA 4:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 4:4"/>Tremble and do not sin! Meditate in your heart on your bed and be silent. Selah<verse eid="PSA 4:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 4:5"/>Sacrifice sacrifices of righteousness and trust in Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 4:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 4:6"/>Many say, “Who will show us good?” Lift up the light of your face on us Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 4:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 4:7"/>You have put joy in my heart more than the time {when} their grain and their new wine abound.<verse eid="PSA 4:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 4:8"/>In peace I will both lie down and sleep, for you alone, Yahweh, cause me to dwell securely.<verse eid="PSA 4:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 4"/>
<chapter number="5" style="c" sid="PSA 5"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 5:1"/>{To} my words give ear, Yahweh! Understand my murmuring!<verse eid="PSA 5:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 5:2"/>Listen attentively to the sound of my cry for help, my king and my God, for to you I pray!<verse eid="PSA 5:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 5:3"/>Yahweh, in the morning you hear my voice. In the morning I prepare for you and watch.<verse eid="PSA 5:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 5:4"/>For you are not a god pleased with wickedness; evil ones will not sojourn with you.<verse eid="PSA 5:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 5:5"/>The arrogant will not stand in front of your eyes; you hate all doers of iniquity.<verse eid="PSA 5:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 5:6"/>You will destroy speakers of falsehood; the man of blood and deceit Yahweh abhors.<verse eid="PSA 5:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 5:7"/>But I, in the greatness of your covenant faithfulness, I will come into your house; I will bow down toward your temple of holiness in fear.<verse eid="PSA 5:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 5:8"/>Yahweh, guide me in your righteousness because of my watchers; straighten before my face your path.<verse eid="PSA 5:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 5:9"/>For there is no firmness in his mouth; their inward being is destruction. An open tomb is their throat; their tongue they make smooth.<verse eid="PSA 5:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 5:10"/>Make them guilty, God; may they fall due to their schemes! Because of their many transgressions, drive them out, for they rebel against you!<verse eid="PSA 5:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 5:11"/>But may all refuge seekers in you rejoice; may they shout joyfully to eternity; and may you cover over them; and may lovers of your name exult in you.<verse eid="PSA 5:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 5:12"/>For you, Yahweh, you bless the righteous, you surround him {with} favor as a shield.<verse eid="PSA 5:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 5"/>
<chapter number="6" style="c" sid="PSA 6"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 6:1"/>Yahweh, not in your nose, rebuke me, and not in your rage, discipline me.<verse eid="PSA 6:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 6:2"/>Be gracious {to} me, Yahweh, for I am frail! Heal me, Yahweh, for my bones are shaking!<verse eid="PSA 6:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 6:3"/>And my soul is very disturbed. And you, Yahweh, until when?<verse eid="PSA 6:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 6:4"/>Turn back, Yahweh! Rescue my soul! Save me for the sake of your covenant faithfulness!<verse eid="PSA 6:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 6:5"/>For in death, there is no remembrance of you. In Sheol, who will thank you?<verse eid="PSA 6:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 6:6"/>I am weary with my groaning. During every night, I cause my bed to swim, With my tears, my couch I melt.<verse eid="PSA 6:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 6:7"/>My eye has wasted away from grief, it advances because of all my adversaries.<verse eid="PSA 6:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 6:8"/>Turn away from me, all you doers of iniquity, for Yahweh has heard the sound of my sobbing!<verse eid="PSA 6:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 6:9"/>Yahweh has heard my appeal for mercy, Yahweh accepts my prayer.<verse eid="PSA 6:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 6:10"/>Let all my enemies be shamed and greatly disturbed. Let them turn back. Let them be shamed {in} an instant.<verse eid="PSA 6:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 6"/>
<chapter number="7" style="c" sid="PSA 7"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 7:1"/>A musical composition of David, which he sang to Yahweh concerning the words of Cush the Benjamite. Yahweh my God, in you I have taken refuge; save me from all my pursuers, and rescue me!<verse eid="PSA 7:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 7:2"/>Lest he rip my life apart like a lion, tearing apart, and there is no one to rescue.<verse eid="PSA 7:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 7:3"/>Yahweh my God, if I have done this, if there is wrong on my hands,<verse eid="PSA 7:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 7:4"/>if I have repaid evil {to} one {who was at} peace with me, or senselessly rescued my adversary,<verse eid="PSA 7:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 7:5"/>let my enemy pursue my soul and overtake {it}, and let him trample my life to the ground and cause my honor to live in the dust.<verse eid="PSA 7:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 7:6"/>Arise, Yahweh! In your nose, be lifted with the rage of my adversaries! And wake up for me! You have ordered judgment.<verse eid="PSA 7:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 7:7"/>And an assembly of peoples surround you, and over it return on high!<verse eid="PSA 7:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 7:8"/>Yahweh, adjudicate the peoples! Judge me, Yahweh, according to my righteousness and according to my integrity, Most High!<verse eid="PSA 7:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 7:9"/>May the evil of wicked ones end, and {would} you establish righteous ones. The righteous God examines hearts and kidneys.<verse eid="PSA 7:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 7:10"/>My shield is with God, the savior of the upright of heart.<verse eid="PSA 7:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 7:11"/>God is a righteous judge, and a God {who is} indignant on every day.<verse eid="PSA 7:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 7:12"/>If he does not repent, his sword he will sharpen, his bow he has bent and prepared.<verse eid="PSA 7:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 7:13"/>and for him he has prepared implements of death, he has made his arrows into burning {arrows}.<verse eid="PSA 7:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 7:14"/>Behold he is pregnant with wickedness, and he conceives trouble, and he births lies.<verse eid="PSA 7:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 7:15"/>He digs a pit and hollows it out and falls into the hole he has made.<verse eid="PSA 7:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 7:16"/>His trouble returns on his head, and his violence comes down on the top of his head.<verse eid="PSA 7:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 7:17"/>I will thank Yahweh according to his righteousness, and sing praise to the name of Yahweh, the Most High.<verse eid="PSA 7:17"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 7"/>
<chapter number="8" style="c" sid="PSA 8"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 8:1"/>For the chief musician; set to the gittith {style}. A psalm of David. Yahweh, our Lord, how magnificent is your name in all the earth, {you} whose splendor is bestowed on the heavens.<verse eid="PSA 8:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 8:2"/>Out of the mouth of children and nursing ones you have established strength because of your adversaries, to cause the enemy and avenger to end.<verse eid="PSA 8:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 8:3"/>When I look at your heavens, the work of your fingers, the moon and the stars, which you have set in place,<verse eid="PSA 8:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 8:4"/>what is mankind that you remember him, or the son of man that you pay attention to him?<verse eid="PSA 8:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 8:5"/>Yet you have made him to lack little from the heavenly beings, and {with} glory and majesty you have crowned him.<verse eid="PSA 8:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 8:6"/>You made him rule over the works of your hands, everything you have put under his feet:<verse eid="PSA 8:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 8:7"/>sheep and oxen—all of them, and also the animals of the field,<verse eid="PSA 8:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 8:8"/>birds of the sky, and the fish of the sea, the passers {on} the paths of the seas.<verse eid="PSA 8:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 8:9"/>Yahweh, our Lord, how magnificent is your name in all the earth!<verse eid="PSA 8:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 8"/>
<chapter number="9" style="c" sid="PSA 9"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 9:1"/>For the chief musician; set to Muth Labben style. A psalm of David. I will thank Yahweh with all my heart, I will recount all your wonders.<verse eid="PSA 9:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 9:2"/>I will rejoice and exult in you, I will sing praise to your name, Most High!<verse eid="PSA 9:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 9:3"/>When my enemies turn back, they stumble and perish from your face.<verse eid="PSA 9:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 9:4"/>For you have done my justice and my claim; you have sat on your throne, a judge of righteousness!<verse eid="PSA 9:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 9:5"/>You rebuked nations; you  destroyed the wicked; you blotted out their name forever and ever.<verse eid="PSA 9:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 9:6"/>The enemy are finished—desolation forever, and you pulled up cities. {As for} them, their remembrance perished,<verse eid="PSA 9:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 9:7"/>but Yahweh will sit forever. He has established his throne for justice,<verse eid="PSA 9:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 9:8"/>as for him, he will judge the world with righteousness, and he will adjudicate for the peoples with fairness.<verse eid="PSA 9:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 9:9"/>And may Yahweh be a secure height for the oppressed, a secure height for times with distress.<verse eid="PSA 9:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 9:10"/>And may the knowers of your name trust in you, because you have not abandoned the seekers of you, Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 9:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 9:11"/>Sing praises to Yahweh, the sitter {in} Zion! Declare his deeds among the peoples<verse eid="PSA 9:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 9:12"/>for the seeker of {vengeance for} bloodshed remembered them, he does not forget the cry of the afflicted ones.<verse eid="PSA 9:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 9:13"/>Have mercy on me, Yahweh! See my affliction from my haters, O lifter of me from the gates of death,<verse eid="PSA 9:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 9:14"/>in order that I might recount all your praise in the gates of the daughter of Zion. I will rejoice in your salvation!<verse eid="PSA 9:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 9:15"/>The nations have sunk down into the pit they made; their foot is caught in the net that they hid.<verse eid="PSA 9:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 9:16"/>Yahweh has revealed himself, he has done justice; the wicked is ensnared by the work of his hands. <verse eid="PSA 9:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 9:17"/>Wicked ones will turn back to Sheol, all nations are forgetful of God.<verse eid="PSA 9:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 9:18"/>But the needy will not be forgotten eternally, {nor} will the hope of the afflicted perish forever.<verse eid="PSA 9:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 9:19"/>Arise, Yahweh! Let not  humanity prevail! On your face let nations be judged.<verse eid="PSA 9:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 9:20"/>Put terror to them, Yahweh! May nations know they are human. <verse eid="PSA 9:20"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 9"/>
<chapter number="10" style="c" sid="PSA 10"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 10:1"/>Why, Yahweh, do you stand far-off? {Why} do you hide in times of trouble?<verse eid="PSA 10:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 10:2"/>In arrogance, the wicked hotly pursue the afflicted; may they be caught by the schemes that they have planned.<verse eid="PSA 10:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 10:3"/>Indeed, the wicked boasts about the desires of his soul and he blesses the robber; he despises Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 10:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 10:4"/>According to the haughtiness of his nose the wicked seeks not; All his thoughts {are}, “{There is} no God.”<verse eid="PSA 10:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 10:5"/>His ways endure at every time; your judgements are high from in front of him; {as for} all his enemies, he snorts at them.<verse eid="PSA 10:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 10:6"/>He says in his heart, “I will not be shaken; to generation and generation {it is I} who {will} not {be} in distress.”<verse eid="PSA 10:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 10:7"/>His mouth is full of curses and lies and oppression; under his tongue are mischief and evil.<verse eid="PSA 10:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 10:8"/>He sits in ambush near the villages; in the secret places he murders the innocent; his eyes stealthily watch for a helpless person.<verse eid="PSA 10:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 10:9"/>He ambushes in a secret place like a lion in cover; he ambushes to seize the afflicted. He seizes the afflicted by pulling in his net.<verse eid="PSA 10:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 10:10"/>He stoops, crouches, and unfortunate people fall by his power.<verse eid="PSA 10:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 10:11"/>He says in his heart, “God has forgotten; he has hidden his face; to perpetuity he sees not.”<verse eid="PSA 10:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 10:12"/>Arise, Yahweh! God, lift up your hand! Do not forget the afflicted ones.<verse eid="PSA 10:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 10:13"/>Why does the wicked despise God? He says in his heart, “You will not seek.”<verse eid="PSA 10:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 10:14"/>You have seen! Indeed, you notice mischief and vexation to take {it} in your hand. The helpless person entrusts {himself} to you; as for the orphan you, {even} you, are {his} helper.<verse eid="PSA 10:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 10:15"/>Break the arm of wicked and evil {people}. May it seek his wickedness, {but} not find {it}.<verse eid="PSA 10:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 10:16"/>Yahweh is king forever and ever; the nations have perished from his land.<verse eid="PSA 10:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 10:17"/>The desire of afflicted ones, you have heard, Yahweh; you strengthen their heart, you cause your ear to attend:<verse eid="PSA 10:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 10:18"/>to judge the orphan and oppressed; {that} mankind {who is} from the earth will never again terrify.<verse eid="PSA 10:18"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 10"/>
<chapter number="11" style="c" sid="PSA 11"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 11:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. To the director. Of David. In Yahweh I have taken refuge. How will you say to myself, “Flutter {away like} a bird to your mountain”?<verse eid="PSA 11:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 11:2"/>For see! The wicked prepare their bows. They make ready their arrows on the strings to shoot in the darkness at the upright in heart.<verse eid="PSA 11:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 11:3"/>For if the foundations are ruined, what can the righteous do?<verse eid="PSA 11:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 11:4"/>Yahweh is in his holy temple; his eyes watch, his eyes examine the children of mankind.<verse eid="PSA 11:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 11:5"/>Yahweh examines both the righteous and the wicked, but he hates those who love to do violence.<verse eid="PSA 11:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 11:6"/>He rains burning coals and brimstone upon the wicked; a scorching wind will be their portion from his cup!<verse eid="PSA 11:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 11:7"/>For Yahweh is righteous, and he loves righteousness; the upright will see his face.<verse eid="PSA 11:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 11"/>
<chapter number="12" style="c" sid="PSA 12"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 12:1"/>For the chief musician; set to the Sheminith. A psalm of David. Help, Yahweh, for the faithful ones have disappeared; those who have integrity have vanished from the children of men.<verse eid="PSA 12:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 12:2"/>Everyone says empty words to his neighbor; everyone speaks with flattering lips and a double heart.<verse eid="PSA 12:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 12:3"/>Yahweh, cut off all flattering lips, every tongue declaring great things.<verse eid="PSA 12:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 12:4"/>These are those who have said, “With our tongues will we prevail. When our lips speak, who can be master over us?”<verse eid="PSA 12:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 12:5"/>“Because of violence against the poor, because of the groans of the needy, I will arise,” says Yahweh. “I will provide the safety for which they long.”<verse eid="PSA 12:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 12:6"/>The words of Yahweh are pure words, like silver purified in a furnace on the earth, refined seven times.<verse eid="PSA 12:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 12:7"/>You are Yahweh! You keep them. You preserve the godly people from this wicked generation and forever.<verse eid="PSA 12:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 12:8"/>The wicked walk on every side when evil is exalted among the children of mankind.<verse eid="PSA 12:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 12"/>
<chapter number="13" style="c" sid="PSA 13"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 13:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. How long, Yahweh, will you keep forgetting about me? How long will you hide your face from me?<verse eid="PSA 13:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 13:2"/>How long must I worry and have grief in my heart all day? How long will my enemy triumph over me?<verse eid="PSA 13:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 13:3"/>Look at me and answer me, Yahweh my God! Give light to my eyes, or I will sleep in death.<verse eid="PSA 13:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 13:4"/>Do not let my enemy say, “I have defeated him,” so that my enemy may not say, “I have prevailed over my adversary”; otherwise, my enemies will rejoice when I am brought down.<verse eid="PSA 13:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 13:5"/>But I have trusted in your covenant faithfulness; my heart rejoices in your salvation.<verse eid="PSA 13:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 13:6"/>I will sing to Yahweh because he has treated me very generously.<verse eid="PSA 13:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 13"/>
<chapter number="14" style="c" sid="PSA 14"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 14:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. To the chief musician A psalm of DavidA A fool says in his heart, “There is no God.” They are corrupt and have done abominable iniquity; there is no one who does good.<verse eid="PSA 14:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 14:2"/>Yahweh looks down from heaven on the children of mankind to see if there are any who understand, who seek after him.<verse eid="PSA 14:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 14:3"/>They have all turned away. Together they have become corrupt. There is no one who does good, no, not one.<verse eid="PSA 14:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 14:4"/>Do they not know anything, those who commit iniquity, those who eat up my people as they eat bread, but who do not call on Yahweh?<verse eid="PSA 14:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 14:5"/>They tremble with dread, for God is with the righteous assembly!<verse eid="PSA 14:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 14:6"/>You want to humiliate the poor person even though Yahweh is his refuge.<verse eid="PSA 14:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 14:7"/>Oh, that the salvation of Israel would come from Zion! When Yahweh brings back his people from the captivity, then Jacob will rejoice and Israel will be glad!<verse eid="PSA 14:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 14"/>
<chapter number="15" style="c" sid="PSA 15"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 15:1"/>A psalm of David. To the chief musician A psalm of David Yahweh, who may stay in your tabernacle? Who may live on your holy hill?<verse eid="PSA 15:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 15:2"/>Whoever walks blamelessly, does what is right and speaks truth from his heart.<verse eid="PSA 15:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 15:3"/>He does not slander with his tongue, he does not harm others, and he does not insult his neighbor.<verse eid="PSA 15:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 15:4"/>The worthless person is despised in his eyes, but he honors those who fear Yahweh. He swears to his own disadvantage and does not take back his promises.<verse eid="PSA 15:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 15:5"/>He does not charge interest when he lends money. He does not take bribes to testify against the innocent. He who does these things will never be shaken.<verse eid="PSA 15:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 15"/>
<chapter number="16" style="c" sid="PSA 16"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 16:1"/>A michtam of David. A song of David Protect me, God, for I take refuge in you.<verse eid="PSA 16:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 16:2"/>You say to Yahweh, “You are my Lord; my goodness is nothing apart from you.<verse eid="PSA 16:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 16:3"/>As for the holy ones who are in the land, they are noble people; all my delight is in them.<verse eid="PSA 16:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 16:4"/>Their troubles will increase, those who seek out other gods. I will not pour out their drink offerings of blood or lift up their names with my lips.<verse eid="PSA 16:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 16:5"/>Yahweh is the portion of my inheritance and my cup. You hold onto my lot.<verse eid="PSA 16:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 16:6"/>Measuring lines have been laid for me in pleasant places; surely a pleasing inheritance is mine.<verse eid="PSA 16:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 16:7"/>I will bless Yahweh, who counsels me; even at night my mind instructs me.<verse eid="PSA 16:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 16:8"/>I set Yahweh before me continually, for he is at my right hand, I will not be shaken.<verse eid="PSA 16:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 16:9"/>Therefore my heart rejoices, and my glory is joyful. Surely my flesh will dwell in security.<verse eid="PSA 16:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 16:10"/>For you will not abandon my soul to Sheol. You will not let your faithful one see the pit.<verse eid="PSA 16:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 16:11"/>You teach me the path of life; abundant joy is in your face; pleasures are at your right hand forever!”<verse eid="PSA 16:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 16"/>
<chapter number="17" style="c" sid="PSA 17"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 17:1"/>A prayer of David. A prayer of David Listen to my plea for justice, Yahweh; pay attention to my call for help! Give ear to my prayer from lips without deceit.<verse eid="PSA 17:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 17:2"/>Let my vindication come from your presence; let your eyes see what is right!<verse eid="PSA 17:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 17:3"/>If you test my heart, if you come to me in the night, you will purify me and will not find any evil plans; my mouth will not transgress.<verse eid="PSA 17:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 17:4"/>As for the deeds of mankind, it is at the word of your lips that I have kept myself from the ways of the lawless.<verse eid="PSA 17:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 17:5"/>My steps have held firmly to your tracks; my feet have not slipped.<verse eid="PSA 17:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 17:6"/>I call to you, for you answer me, God; turn your ear to me and listen when I speak.<verse eid="PSA 17:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 17:7"/>Show your covenant faithfulness in a wonderful way, you who save by your right hand those who take refuge in you from their enemies!<verse eid="PSA 17:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 17:8"/>Protect me like the apple of your eye; hide me under the shadow of your wings<verse eid="PSA 17:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 17:9"/>from the presence of the wicked ones who assault me, my enemies who surround me.<verse eid="PSA 17:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 17:10"/>They have no mercy on anyone; their mouths speak with pride.<verse eid="PSA 17:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 17:11"/>They have surrounded my steps. They set their eyes to strike me to the ground.<verse eid="PSA 17:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 17:12"/>They are like a lion eager for a victim, like a young lion crouching in hidden places.<verse eid="PSA 17:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 17:13"/>Arise, Yahweh! Attack them! Throw them down on their faces! Rescue my life from the wicked by your sword!<verse eid="PSA 17:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 17:14"/>Rescue me from men by your hand, Yahweh, from men of this world whose prosperity is in this life alone! You will fill the bellies of your treasured ones with riches; they will have many children and will leave their wealth to their children.<verse eid="PSA 17:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 17:15"/>As for me, I will see your face in righteousness; I will be satisfied, when I awake, with a sight of you.<verse eid="PSA 17:15"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 17"/>
<chapter number="18" style="c" sid="PSA 18"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 18:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David, the servant of Yahweh, when he sang to Yahweh the words of this song on the day that Yahweh rescued him from the hand of all his enemies and from the hand of Saul. He sang: I love you, Yahweh, my strength.<verse eid="PSA 18:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 18:2"/>Yahweh is my rock, my fortress, the one who brings me to safety; he is my God, my rock; I take refuge in him. He is my shield, the horn of my salvation, and my stronghold.<verse eid="PSA 18:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 18:3"/>I will call on Yahweh who is worthy to be praised, and I will be saved from my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 18:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 18:4"/>The cords of death surrounded me, and the rushing waters of worthlessness overwhelmed me.<verse eid="PSA 18:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 18:5"/>The cords of Sheol surrounded me; the snares of death trapped me.<verse eid="PSA 18:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 18:6"/>In my distress I called to Yahweh; I called for help to my God. He heard my voice from his temple; my call for help went into his presence; it went into his ears.<verse eid="PSA 18:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 18:7"/>Then the earth shook and trembled; the foundations of the mountains also trembled and were shaken because God was angry.<verse eid="PSA 18:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 18:8"/>Smoke went up from out of his nostrils, and blazing fire came out of his mouth. Coals were ignited by it.<verse eid="PSA 18:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 18:9"/>He opened the heavens and came down, and thick darkness was under his feet.<verse eid="PSA 18:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 18:10"/>He rode on a cherub and flew; he glided on the wings of the wind.<verse eid="PSA 18:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 18:11"/>He made darkness a tent around him, heavy rainclouds in the skies.<verse eid="PSA 18:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 18:12"/>Hailstones and coals of fire fell from the lightning before him.<verse eid="PSA 18:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 18:13"/>Yahweh thundered in the heavens! The voice of the Most High shouted hailstones and coals of fire<verse eid="PSA 18:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 18:14"/>He shot his arrows and scattered his enemies; many lightning bolts dispersed them.<verse eid="PSA 18:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 18:15"/>Then the water channels appeared; the foundations of the world were laid bare at your rebuke, Yahweh, at the blast of the breath of your nostrils.<verse eid="PSA 18:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 18:16"/>He reached down from above; he took hold of me! He pulled me out of the surging water.<verse eid="PSA 18:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 18:17"/>He rescued me from my strong enemy, from those who hated me, for they were too strong for me.<verse eid="PSA 18:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 18:18"/>They came against me on the day of my distress but Yahweh was my support!<verse eid="PSA 18:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 18:19"/>He set me free in a wide open place; he saved me because he was pleased with me.<verse eid="PSA 18:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 18:20"/>Yahweh has rewarded me because of my righteousness; he has restored me because my hands were clean.<verse eid="PSA 18:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 18:21"/>For I have kept the ways of Yahweh and have not wickedly turned away from my God.<verse eid="PSA 18:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 18:22"/>For all his righteous decrees have been before me; as for his statutes, I have not turned away from them.<verse eid="PSA 18:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 18:23"/>I have also been innocent before him, and I have kept myself from sin.<verse eid="PSA 18:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 18:24"/>Therefore Yahweh has restored me because of my righteousness, because my hands were clean before his eyes.<verse eid="PSA 18:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 18:25"/>To the one who is faithful, you show yourself to be faithful; to a man who is blameless, you show yourself to be blameless.<verse eid="PSA 18:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 18:26"/>To anyone who is pure, you show yourself pure; but you are clever toward anyone who is twisted.<verse eid="PSA 18:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 18:27"/>For you save afflicted people, but you bring down those with proud, uplifted eyes!<verse eid="PSA 18:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 18:28"/>For you give light to my lamp; Yahweh my God lights up my darkness.<verse eid="PSA 18:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 18:29"/>For by you I can run over a barricade; by my God I can leap over a wall.<verse eid="PSA 18:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 18:30"/>As for God—his way is perfect! The word of Yahweh is pure! He is a shield to everyone who takes refuge in him.<verse eid="PSA 18:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 18:31"/>For who is God except Yahweh? Who is a rock except our God?<verse eid="PSA 18:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 18:32"/>It is God who puts strength on me like a belt, who places the blameless person on his path.<verse eid="PSA 18:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 18:33"/>He makes my feet swift like a deer and places me on the heights!<verse eid="PSA 18:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 18:34"/>He trains my hands for war and my arms to bend a bow of bronze.<verse eid="PSA 18:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 18:35"/>You have given me the shield of your salvation. Your right hand has supported me, and your favor has made me great.<verse eid="PSA 18:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 18:36"/>You have made a wide place for my feet beneath me so that my feet have not slipped.<verse eid="PSA 18:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 18:37"/>I pursued my enemies and caught them; I did not turn back until they were destroyed.<verse eid="PSA 18:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 18:38"/>I smashed them so that they were unable to rise; they have fallen under my feet.<verse eid="PSA 18:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 18:39"/>For you put strength on me like a belt for battle; you put under me those who rise up against me.<verse eid="PSA 18:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 18:40"/>You gave me the back of my enemies’ necks; I annihilated those who hated me.<verse eid="PSA 18:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 18:41"/>They called for help, but no one saved them; they called out to Yahweh, but he did not answer them.<verse eid="PSA 18:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 18:42"/>I beat them into fine pieces like dust before the wind; I threw them out like mud in the streets.<verse eid="PSA 18:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 18:43"/>You rescued me from the disputes of people. You have made me the head over nations. People that I have not known serve me.<verse eid="PSA 18:43"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="44" style="v" sid="PSA 18:44"/>As soon as they heard of me, they obeyed me; foreigners were forced to bow to me.<verse eid="PSA 18:44"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="45" style="v" sid="PSA 18:45"/>The foreigners came trembling out of their strongholds.<verse eid="PSA 18:45"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="46" style="v" sid="PSA 18:46"/>Yahweh lives; may my rock be praised. May the God of my salvation be exalted.<verse eid="PSA 18:46"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="47" style="v" sid="PSA 18:47"/>He is the God who executes vengeance for me, who subdues the nations under me.<verse eid="PSA 18:47"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="48" style="v" sid="PSA 18:48"/>I am set free from my enemies! Indeed, you lifted me above the ones who rose against me! You rescued me from violent men.<verse eid="PSA 18:48"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="49" style="v" sid="PSA 18:49"/>Therefore I will give thanks to you, Yahweh, among the nations; I will sing praises to your name!<verse eid="PSA 18:49"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="50" style="v" sid="PSA 18:50"/>God gives great victory to his king, and he shows his covenant loyalty to his anointed one, to David and to his descendants forever.<verse eid="PSA 18:50"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 18"/>
<chapter number="19" style="c" sid="PSA 19"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 19:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. The heavens declare the glory of God, and the skies make his handiwork known!<verse eid="PSA 19:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 19:2"/>Day after day speech pours out; night after night it reveals knowledge.<verse eid="PSA 19:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 19:3"/>There is no speech or spoken words; their voice is not heard.<verse eid="PSA 19:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 19:4"/>Yet their words go out over all the earth, and their speech to the end of the world. He has pitched a tent for the sun among them.<verse eid="PSA 19:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 19:5"/>The sun is like a bridegroom coming out of his chamber and like a strong man who rejoices when he runs his race.<verse eid="PSA 19:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 19:6"/>The sun rises from the one horizon and crosses the sky to the other; nothing escapes its heat.<verse eid="PSA 19:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 19:7"/>The law of Yahweh is perfect, restoring the soul; the testimony of Yahweh is reliable, making the simple wise.<verse eid="PSA 19:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 19:8"/>The instructions of Yahweh are right, making the heart glad; the commandment of Yahweh is pure, bringing light to the eyes.<verse eid="PSA 19:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 19:9"/>The fear of Yahweh is pure, enduring forever; the righteous decrees of Yahweh are true and altogether right!<verse eid="PSA 19:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 19:10"/>They are of greater value than gold, even more than much fine gold; they are sweeter than honey and the dripping honey from the honeycomb.<verse eid="PSA 19:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 19:11"/>Yes, by them your servant is warned; in obeying them there is great reward.<verse eid="PSA 19:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 19:12"/>Who can discern all his own errors? Cleanse me from hidden faults.<verse eid="PSA 19:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 19:13"/>Keep your servant also from arrogant sins; let them not rule over me. Then I will be perfect, and I will be innocent from many transgressions.<verse eid="PSA 19:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 19:14"/>May the words of my mouth and the thoughts of my heart be acceptable in your sight, Yahweh, my rock and my redeemer.<verse eid="PSA 19:14"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 19"/>
<chapter number="20" style="c" sid="PSA 20"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 20:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. May Yahweh help you in the day of trouble; may the name of the God of Jacob protect you<verse eid="PSA 20:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 20:2"/>and send help from the holy place to support you from Zion.<verse eid="PSA 20:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 20:3"/>May he call to mind all your offerings and accept your burnt sacrifice. <verse eid="PSA 20:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 20:4"/>May he grant you your heart’s desire and fulfill all your plans.<verse eid="PSA 20:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 20:5"/>Then we will rejoice in your victory, and, in the name of our God, we will raise banners. May Yahweh grant all your petitions.<verse eid="PSA 20:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 20:6"/>Now I know that Yahweh will rescue his anointed one; he will answer him from his holy heaven with the strength of his right hand that can rescue him.<verse eid="PSA 20:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 20:7"/>These trust in chariots and others in horses, but we will remember the name of Yahweh our God.<verse eid="PSA 20:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 20:8"/>They will be brought down and fall, but we will rise and stand upright!<verse eid="PSA 20:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 20:9"/>Yahweh, rescue the king; help us when we call.<verse eid="PSA 20:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 20"/>
<chapter number="21" style="c" sid="PSA 21"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 21:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. The king rejoices in your strength, Yahweh! How greatly he rejoices in the salvation you provide!<verse eid="PSA 21:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 21:2"/>You have given him his heart’s desire and have not held back the request of his lips. Selah<verse eid="PSA 21:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 21:3"/>For you bring him rich blessings; you placed on his head a crown of purest gold.<verse eid="PSA 21:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 21:4"/>He asked you for life; you gave it to him; you gave him the length of his days forever and ever.<verse eid="PSA 21:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 21:5"/>His glory is great because of your victory; you have bestowed on him splendor and majesty.<verse eid="PSA 21:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 21:6"/>For you grant him lasting blessings; you make him glad with the joy of your presence.<verse eid="PSA 21:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 21:7"/>For the king trusts in Yahweh; through the covenant faithfulness of the Most High he will not be moved.<verse eid="PSA 21:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 21:8"/>Your hand will seize all your enemies; your right hand will seize those who hate you.<verse eid="PSA 21:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 21:9"/>At the time of your anger, you will burn them up as in a fiery furnace. Yahweh will consume them in his wrath, and the fire will devour them.<verse eid="PSA 21:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 21:10"/>You will destroy their offspring from the earth and their descendants from among the human race.<verse eid="PSA 21:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 21:11"/>For they intended evil against you; they conceived a plot with which they will not succeed!<verse eid="PSA 21:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 21:12"/>For you will turn them back; you will draw your bow before them.<verse eid="PSA 21:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 21:13"/>Be exalted, Yahweh, in your strength; we will sing and praise your power.<verse eid="PSA 21:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 21"/>
<chapter number="22" style="c" sid="PSA 22"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 22:1"/>For the chief musician; set to “The rhythm of the deer.” A psalm of David. My God, my God, why have you abandoned me? Why are you so far from saving me and far from the words of my anguish?<verse eid="PSA 22:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 22:2"/>My God, I cry out in the daytime, but you do not answer, and at night I am not silent!<verse eid="PSA 22:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 22:3"/>Yet you are holy; you sit as king with the praises of Israel.<verse eid="PSA 22:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 22:4"/>Our ancestors trusted in you; they trusted in you, and you rescued them.<verse eid="PSA 22:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 22:5"/>They cried to you and they were rescued. They trusted in you and were not disappointed.<verse eid="PSA 22:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 22:6"/>But I am a worm and not a man, a disgrace to humanity and despised by the people.<verse eid="PSA 22:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 22:7"/>All those who see me taunt me; they mock me; they shake their heads at me.<verse eid="PSA 22:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 22:8"/>They say, “He trusts in Yahweh; let Yahweh rescue him. Let him rescue him, for he delights in him.”<verse eid="PSA 22:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 22:9"/>For you brought me from the womb; you made me trust you when I was on my mother’s breasts.<verse eid="PSA 22:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 22:10"/>I have been thrown on you from the womb; you are my God since I was in my mother’s womb!<verse eid="PSA 22:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 22:11"/>Do not be far away from me, for trouble is near; there is no one to help.<verse eid="PSA 22:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 22:12"/>Many bulls surround me; strong bulls of Bashan surround me.<verse eid="PSA 22:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 22:13"/>They open their mouths wide against me like a roaring lion ripping its victim.<verse eid="PSA 22:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 22:14"/>I am being poured out like water, and all my bones are dislocated. My heart is like wax; it melts away within my inner parts.<verse eid="PSA 22:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 22:15"/>My strength has dried up like a piece of pottery; my tongue sticks to the roof of my mouth. You have laid me in the dust of death.<verse eid="PSA 22:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 22:16"/>For dogs have surrounded me; a company of evildoers has encircled me; they have pierced my hands and my feet.<verse eid="PSA 22:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 22:17"/>I can count all my bones. They look and stare at me.<verse eid="PSA 22:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 22:18"/>They divide my garments among themselves, they cast lots for my clothes.<verse eid="PSA 22:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 22:19"/>Do not be far away, Yahweh; please hurry to help me, my strength!<verse eid="PSA 22:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 22:20"/>Rescue my soul from the sword, my only life from the claws of wild dogs.<verse eid="PSA 22:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 22:21"/>Save me from the lion’s mouth; rescue me from the horns of the wild oxen.<verse eid="PSA 22:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 22:22"/>I will declare your name to my brothers; in the midst of the assembly I will praise you.<verse eid="PSA 22:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 22:23"/>You who fear Yahweh, praise him! All you descendants of Jacob, honor him! Stand in awe of him, all you descendants of Israel!<verse eid="PSA 22:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 22:24"/>For he has not despised or abhorred the suffering of the afflicted one; Yahweh has not hidden his face from him; when the afflicted one cried to him, he heard.<verse eid="PSA 22:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 22:25"/>My praise will be because of you in the great assembly; I will fulfill my vows before those who fear him.<verse eid="PSA 22:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 22:26"/>The oppressed will eat and be satisfied; those who seek Yahweh will praise him. May your hearts live forever.<verse eid="PSA 22:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 22:27"/>All the peoples of the earth will remember and turn to Yahweh; all the families of the nations will bow down before you.<verse eid="PSA 22:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 22:28"/>For the kingdom is Yahweh’s; he is the ruler over the nations.<verse eid="PSA 22:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 22:29"/>All the prosperous people of the earth will feast and will worship; all those who are descending into the dust will bow before him, those who cannot preserve their own lives.<verse eid="PSA 22:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 22:30"/>A generation to come will serve him; they will tell the next generation of the Lord.<verse eid="PSA 22:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 22:31"/>They will come and tell of his righteousness; they will tell to a people not yet born what he has done!<verse eid="PSA 22:31"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 22"/>
<chapter number="23" style="c" sid="PSA 23"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 23:1"/>A psalm of David. [A Psalm of David] Yahweh is my shepherd; I will lack nothing.<verse eid="PSA 23:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 23:2"/>He makes me to lie down in green pastures; he leads me beside tranquil water.<verse eid="PSA 23:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 23:3"/>He brings back my life; he guides me along right paths for the sake of his name.<verse eid="PSA 23:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 23:4"/>Even though I walk through a valley of darkest shadow, I will not fear harm since you are with me; your rod and your staff, they comfort me.<verse eid="PSA 23:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 23:5"/>You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies; you have anointed my head with oil; my cup runs over.<verse eid="PSA 23:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 23:6"/>Surely goodness and covenant faithfulness will pursue me all the days of my life; and I will live in the house of Yahweh for the length of my days!<verse eid="PSA 23:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 23"/>
<chapter number="24" style="c" sid="PSA 24"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 24:1"/>A psalm of David. The earth is Yahweh’s, and its fullness, the world, and all who live in it.<verse eid="PSA 24:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 24:2"/>For he has founded it upon the seas and established it on the rivers.<verse eid="PSA 24:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 24:3"/>Who will ascend the mountain of Yahweh? Who will stand in his holy place?<verse eid="PSA 24:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 24:4"/>The one with clean hands and a pure heart; who has not lifted up my life as a falsehood, and has not sworn an oath in order to deceive.<verse eid="PSA 24:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 24:5"/>He will receive a blessing from Yahweh and righteousness from the God of his salvation.<verse eid="PSA 24:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 24:6"/>Such is the generation of those who seek him, those who seek the face of Jacob. <verse eid="PSA 24:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 24:7"/>Lift up your heads, you gates; be lifted up, everlasting doors, so that the King of glory may come in!<verse eid="PSA 24:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 24:8"/>Who is this King of glory? Yahweh, strong and mighty; Yahweh, mighty in battle.<verse eid="PSA 24:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 24:9"/>Lift up your heads, you gates; be lifted up, everlasting doors, so that the King of glory may come in!<verse eid="PSA 24:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 24:10"/>Who is this King of glory? Yahweh of hosts, he is the King of glory. <verse eid="PSA 24:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 24"/>
<chapter number="25" style="c" sid="PSA 25"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 25:1"/>David To you, Yahweh, I lift up my life!<verse eid="PSA 25:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 25:2"/>My God, I trust in you. Do not let me be humiliated; do not let my enemies rejoice triumphantly over me.<verse eid="PSA 25:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 25:3"/>May no one who hopes in you be disgraced may those who act treacherously without cause be ashamed!<verse eid="PSA 25:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 25:4"/>Make known to me your ways, Yahweh; teach me your paths.<verse eid="PSA 25:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 25:5"/>Guide me into your truth and teach me, for you are the God of my salvation; I hope in you all day long.<verse eid="PSA 25:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 25:6"/>Call to mind, Yahweh, your acts of compassion and of covenant faithfulness; for they have always existed.<verse eid="PSA 25:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 25:7"/>Do not think about the sins of my youth or my rebelliousness; Call me to mind with covenant faithfulness because of your goodness, Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 25:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 25:8"/>Yahweh is good and upright; therefore he teaches sinners the way.<verse eid="PSA 25:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 25:9"/>He guides the humble in what is right and he teaches them his way.<verse eid="PSA 25:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 25:10"/>All the paths of Yahweh are steadfast love and faithfulness to those who keep his covenant and his solemn commands.<verse eid="PSA 25:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 25:11"/>For your name’s sake, Yahweh, pardon my sin, for it is great.<verse eid="PSA 25:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 25:12"/>Who is the man who fears Yahweh? The Lord will instruct him in the way that he should choose.<verse eid="PSA 25:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 25:13"/>His life will go along in goodness; and his descendants will inherit the land.<verse eid="PSA 25:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 25:14"/>The friendship of Yahweh is for those who honor him, and he makes his covenant known to them.<verse eid="PSA 25:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 25:15"/>My eyes are always on Yahweh, for he will free my feet from the net.<verse eid="PSA 25:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 25:16"/>Turn toward me and have mercy on me; for I am alone and afflicted.<verse eid="PSA 25:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 25:17"/>The troubles of my heart are enlarged; draw me out from my distress!<verse eid="PSA 25:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 25:18"/>See my affliction and my toils; forgive all my sins.<verse eid="PSA 25:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 25:19"/>See my enemies, for they are many; they hate me with cruel hatred.<verse eid="PSA 25:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 25:20"/>Protect my life and rescue me; do not let me be humiliated, for I take refuge in you!<verse eid="PSA 25:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 25:21"/>May integrity and uprightness preserve me, for I hope in you.<verse eid="PSA 25:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 25:22"/>Rescue Israel, God, from all of his troubles!<verse eid="PSA 25:22"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 25"/>
<chapter number="26" style="c" sid="PSA 26"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 26:1"/>A psalm of David. David Judge me, Yahweh, for I have walked with integrity; I have trusted in Yahweh without wavering.<verse eid="PSA 26:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 26:2"/>Examine me, Yahweh, and test me; test the purity of my inner parts and my heart!<verse eid="PSA 26:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 26:3"/>For your covenant faithfulness is before my eyes, and I walk about in your faithfulness.<verse eid="PSA 26:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 26:4"/>I do not associate with deceitful people, nor do I mingle with dishonest people.<verse eid="PSA 26:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 26:5"/>I hate the assembly of evildoers, and I do not live with the wicked.<verse eid="PSA 26:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 26:6"/>I wash my hands in innocence, and I go around your altar, Yahweh,<verse eid="PSA 26:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 26:7"/>to sing a loud song of praise and report all your wonderful deeds.<verse eid="PSA 26:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 26:8"/>Yahweh, I love the house where you live, the place where your glory lives!<verse eid="PSA 26:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 26:9"/>Do not sweep me away with sinners, or my life with people who are bloodthirsty,<verse eid="PSA 26:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 26:10"/>in whose hands there is a plot, and whose right hand is full of bribes.<verse eid="PSA 26:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 26:11"/>But as for me, I will walk in integrity; redeem me and have mercy on me.<verse eid="PSA 26:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 26:12"/>My foot stands on level ground; in the assemblies will I bless Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 26:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 26"/>
<chapter number="27" style="c" sid="PSA 27"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 27:1"/>A psalm of David. David Yahweh is my light and my salvation; whom should I fear? Yahweh is my life’s refuge; whom should I dread?<verse eid="PSA 27:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 27:2"/>When evildoers approached me to devour my flesh, my adversaries and my enemies stumbled and fell.<verse eid="PSA 27:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 27:3"/>Though an army encamps against me, my heart will not fear; though war rises up against me, even then I will remain confident.<verse eid="PSA 27:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 27:4"/>One thing have I asked of Yahweh, and I will seek that: that I may live in the house of Yahweh all the days of my life, to see the beauty of Yahweh and to meditate in his temple.<verse eid="PSA 27:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 27:5"/>For in the day of trouble he will hide me in his shelter; in the cover of his tent he will conceal me. He will lift me high on a rock!<verse eid="PSA 27:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 27:6"/>Then my head will be lifted up above my enemies all around me, and I will offer sacrifices of joy in his tent! I will sing and make songs to Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 27:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 27:7"/>Hear, Yahweh, my voice when I cry out! Have mercy on me, and answer me!<verse eid="PSA 27:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 27:8"/>My heart says about you, “Seek his face!” I seek your face, Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 27:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 27:9"/>Do not hide your face from me; do not turn your servant away in anger! You have been my helper; do not forsake me or abandon me, God of my salvation!<verse eid="PSA 27:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 27:10"/>Even if my father and my mother forsake me, Yahweh will take me in.<verse eid="PSA 27:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 27:11"/>Teach me your way, Yahweh! Lead me on a level path because of my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 27:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 27:12"/>Do not give me up to the desires of my enemies, for false witnesses have risen up against me, and they breathe out violence!<verse eid="PSA 27:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 27:13"/>What would have happened to me if I had not believed that I would see the goodness of Yahweh in the land of the living?<verse eid="PSA 27:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 27:14"/>Wait for Yahweh; be strong, and let your heart be courageous! Wait for Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 27:14"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 27"/>
<chapter number="28" style="c" sid="PSA 28"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 28:1"/>A psalm of David. David To you, Yahweh, I cry out; my rock, do not ignore me. If you do not respond to me, I will join those who go down to the grave.<verse eid="PSA 28:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 28:2"/>Hear the sound of my pleading when I call for help from you, when I lift up my hands toward your most holy place!<verse eid="PSA 28:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 28:3"/>Do not drag me away with the wicked, those who do iniquity, who speak peace with their neighbors but have evil in their hearts.<verse eid="PSA 28:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 28:4"/>Give them what their deeds deserve and repay them what their wickedness demands, repay them for the work of their hands and render to them their due.<verse eid="PSA 28:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 28:5"/>Because they do not understand the deeds of Yahweh or the work of his hands, he will tear them down and never rebuild them.<verse eid="PSA 28:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 28:6"/>Blessed be Yahweh because he has heard the sound of my pleading!<verse eid="PSA 28:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 28:7"/>Yahweh is my strength and my shield; my heart trusts in him, and I am helped. Therefore my heart greatly rejoices, and I will praise him with singing.<verse eid="PSA 28:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 28:8"/>Yahweh is the strength of his people, and he is the saving refuge of his anointed one.<verse eid="PSA 28:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 28:9"/>Save your people and bless your inheritance. Be their shepherd and carry them forever.<verse eid="PSA 28:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 28"/>
<chapter number="29" style="c" sid="PSA 29"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 29:1"/>A psalm of David. A Psalm of David Ascribe to Yahweh, you sons of God, ascribe to Yahweh glory and strength!<verse eid="PSA 29:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 29:2"/>Ascribe to Yahweh the glory his name deserves. Bow down to Yahweh in the splendor of holiness!<verse eid="PSA 29:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 29:3"/>The voice of Yahweh is heard over the waters; the God of glory thunders, Yahweh thunders over many waters.<verse eid="PSA 29:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 29:4"/>The voice of Yahweh is powerful; the voice of Yahweh is majestic.<verse eid="PSA 29:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 29:5"/>The voice of Yahweh breaks the cedars; Yahweh breaks in pieces the cedars of Lebanon.<verse eid="PSA 29:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 29:6"/>He makes Lebanon skip like a calf and Sirion like a young ox.<verse eid="PSA 29:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 29:7"/>The voice of Yahweh sends out flames of fire.<verse eid="PSA 29:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 29:8"/>The voice of Yahweh shakes the wilderness; Yahweh shakes the wilderness of Kadesh.<verse eid="PSA 29:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 29:9"/>The voice of Yahweh causes the oaks to twist and strips the forests bare. Everyone in his temple says, “Glory!”<verse eid="PSA 29:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 29:10"/>Yahweh sits as king over the flood; Yahweh sits as king forever.<verse eid="PSA 29:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 29:11"/>Yahweh gives strength to his people; Yahweh blesses his people with peace.<verse eid="PSA 29:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 29"/>
<chapter number="30" style="c" sid="PSA 30"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 30:1"/>A psalm; a song at the dedication of the temple. A psalm of David. I will exalt you, Yahweh, for you have raised me up and have not allowed my enemies to rejoice over me.<verse eid="PSA 30:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 30:2"/>Yahweh my God, I cried to you for help, and you healed me.<verse eid="PSA 30:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 30:3"/>Yahweh, you have brought up my soul from Sheol; you have kept me alive from going down to the grave.<verse eid="PSA 30:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 30:4"/>Sing praises to Yahweh, you his faithful ones! Give thanks when you remember his holiness.<verse eid="PSA 30:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 30:5"/>For his anger is only for a moment; but his favor is for a lifetime. Weeping comes for a night, but joy comes in the morning.<verse eid="PSA 30:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 30:6"/>In confidence I said, “I will never be shaken.”<verse eid="PSA 30:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 30:7"/>Yahweh, by your favor you established me as a strong mountain; but when you hid your face, I was troubled.<verse eid="PSA 30:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 30:8"/>I cried to you, Yahweh, and sought favor from my Lord!<verse eid="PSA 30:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 30:9"/>What advantage is there in my death, if I go down to the grave? Will the dust praise you? Will it declare your trustworthiness?<verse eid="PSA 30:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 30:10"/>Hear, Yahweh, and have mercy on me! Yahweh, be my helper.<verse eid="PSA 30:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 30:11"/>You have turned my mourning into dancing; you have removed my sackcloth and clothed me with gladness.<verse eid="PSA 30:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 30:12"/>So now my glory will sing praise to you and not be silent; Yahweh my God, I will give thanks to you forever!<verse eid="PSA 30:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 30"/>
<chapter number="31" style="c" sid="PSA 31"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 31:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. In you, Yahweh, I take refuge; never let me be humiliated. Rescue me in your righteousness.<verse eid="PSA 31:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 31:2"/>Listen to me; rescue me quickly; be my rock of refuge, a stronghold to save me.<verse eid="PSA 31:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 31:3"/>For you are my rock and my fortress; therefore for your name’s sake, lead and guide me.<verse eid="PSA 31:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 31:4"/>Pluck me out of the net that they have hidden for me, for you are my refuge.<verse eid="PSA 31:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 31:5"/>Into your hands I entrust my spirit; you will redeem me, Yahweh, God of trustworthiness.<verse eid="PSA 31:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 31:6"/>I hate those who serve worthless idols, but I trust in Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 31:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 31:7"/>I will be glad and rejoice in your covenant faithfulness, for you saw my affliction; you knew the distress of my soul.<verse eid="PSA 31:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 31:8"/>You have not given me into the hand of my enemy. You have set my feet in a wide open place.<verse eid="PSA 31:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 31:9"/>Have mercy upon me, Yahweh, for I am in distress; my eyes grow weary with grief with my soul and my body.<verse eid="PSA 31:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 31:10"/>For my life is weary with sorrow and my years with groaning. My strength fails because of my sin, and my bones are wasting away.<verse eid="PSA 31:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 31:11"/>Because of all my enemies, people disdain me; my neighbors are appalled at my situation, and those who know me are horrified. Those who see me in the street run from me.<verse eid="PSA 31:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 31:12"/>I am forgotten as a dead man whom no one thinks about. I am like a broken pot.<verse eid="PSA 31:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 31:13"/>For I have heard the whispering of many, terrifying news from every side as they plot together against me. They plot to take away my life.<verse eid="PSA 31:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 31:14"/>But I trust in you, Yahweh; I say, “You are my God.”<verse eid="PSA 31:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 31:15"/>My times are in your hand. Rescue me from the hands of my enemies and from those who pursue me.<verse eid="PSA 31:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 31:16"/>Make your face shine on your servant; save me in your covenant faithfulness.<verse eid="PSA 31:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 31:17"/>Do not let me be humiliated, Yahweh; for I call out to you! May the wicked be humiliated! May they be silent in Sheol.<verse eid="PSA 31:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 31:18"/>May lying lips be silenced that speak against the righteous defiantly with arrogance and contempt.<verse eid="PSA 31:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 31:19"/>How great is your goodness that you have stored up for those who revere you, that you perform for those who take refuge in you before all the children of mankind!<verse eid="PSA 31:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 31:20"/>In the shelter of your presence, you hide them from the plots of men. You hide them in a shelter from the violence of tongues.<verse eid="PSA 31:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 31:21"/>Blessed be Yahweh, for he showed me his marvelous covenant faithfulness when I was in a besieged city.<verse eid="PSA 31:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 31:22"/>Though I said in my haste, “I am cut off from your eyes,” yet you heard my plea for help when I cried to you.<verse eid="PSA 31:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 31:23"/>Love Yahweh, all you faithful ones. Yahweh protects the faithful, but he pays back the arrogant in full.<verse eid="PSA 31:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 31:24"/>Be strong and confident, all you who trust in Yahweh for help.<verse eid="PSA 31:24"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 31"/>
<chapter number="32" style="c" sid="PSA 32"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 32:1"/>A psalm of David. A maschil. A writing of David Blessed is the person whose transgression is forgiven, whose sin is covered.<verse eid="PSA 32:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 32:2"/>Blessed is the man to whom Yahweh reckons no guilt and in whose spirit there is no deceit.<verse eid="PSA 32:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 32:3"/>When I remained silent, my bones were wasting away while I groaned all day long.<verse eid="PSA 32:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 32:4"/>For day and night your hand was heavy upon me. My strength withered as in summer drought. <verse eid="PSA 32:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 32:5"/>Then I acknowledged my sin to you, and I no longer hid my iniquity. I said, “I will confess my transgressions to Yahweh,” and you forgave the guilt of my sin. <verse eid="PSA 32:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 32:6"/>For this reason every one of your faithful followers should pray to you at a time of great distress. When the surging waters overflow, the waters will not reach them.<verse eid="PSA 32:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 32:7"/>You are my hiding place; you will guard me from trouble. You will surround me with the songs of victory. <verse eid="PSA 32:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 32:8"/>I will instruct you and teach you in the way which you should go. I will instruct you with my eye upon you.<verse eid="PSA 32:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 32:9"/>Do not be like a horse or like a mule, which have no understanding; it is only with bridle and bit to control them that they will go where you want them to.<verse eid="PSA 32:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 32:10"/>The wicked have many sorrows, but Yahweh’s covenant faithfulness will surround the one who trusts in him.<verse eid="PSA 32:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 32:11"/>Be glad in Yahweh, and rejoice, you righteous; shout for joy, all you who are upright in heart.<verse eid="PSA 32:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 32"/>
<chapter number="33" style="c" sid="PSA 33"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 33:1"/>Rejoice in Yahweh, you righteous; praise is appropriate for the upright.<verse eid="PSA 33:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 33:2"/>Give thanks to Yahweh with the harp; sing praises to him with the harp of ten strings.<verse eid="PSA 33:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 33:3"/>Sing to him a new song; play skillfully and sing with joy.<verse eid="PSA 33:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 33:4"/>For Yahweh’s word is upright, and everything he does is fair.<verse eid="PSA 33:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 33:5"/>He loves righteousness and justice. The earth is full of Yahweh’s covenant faithfulness.<verse eid="PSA 33:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 33:6"/>By the word of Yahweh the heavens were made, and all the stars were made by the breath of his mouth.<verse eid="PSA 33:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 33:7"/>He gathers the waters of the sea together like a heap; he puts the oceans in storehouses.<verse eid="PSA 33:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 33:8"/>Let the whole earth fear Yahweh; let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of him.<verse eid="PSA 33:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 33:9"/>For he spoke, and it was done; he commanded, and it stood in place.<verse eid="PSA 33:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 33:10"/>Yahweh frustrates the alliances of nations; he overrules the plans of the peoples.<verse eid="PSA 33:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 33:11"/>The plans of Yahweh stand forever, the plans of his heart for all generations.<verse eid="PSA 33:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 33:12"/>Blessed is the nation whose God is Yahweh, the people whom he has chosen as his own inheritance.<verse eid="PSA 33:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 33:13"/>Yahweh looks from heaven; he sees all the people.<verse eid="PSA 33:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 33:14"/>From the place where he lives, he looks down on all who live on the earth.<verse eid="PSA 33:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 33:15"/>He who shapes the hearts of them all observes all their deeds.<verse eid="PSA 33:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 33:16"/>No king is saved by a vast army; a warrior is not saved by his great strength.<verse eid="PSA 33:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 33:17"/>A horse is a false hope for victory; in spite of his great strength, he cannot rescue.<verse eid="PSA 33:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 33:18"/>See, Yahweh’s eye is on those who fear him, on those who hope in his covenant faithfulness<verse eid="PSA 33:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 33:19"/>to deliver their lives from death and to keep them alive in times of famine.<verse eid="PSA 33:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 33:20"/>We wait for Yahweh; he is our help and our shield.<verse eid="PSA 33:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 33:21"/>Our hearts rejoice in him, for we trust in his holy name.<verse eid="PSA 33:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 33:22"/>Let your covenant faithfulness, Yahweh, be with us as we put our hope in you.<verse eid="PSA 33:22"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 33"/>
<chapter number="34" style="c" sid="PSA 34"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 34:1"/>A psalm of David; when he pretended to be insane before Abimelech, who drove him out. I will praise Yahweh at all times, his praise will always be in my mouth.<verse eid="PSA 34:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 34:2"/>I will praise Yahweh! May the oppressed hear and rejoice.<verse eid="PSA 34:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 34:3"/>Praise Yahweh with me, let us lift up his name together.<verse eid="PSA 34:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 34:4"/>I sought Yahweh and he answered me, and he gave me victory over all my fears.<verse eid="PSA 34:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 34:5"/>Those who look to him are radiant, and their faces are not ashamed.<verse eid="PSA 34:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 34:6"/>This oppressed man cried and Yahweh heard him and saved him from all his troubles.<verse eid="PSA 34:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 34:7"/>The angel of Yahweh camps around those who fear him and rescues them.<verse eid="PSA 34:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 34:8"/>Taste and see that Yahweh is good. Blessed is the man who takes refuge in him.<verse eid="PSA 34:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 34:9"/>Fear Yahweh, you his holy people. There is no lack for those who fear him.<verse eid="PSA 34:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 34:10"/>The young lions sometimes lack food and suffer hunger, but those who seek Yahweh will not lack anything good.<verse eid="PSA 34:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 34:11"/>Come, sons, listen to me. I will teach you the fear of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 34:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 34:12"/>What man is there who desires life and loves many days, that he may see good?<verse eid="PSA 34:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 34:13"/>Then keep your tongue from evil and keep your lips from speaking lies.<verse eid="PSA 34:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 34:14"/>Turn away from evil and do good. Seek peace and go after it.<verse eid="PSA 34:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 34:15"/>The eyes of Yahweh are on the righteous and his ears are directed toward their cry.<verse eid="PSA 34:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 34:16"/>The face of Yahweh is against those who do evil, to cut off the memory of them from the earth.<verse eid="PSA 34:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 34:17"/>The righteous cry out and Yahweh hears and he rescues them from all their troubles.<verse eid="PSA 34:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 34:18"/>Yahweh is close to the brokenhearted, and he saves those who are crushed in spirit.<verse eid="PSA 34:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 34:19"/>Many are the troubles of the righteous, but Yahweh delivers them out of them all.<verse eid="PSA 34:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 34:20"/>He keeps all his bones, not one of them will be broken.<verse eid="PSA 34:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 34:21"/>Evil will kill the wicked. Those who hate the righteous will be condemned.<verse eid="PSA 34:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 34:22"/>Yahweh rescues the lives of his servants. None of those who take refuge in him will be condemned.<verse eid="PSA 34:22"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 34"/>
<chapter number="35" style="c" sid="PSA 35"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 35:1"/>A psalm of David. David Yahweh, work against those who work against me; fight against those who fight against me.<verse eid="PSA 35:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 35:2"/>Grab your small shield and large shield; rise up and help me.<verse eid="PSA 35:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 35:3"/>Use your spear and battle ax against those who chase me; say to my soul, “I am your salvation.”<verse eid="PSA 35:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 35:4"/>May those who seek my life be shamed and dishonored. May those who plan to harm me be turned back and confounded.<verse eid="PSA 35:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 35:5"/>May they be as chaff before the wind, as the angel of Yahweh drives them away.<verse eid="PSA 35:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 35:6"/>May their way be dark and slippery, as the angel of Yahweh chases them.<verse eid="PSA 35:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 35:7"/>Without cause they set their net for me; without cause they dug a pit for my life.<verse eid="PSA 35:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 35:8"/>Let destruction overtake them by surprise. Let the net that they have set catch them. Let them fall into it, to their destruction.<verse eid="PSA 35:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 35:9"/>But I will be joyful in Yahweh and rejoice in his salvation.<verse eid="PSA 35:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 35:10"/>All my bones will say, “Yahweh, who is like you, who rescues the oppressed from those who are too strong for them and the poor and needy from those who try to rob them?”<verse eid="PSA 35:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 35:11"/>Unrighteous witnesses rise up; they accuse me falsely.<verse eid="PSA 35:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 35:12"/>They repay me evil for good. I am sorrowful.<verse eid="PSA 35:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 35:13"/>But, when they were sick, I wore sackcloth; I fasted for them with my head bowed on my chest.<verse eid="PSA 35:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 35:14"/>I went about in grief as for my brother; I bent down in mourning as for my mother.<verse eid="PSA 35:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 35:15"/>But when I stumbled, they rejoiced and gathered together; they gathered together against me, and I was surprised by them. They tore at me without stopping.<verse eid="PSA 35:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 35:16"/>With no respect at all they mocked me; they grind their teeth at me in rage.<verse eid="PSA 35:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 35:17"/>Lord, how long will you look on? Rescue my soul from their destructive attacks, my life from the lions.<verse eid="PSA 35:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 35:18"/>Then I will thank you in the great assembly; I will praise you among many people.<verse eid="PSA 35:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 35:19"/>Do not let my deceitful enemies rejoice over me; do not let them carry out their wicked schemes.<verse eid="PSA 35:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 35:20"/>For they do not speak peace, but they devise deceitful words against those in our land who live in peace.<verse eid="PSA 35:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 35:21"/>They open their mouths wide against me; they said, “Aha, Aha, our eyes have seen it.”<verse eid="PSA 35:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 35:22"/>You have seen it, Yahweh, do not be silent; Lord, do not be far from me.<verse eid="PSA 35:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 35:23"/>Arouse yourself and awake to my defense; My God and my Lord, defend my cause.<verse eid="PSA 35:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 35:24"/>Defend me, Yahweh my God, because of your righteousness; do not let them rejoice over me.<verse eid="PSA 35:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 35:25"/>Do not let them say in their heart, “Aha, we have what we wanted.” Do not let them say, “We have devoured him.”<verse eid="PSA 35:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 35:26"/>May they be put to shame and may they be confounded who rejoice at my distress. May those who exalt themselves over me be clothed with shame and dishonor.<verse eid="PSA 35:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 35:27"/>Let those who desire my vindication shout for joy and be glad; may they say continually, “Yahweh be praised, he who delights in the welfare of his servant.”<verse eid="PSA 35:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 35:28"/>Then I will tell of your justice and praise you all day long.<verse eid="PSA 35:28"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 35"/>
<chapter number="36" style="c" sid="PSA 36"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 36:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David the servant of Yahweh. An evil man speaks of his transgression from deep in his heart, there is no fear of God before his eyes.<verse eid="PSA 36:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 36:2"/>For he comforts himself, thinking that his sin will not be discovered and be hated.<verse eid="PSA 36:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 36:3"/>His words are sinful and deceitful; he does not want to be wise and do good.<verse eid="PSA 36:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 36:4"/>While he lies in bed, he plans ways to sin; he sets out on an evil way; he does not reject evil.<verse eid="PSA 36:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 36:5"/>Your covenant faithfulness, Yahweh, reaches to the heavens; your loyalty reaches to the clouds.<verse eid="PSA 36:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 36:6"/>Your righteousness is like the mountains of God; your judgments are like the great deep. Yahweh, you preserve both mankind and the animals.<verse eid="PSA 36:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 36:7"/>How precious is your covenant faithfulness, God! Humanity takes refuge under the shadow of your wings.<verse eid="PSA 36:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 36:8"/>They feast upon the abundance of your house; you let them drink from the river of your delights.<verse eid="PSA 36:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 36:9"/>For with you is the fountain of life; in your light we will see light.<verse eid="PSA 36:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 36:10"/>Extend your covenant faithfulness fully to those who know you, your defense to the upright of heart.<verse eid="PSA 36:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 36:11"/>Do not let the foot of the arrogant man come near to me. Do not let the hand of the wicked drive me away.<verse eid="PSA 36:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 36:12"/>Over there the evildoers have fallen; they are knocked down and are not able to get up.<verse eid="PSA 36:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 36"/>
<chapter number="37" style="c" sid="PSA 37"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 37:1"/>A psalm of David. David Do not be irritated because of evildoers; do not be envious of those who act unrighteously.<verse eid="PSA 37:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 37:2"/>For they will soon dry up as the grass and wither as the green plants.<verse eid="PSA 37:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 37:3"/>Trust in Yahweh and do what is good; settle in the land and graze in faithfulness.<verse eid="PSA 37:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 37:4"/>Then delight yourself in Yahweh, and he will give you the desires of your heart.<verse eid="PSA 37:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 37:5"/>Give your ways to Yahweh; trust in him, and he will act on your behalf.<verse eid="PSA 37:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 37:6"/>He will display your justice like the daylight and your innocence like the day at noon.<verse eid="PSA 37:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 37:7"/>Be still before Yahweh and wait patiently for him. Do not be angry if someone succeeds in what he does, or when he makes evil plots.<verse eid="PSA 37:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 37:8"/>Do not be angry and frustrated. Do not worry. This only makes trouble.<verse eid="PSA 37:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 37:9"/>Evildoers will be cut off, but those who wait for Yahweh will inherit the land.<verse eid="PSA 37:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 37:10"/>In a little while the evil man will disappear; you will look at his place, but he will be gone.<verse eid="PSA 37:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 37:11"/>But the meek will inherit the land and will delight in great prosperity.<verse eid="PSA 37:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 37:12"/>The wicked man plots against the righteous and he grinds his teeth in rage against him.<verse eid="PSA 37:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 37:13"/>The Lord laughs at him, for he sees that his day is coming.<verse eid="PSA 37:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 37:14"/>The wicked have drawn out their swords and have bent their bows to cast down the oppressed and needy, to kill those who are upright.<verse eid="PSA 37:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 37:15"/>Their swords will pierce their own hearts, and their bows will be broken.<verse eid="PSA 37:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 37:16"/>Better is the little that the righteous has than the abundance of many wicked people.<verse eid="PSA 37:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 37:17"/>For the arms of the wicked people will be broken, but Yahweh supports the righteous people.<verse eid="PSA 37:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 37:18"/>Yahweh watches over the blameless day by day, and their heritage will be forever.<verse eid="PSA 37:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 37:19"/>They will not be ashamed when times are bad. When famine comes, they will have enough to eat.<verse eid="PSA 37:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 37:20"/>But evil men will perish. Yahweh’s enemies will be like the glory of the pastures; they will be consumed and disappear in the smoke.<verse eid="PSA 37:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 37:21"/>The wicked person borrows but does not repay, but the righteous person is generous and gives.<verse eid="PSA 37:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 37:22"/>Those who are blessed by God will inherit the land; those who are cursed by him will be cut off.<verse eid="PSA 37:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 37:23"/>It is by Yahweh that a man’s steps are established, the man whose way is commendable in God’s sight.<verse eid="PSA 37:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 37:24"/>Though he stumbles, he will not fall down, for Yahweh is holding him with his hand.<verse eid="PSA 37:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 37:25"/>I was young and now am old; I have never seen the righteous person abandoned or his children begging for bread.<verse eid="PSA 37:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 37:26"/>All the day long he is gracious and lends, and his children become a blessing.<verse eid="PSA 37:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 37:27"/>Turn away from evil and do what is right; then you will be safe forever.<verse eid="PSA 37:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 37:28"/>For Yahweh loves justice and does not abandon his faithful ones. They are preserved forever, but the descendants of the wicked will be cut off.<verse eid="PSA 37:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 37:29"/>The righteous will inherit the land and live there forever.<verse eid="PSA 37:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 37:30"/>The mouth of the righteous person speaks wisdom and increases justice.<verse eid="PSA 37:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 37:31"/>The law of his God is in his heart; his feet will not slip.<verse eid="PSA 37:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 37:32"/>The wicked person watches the righteous person and seeks to kill him.<verse eid="PSA 37:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 37:33"/>Yahweh will not abandon him into the evil person’s hand or condemn him when he is judged.<verse eid="PSA 37:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 37:34"/>Wait for Yahweh and keep his way, and he will raise you up to possess the land. You will see when the wicked are cut off.<verse eid="PSA 37:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 37:35"/>I have seen the wicked and terrifying person spread out like a green tree in its native soil.<verse eid="PSA 37:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 37:36"/>But when I passed by again, he was not there. I looked for him, but he could not be found.<verse eid="PSA 37:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 37:37"/>Observe the man of integrity, and mark the upright; there is a good future for a man of peace.<verse eid="PSA 37:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 37:38"/>Sinners will be totally destroyed; the future for the wicked man is cut off.<verse eid="PSA 37:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 37:39"/>Salvation of the righteous comes from Yahweh; he protects them in the times of trouble.<verse eid="PSA 37:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 37:40"/>Yahweh helps them and rescues them. He rescues them from evil men and saves them because they have taken refuge in him.<verse eid="PSA 37:40"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 37"/>
<chapter number="38" style="c" sid="PSA 38"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 38:1"/>A psalm of David, to bring to remembrance. Yahweh, do not rebuke me in your anger; do not punish me in your wrath.<verse eid="PSA 38:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 38:2"/>For your arrows pierce me, and your hand presses me down.<verse eid="PSA 38:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 38:3"/>My whole body is sick because of your anger; there is no health in my bones because of my sin.<verse eid="PSA 38:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 38:4"/>For my iniquities overwhelm me; they are a burden too heavy for me.<verse eid="PSA 38:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 38:5"/>My wounds are infected and smell because of my foolish sins.<verse eid="PSA 38:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 38:6"/>I am stooped over and humiliated every day; I go about mourning all day long.<verse eid="PSA 38:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 38:7"/>For within me, I am filled with burning; there is no health in my flesh.<verse eid="PSA 38:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 38:8"/>I am numb and utterly crushed; I groan because of the anguish of my heart.<verse eid="PSA 38:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 38:9"/>Lord, you understand my heart’s deepest yearnings, and my groanings are not hidden from you.<verse eid="PSA 38:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 38:10"/>My heart pounds, my strength fades, and my eyesight dims.<verse eid="PSA 38:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 38:11"/>My friends and companions shun me because of my condition; my neighbors stand far off.<verse eid="PSA 38:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 38:12"/>Those who seek my life lay snares for me. They who seek my harm speak destructive words and say deceitful words all day long.<verse eid="PSA 38:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 38:13"/>But I, I am like a deaf man and hear nothing; I am like a mute man who says nothing.<verse eid="PSA 38:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 38:14"/>I am like a man who does not hear and who has no reply.<verse eid="PSA 38:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 38:15"/>Surely I wait for you, Yahweh; you will answer, Lord my God.<verse eid="PSA 38:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 38:16"/>For I said "Hear me, so that they will not gloat over me. If my foot slips, they will do terrible things to me.<verse eid="PSA 38:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 38:17"/>For I am about to stumble, and I am in constant pain.<verse eid="PSA 38:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 38:18"/>I confess my guilt; I am concerned about my sin.<verse eid="PSA 38:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 38:19"/>But my enemies are numerous; those who hate me wrongfully are many.<verse eid="PSA 38:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 38:20"/>They repay me evil for good; they hurl accusations at me although I have pursued what is good.<verse eid="PSA 38:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 38:21"/>Do not abandon me, Yahweh; my God, do not stay far away from me.<verse eid="PSA 38:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 38:22"/>Come quickly to help me, Lord, my salvation.<verse eid="PSA 38:22"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 38"/>
<chapter number="39" style="c" sid="PSA 39"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 39:1"/>For the chief musician, for Jeduthun. A psalm of David. I decided, “I will watch what I say so that I do not sin with my tongue. I will muzzle my mouth while in the presence of an evil man.”<verse eid="PSA 39:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 39:2"/>I kept silent; I kept back my words even from saying anything good, and my pain grew worse.<verse eid="PSA 39:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 39:3"/>My heart became hot; when I thought about these things, it burned like a fire. Then finally I spoke.<verse eid="PSA 39:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 39:4"/>“Yahweh, make me know when will be the end of my life and the extent of my days. Show me how transient I am.<verse eid="PSA 39:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 39:5"/>See, you have made my days only the width of my hand, and my lifetime is like nothing before you. Surely every man is a single breath. <verse eid="PSA 39:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 39:6"/>Surely every man walks about like a shadow. Surely everyone hurries about to accumulate riches although they do not know who will receive them.<verse eid="PSA 39:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 39:7"/>Now, Lord, for what am I waiting? You are my only hope.<verse eid="PSA 39:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 39:8"/>Rescue me from my sins; do not make me the reproach of fools.<verse eid="PSA 39:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 39:9"/>I am silent and cannot open my mouth, because it is you who has done it.<verse eid="PSA 39:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 39:10"/>Stop wounding me; I am overwhelmed by the blow of your hand.<verse eid="PSA 39:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 39:11"/>When you discipline people for sin, you consume the things they desire like a moth; surely all people are nothing but vapor. <verse eid="PSA 39:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 39:12"/>Hear my prayer, Yahweh, and listen to me; listen to my weeping! Do not be deaf to me, for I am like a foreigner with you, a refugee like all my ancestors were.<verse eid="PSA 39:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 39:13"/>Turn your gaze from me so that I may smile again before I die.”<verse eid="PSA 39:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 39"/>
<chapter number="40" style="c" sid="PSA 40"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 40:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. I waited patiently for Yahweh; he listened to me and heard my cry.<verse eid="PSA 40:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 40:2"/>He brought me up out of a horrible pit, out of the miry clay, and he set my feet on a rock and made my steps secure.<verse eid="PSA 40:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 40:3"/>He has put a new song in my mouth, praise to our God. Many will see it and honor him and will trust in Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 40:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 40:4"/>Blessed is the man who makes Yahweh his trust and does not honor the proud or those who turn away from him to lies.<verse eid="PSA 40:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 40:5"/>Many, Yahweh my God, are the wonderful deeds that you have done, and your thoughts which are about us cannot be numbered; if I declared and spoke of them, they would be more than could be counted.<verse eid="PSA 40:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 40:6"/>You have no delight in sacrifice or offering, but you have opened my ears; you have not required burnt offerings or sin offerings.<verse eid="PSA 40:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 40:7"/>Then said I, “See, I have come; it is written about me in the scroll of the document.<verse eid="PSA 40:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 40:8"/>I delight to do your will, my God; your laws are in my heart.”<verse eid="PSA 40:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 40:9"/>I have proclaimed good news of your righteousness in the great assembly; Yahweh, you know that my lips have not kept back from doing this.<verse eid="PSA 40:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 40:10"/>I have not concealed your righteousness in my heart; I have declared your faithfulness and your salvation; I have not concealed your covenant faithfulness or your trustworthiness from the great assembly.<verse eid="PSA 40:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 40:11"/>Do not keep back your acts of mercy from me, Yahweh; let your covenant faithfulness and your trustworthiness always preserve me.<verse eid="PSA 40:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 40:12"/>Troubles that cannot be numbered surround me; my iniquities have caught up with me so that I am no longer able to see anything; they are more than the hairs on my head, and my heart has failed me.<verse eid="PSA 40:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 40:13"/>Be pleased, Yahweh, to rescue me; hurry to help me, Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 40:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 40:14"/>Let them be ashamed and completely disappointed who pursue my life to take it away. Let them be turned back and brought to dishonor, those who delight in hurting me.<verse eid="PSA 40:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 40:15"/>Let them be shocked because of their shame, those who say to me, “Aha, aha!”<verse eid="PSA 40:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 40:16"/>But may all those who seek you rejoice and be glad in you; let everyone who loves your salvation say continually, “May Yahweh be praised.”<verse eid="PSA 40:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 40:17"/>I am poor and needy; yet the Lord thinks about me. You are my help and you come to my rescue; do not delay, my God.<verse eid="PSA 40:17"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 40"/>
<chapter number="41" style="c" sid="PSA 41"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 41:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. Blessed is he who is concerned for the weak; in the day of trouble, Yahweh will rescue him.<verse eid="PSA 41:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 41:2"/>Yahweh will preserve him and keep him alive, and he will be blessed on the earth; Yahweh will not turn him over to the will of his enemies.<verse eid="PSA 41:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 41:3"/>Yahweh will support him on the bed of suffering; you will make his bed of sickness into a bed of healing.<verse eid="PSA 41:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 41:4"/>I said, “Yahweh, have mercy on me! Heal me, for I have sinned against you.”<verse eid="PSA 41:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 41:5"/>My enemies speak evil against me, saying, ‘When will he die and his name perish?’<verse eid="PSA 41:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 41:6"/>If my enemy comes to see me, he says worthless things; his heart gathers up my disaster for itself; when he goes away from me, he tells others about it.<verse eid="PSA 41:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 41:7"/>All who hate me whisper together against me; against me they hope for my hurt.<verse eid="PSA 41:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 41:8"/>They say, “An evil disease holds on tightly to him; now that he is lying down, he will rise up no more.”<verse eid="PSA 41:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 41:9"/>Indeed, even my own close friend, in whom I trusted, who ate my bread, has lifted up his heel against me.<verse eid="PSA 41:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 41:10"/>But you, Yahweh, have mercy on me and raise me up so that I may pay them back.<verse eid="PSA 41:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 41:11"/>By this I know that you delight in me, for my enemy does not triumph over me.<verse eid="PSA 41:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 41:12"/>As for me, you support me in my integrity and will keep me before your face forever.<verse eid="PSA 41:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 41:13"/>May Yahweh, the God of Israel be praised from everlasting to everlasting. Amen and Amen.<verse eid="PSA 41:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 41"/>
<chapter number="42" style="c" sid="PSA 42"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 42:1"/>For the chief musician. A maschil of the sons of Korah. As a deer longs for streams of water, so my soul longs for you, God.<verse eid="PSA 42:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 42:2"/>My soul thirsts for God, for the living God. When will I come and appear before the face of God?<verse eid="PSA 42:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 42:3"/>My tears are my food day and night, as {people are} saying to me every day, “Where is your God?”<verse eid="PSA 42:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 42:4"/>These things I remember, and I pour out my soul within myself: I traveled with the crowd and accompanied them to the house of God with a voice of joy and praise, a multitude celebrating a festival.<verse eid="PSA 42:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 42:5"/>Why are you bowed down, O my soul, and upset within me? Hope in God, for again I will praise him,  the salvation of my face<verse eid="PSA 42:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 42:6"/>and my God.  My soul is bowed down within me, therefore I remember you from the land of the Jordan and the Hermons, and from Mount Mizar.<verse eid="PSA 42:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 42:7"/>Deep is calling to deep at the sound of your waterfalls; All of your waves and your billows flow over me.<verse eid="PSA 42:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 42:8"/>During the day, Yahweh commands his covenant faithfulness, and in the night, his song is with me— a prayer to the God of my life.<verse eid="PSA 42:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 42:9"/>I will say to God, my rock, “Why have you forgotten me? Why do I walk around mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?”<verse eid="PSA 42:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 42:10"/>In the crushing of my bones, those who are hostile to me rebuke me when they are saying to me all day long, “Where is your God?”<verse eid="PSA 42:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 42:11"/>Why are you bowed down, O my soul? And why are you upset within me? Hope in God, for again I will give him thanks,  the salvation of my face is my God.<verse eid="PSA 42:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 42"/>
<chapter number="43" style="c" sid="PSA 43"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 43:1"/>Declare me righteous, O God, and defend my case against a nation that is not faithful. Deliver me from a deceitful and evil man.<verse eid="PSA 43:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 43:2"/>For you are the God of my fortification. Why have you rejected me? Why do I walk around mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?<verse eid="PSA 43:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 43:3"/>Send out your light and your truth, let them lead me. Let them bring me to your holy mountain and to your dwelling place.<verse eid="PSA 43:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 43:4"/>I will go to the altar of God, to the God of the joy of my gladness. I will praise you with the lyre, O God, my God.<verse eid="PSA 43:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 43:5"/>Why are you bowed down, O my soul? And why are you upset within me? Hope in God, for again I will give him thanks,  the salvation of my face is my God.<verse eid="PSA 43:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 43"/>
<chapter number="44" style="c" sid="PSA 44"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 44:1"/>For the chief musician. Of the sons of Korah. A maschil. O God, we have listened with our ears, our fathers have told us the work you did in their days, in the days of old.<verse eid="PSA 44:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 44:2"/>You drove out the nations {by} your hand, but you planted them. You afflicted the peoples, but you sent them.<verse eid="PSA 44:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 44:3"/>For with their sword they did not possess the land, and their arm did not save them, but your right hand, and your arm, and the light of your face, because you were pleased with them.<verse eid="PSA 44:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 44:4"/>You are my king, O God. Appoint salvation for Jacob.<verse eid="PSA 44:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 44:5"/>Through you we will gore our adversaries, by your name we will trample those who rise up against us.<verse eid="PSA 44:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 44:6"/>For I will not trust in my bow, and my sword will not save me.<verse eid="PSA 44:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 44:7"/>For you have saved us from our adversaries, and have put to shame those who hate us.<verse eid="PSA 44:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 44:8"/>In God we have boasted every day, and we will praise your name forever. <verse eid="PSA 44:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 44:9"/>Yet, you have rejected and humiliated us, and you do not go out with our armies.<verse eid="PSA 44:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 44:10"/>You made us turn back from the adversary, and those who hate us plunder for themselves.<verse eid="PSA 44:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 44:11"/>You have appoint us {to be} like sheep for food, and you have scattered us among the nations.<verse eid="PSA 44:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 44:12"/>You have sold your people for what is not valuable, you have not increased their price.<verse eid="PSA 44:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 44:13"/>You have made us a reproach to our neighbors, a contempt and a scorn to those around us.<verse eid="PSA 44:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 44:14"/>You made us an insult among the nations, a shaking of the head among the peoples.<verse eid="PSA 44:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 44:15"/>All day my dishonor is before me, and the shame of my face has covered me<verse eid="PSA 44:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 44:16"/>from of the voice of reproaching and insulting, and from the face of an enemy and a vengeful one.<verse eid="PSA 44:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 44:17"/>All of this has come {against} us, and we have not forgotten you, and we have not dealt falsely with your covenant.<verse eid="PSA 44:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 44:18"/>Our heart has not turned back, our steps bent from your way.<verse eid="PSA 44:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 44:19"/>But you have crushed us in the place of jackals, and you have covered over us with extreme darkness.<verse eid="PSA 44:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 44:20"/>If we had forgotten the name of our God and spread out our hands to a foreign god,<verse eid="PSA 44:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 44:21"/>would God not have discovered this? For he knows the secrets of the heart.<verse eid="PSA 44:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 44:22"/>Indeed, because of you we are killed all the day, we are considered {to be} like sheep of slaughtering.<verse eid="PSA 44:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 44:23"/>Awake! Why do you sleep, Lord? Arise! Do not reject {us} forever!<verse eid="PSA 44:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 44:24"/>Why do you hide your face and forget our affliction and our oppression?<verse eid="PSA 44:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 44:25"/>For our life has sunk down into the dust, our belly has clung to the earth.<verse eid="PSA 44:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 44:26"/>Rise up {as) our helper and redeem us because of your covenant faithfulness.<verse eid="PSA 44:26"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 44"/>
<chapter number="45" style="c" sid="PSA 45"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 45:1"/>For the chief musician; set to Shoshannim. A psalm of the sons of Korah. A maschil. A song of loves. My heart overflows on a good subject; I will read aloud the words I have composed about the king; my tongue is the pen of a ready writer.<verse eid="PSA 45:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 45:2"/>You are fairer than the children of mankind; grace is poured onto your lips; therefore we know that God has blessed you forever.<verse eid="PSA 45:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 45:3"/>Put your sword on your side, mighty one, in your glory and your majesty.<verse eid="PSA 45:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 45:4"/>In your majesty ride on triumphantly because of trustworthiness, meekness, and righteousness; your right hand will teach you fearful things.<verse eid="PSA 45:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 45:5"/>Your arrows are sharp; the peoples fall under you; your arrows are in the hearts of the king’s enemies.<verse eid="PSA 45:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 45:6"/>Your throne, God, is forever and ever; a scepter of justice is the scepter of your kingdom.<verse eid="PSA 45:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 45:7"/>You have loved righteousness and hated wickedness; therefore God, your God, has anointed you with the oil of gladness more than your companions.<verse eid="PSA 45:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 45:8"/>All your garments smell of myrrh, aloes, and cassia; out of ivory palaces stringed instruments have made you glad.<verse eid="PSA 45:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 45:9"/>Kings’ daughters are among your honorable women; at your right hand stands the queen clothed in gold of Ophir.<verse eid="PSA 45:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 45:10"/>Listen, daughter, consider and incline your ear; forget your own people and your father’s house.<verse eid="PSA 45:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 45:11"/>In this way the king will desire your beauty; he is your master; revere him.<verse eid="PSA 45:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 45:12"/>The daughter of Tyre will be there with a gift; the rich among the people will beg for your favor.<verse eid="PSA 45:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 45:13"/>The royal daughter in the palace is all glorious; her clothing is worked with gold.<verse eid="PSA 45:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 45:14"/>She will be led to the king in embroidered dress; the virgins, her companions who follow her, will be brought to you.<verse eid="PSA 45:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 45:15"/>They will be led by gladness and rejoicing; they will enter into the king’s palace.<verse eid="PSA 45:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 45:16"/>In the place of your fathers will be your children, whom you will make princes in all the earth.<verse eid="PSA 45:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 45:17"/>I will make your name to be remembered in all generations; therefore the peoples will give you thanks forever and ever.<verse eid="PSA 45:17"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 45"/>
<chapter number="46" style="c" sid="PSA 46"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 46:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of the sons of Korah; set to Alamoth. A song. God is our refuge and strength, a very present help in trouble.<verse eid="PSA 46:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 46:2"/>Therefore we will not fear, though the earth should change, though the mountains should be shaken into the heart of the seas,<verse eid="PSA 46:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 46:3"/>though its waters roar and rage, and though the mountains tremble with their swelling. Selah<verse eid="PSA 46:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 46:4"/>There is a river whose streams make the city of God happy, the holy place where the Most High dwells.<verse eid="PSA 46:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 46:5"/>God is in the middle of her; she will not be moved; God will help her, and he will do so at the dawn of morning.<verse eid="PSA 46:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 46:6"/>The nations raged and the kingdoms were shaken; he lifted up his voice, and the earth melted.<verse eid="PSA 46:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 46:7"/>Yahweh of hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our refuge. <verse eid="PSA 46:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 46:8"/>Come, behold the deeds of Yahweh, the destruction he has caused on earth.<verse eid="PSA 46:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 46:9"/>He makes wars cease to the ends of the earth; he breaks the bow and cuts the spear into pieces; he burns up the shields.<verse eid="PSA 46:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 46:10"/>Be quiet and know that I am God; I will be exalted among the nations; I will be exalted on the earth.<verse eid="PSA 46:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 46:11"/>Yahweh of hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our refuge. <verse eid="PSA 46:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 46"/>
<chapter number="47" style="c" sid="PSA 47"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 47:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of the sons of Korah. Clap your hands, all you peoples; shout to God with the sound of triumph.<verse eid="PSA 47:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 47:2"/>For Yahweh Most High is terrifying; he is a great King over all the earth.<verse eid="PSA 47:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 47:3"/>He subdues peoples under us and nations under our feet.<verse eid="PSA 47:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 47:4"/>He chooses our inheritance for us, the glory of Jacob whom he loved. <verse eid="PSA 47:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 47:5"/>God has gone up with a shout, Yahweh with the sound of a trumpet.<verse eid="PSA 47:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 47:6"/>Sing praises to God, sing praises; sing praises to our King, sing praises.<verse eid="PSA 47:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 47:7"/>For God is the King over all the earth; sing praises with understanding.<verse eid="PSA 47:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 47:8"/>God reigns over the nations; God sits on his holy throne.<verse eid="PSA 47:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 47:9"/>The princes of the peoples have gathered together to the people of the God of Abraham; for the shields of the earth belong to God; he is greatly exalted.<verse eid="PSA 47:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 47"/>
<chapter number="48" style="c" sid="PSA 48"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 48:1"/>A song; a psalm of the sons of Korah. Great is Yahweh and greatly to be praised, in the city of our God on his holy mountain.<verse eid="PSA 48:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 48:2"/>Beautiful in elevation, the joy of the whole earth, is Mount Zion, on the sides of the north, the city of the great King.<verse eid="PSA 48:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 48:3"/>God has made himself known in her palaces as a refuge.<verse eid="PSA 48:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 48:4"/>For, see, the kings assembled themselves; they passed by together.<verse eid="PSA 48:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 48:5"/>They saw it, then they were amazed; they were dismayed, and they hurried away.<verse eid="PSA 48:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 48:6"/>Trembling took hold of them there, pain as when a woman is in labor.<verse eid="PSA 48:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 48:7"/>With the east wind you break the ships of Tarshish.<verse eid="PSA 48:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 48:8"/>As we have heard, so have we seen in the city of Yahweh of hosts, in the city of our God; God will establish it forever. <verse eid="PSA 48:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 48:9"/>We have thought about your covenant faithfulness, God, in the middle of your temple.<verse eid="PSA 48:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 48:10"/>As your name is, God, so is your praise to the ends of the earth; your right hand is full of righteousness.<verse eid="PSA 48:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 48:11"/>Let Mount Zion be glad, let the daughters of Judah rejoice because of your righteous decrees.<verse eid="PSA 48:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 48:12"/>Walk around Mount Zion, go round about her; count her towers,<verse eid="PSA 48:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 48:13"/>notice well her walls, and look at her palaces so that you may tell it to the next generation.<verse eid="PSA 48:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 48:14"/>For this God is our God forever and ever; he will be our guide to death.<verse eid="PSA 48:14"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 48"/>
<chapter number="49" style="c" sid="PSA 49"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 49:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of the sons of Korah. Hear this, all you peoples; give ear, all you inhabitants of the world,<verse eid="PSA 49:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 49:2"/>both low and high, rich and poor together.<verse eid="PSA 49:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 49:3"/>My mouth will speak wisdom and the meditation of my heart will be of understanding.<verse eid="PSA 49:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 49:4"/>I will incline my ear to a parable; I will begin my parable with the harp.<verse eid="PSA 49:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 49:5"/>Why should I fear the days of evil, when iniquity surrounds me at my heels?<verse eid="PSA 49:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 49:6"/>Why should I fear those who trust in their wealth and boast about the amount of their riches?<verse eid="PSA 49:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 49:7"/>It is certain that no one can redeem his brother or give God a ransom for him,<verse eid="PSA 49:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 49:8"/>For the redemption of one’s life is costly, and no one can pay what we owe.<verse eid="PSA 49:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 49:9"/>No one can live forever so that his body should not decay.<verse eid="PSA 49:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 49:10"/>For he will see decay. Wise men die; the fool and the brute alike perish and leave their wealth to others.<verse eid="PSA 49:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 49:11"/>Their inner thought is that their families will continue forever, and the places where they live, to all generations; they call their lands after their own names.<verse eid="PSA 49:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 49:12"/>But man, having wealth, does not remain alive; he is like the beasts that perish.<verse eid="PSA 49:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 49:13"/>This, their way, is their folly; yet after them, men approve of their sayings. <verse eid="PSA 49:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 49:14"/>Like sheep they are appointed for Sheol, and death will be their shepherd. The upright will rule over them in the morning, and their bodies will be consumed in Sheol, with no place for them to live.<verse eid="PSA 49:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 49:15"/>But God will redeem my life from the power of Sheol; he will receive me. <verse eid="PSA 49:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 49:16"/>Do not be afraid when one becomes rich, and the glory of his house increases.<verse eid="PSA 49:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 49:17"/>For when he dies he will take nothing away; his glory will not go down after him.<verse eid="PSA 49:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 49:18"/>He blessed his soul while he lived— and men praise you when you live for yourself—<verse eid="PSA 49:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 49:19"/>he will go to the generation of his fathers and they will never see the light again.<verse eid="PSA 49:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 49:20"/>One who has wealth but no understanding is like the beasts, which perish.<verse eid="PSA 49:20"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 49"/>
<chapter number="50" style="c" sid="PSA 50"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 50:1"/>A psalm of Asaph. A Psalm of Asaph The Mighty One, God, Yahweh, has spoken and called the earth from the rising of the sun to its setting.<verse eid="PSA 50:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 50:2"/>Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty, God has shone.<verse eid="PSA 50:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 50:3"/>Our God comes and does not stay silent; a fire devours before him, and it is very stormy around him.<verse eid="PSA 50:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 50:4"/>He calls to the heavens above and to the earth so that he may judge his people:<verse eid="PSA 50:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 50:5"/>“Gather my faithful ones together to me, those who have made a covenant with me by sacrifice.”<verse eid="PSA 50:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 50:6"/>The heavens will declare his righteousness, for God himself is judge. <verse eid="PSA 50:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 50:7"/>“Israel, I will testify against you. Hear, my people, and I will speak; I am God, your God.<verse eid="PSA 50:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 50:8"/>I will not reprove you for your sacrifices; your burnt offerings are always before me.<verse eid="PSA 50:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 50:9"/>I will take no bull out of your house, or male goats out of your folds.<verse eid="PSA 50:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 50:10"/>For every beast of the forest is mine, and the cattle on a thousand hills.<verse eid="PSA 50:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 50:11"/>I know all the birds of the mountains, and the wild beasts of the field are mine.<verse eid="PSA 50:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 50:12"/>If I were hungry, I would not tell you; for the world is mine, and everything in it.<verse eid="PSA 50:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 50:13"/>Will I eat the flesh of bulls or drink the blood of goats?<verse eid="PSA 50:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 50:14"/>Offer to God the sacrifice of thanksgiving, and pay your vows to the Most High.<verse eid="PSA 50:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 50:15"/>Call on me in the day of trouble; I will rescue you, and you will glorify me.”<verse eid="PSA 50:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 50:16"/>But to the wicked God says, “What have you to do with declaring my statutes, that you have taken my covenant in your mouth,<verse eid="PSA 50:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 50:17"/>since you hate instruction and throw my words away?<verse eid="PSA 50:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 50:18"/>When you see a thief, you agree with him; you participate with those who commit adultery.<verse eid="PSA 50:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 50:19"/>You give your mouth to evil, and your tongue expresses deceit.<verse eid="PSA 50:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 50:20"/>You sit and speak against your brother; you slander your own mother’s son.<verse eid="PSA 50:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 50:21"/>You have done these things, but I have kept silent, so you thought that I was someone just like yourself. But I will reprove you and bring up, right before your eyes, all the things you have done.<verse eid="PSA 50:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 50:22"/>Give this careful consideration, you who forget God, otherwise I will tear you to pieces, and there will be no one to come to help you!<verse eid="PSA 50:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 50:23"/>The one who offers a sacrifice of thanksgiving praises me, and to anyone who plans his path in the right way I will show God’s salvation.”<verse eid="PSA 50:23"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 50"/>
<chapter number="51" style="c" sid="PSA 51"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 51:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David; when Nathan the prophet came to him after he had gone in to Bathsheba. Have mercy on me, God, because of your covenant faithfulness; for the sake of the multitude of your merciful actions, blot out my transgressions.<verse eid="PSA 51:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 51:2"/>Wash me thoroughly from my iniquity and cleanse me from my sin.<verse eid="PSA 51:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 51:3"/>For I know my transgressions, and my sin is always before me.<verse eid="PSA 51:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 51:4"/>Against you, you only, I have sinned and done what is evil in your sight; you are right when you speak; you are correct when you judge.<verse eid="PSA 51:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 51:5"/>See, I was born in iniquity; as soon as my mother conceived me, I was in sin.<verse eid="PSA 51:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 51:6"/>See, you desire trustworthiness in my inner self; and you teach me wisdom in the secret place within.<verse eid="PSA 51:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 51:7"/>Purify me with hyssop, and I will be clean; wash me, and I will be whiter than snow.<verse eid="PSA 51:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 51:8"/>Make me hear joy and gladness so that the bones that you have broken may rejoice.<verse eid="PSA 51:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 51:9"/>Hide your face from my sins and blot out all my iniquities.<verse eid="PSA 51:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 51:10"/>Create in me a clean heart, God, and renew a right spirit within me.<verse eid="PSA 51:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 51:11"/>Do not drive me away from your presence, and do not take your holy Spirit from me.<verse eid="PSA 51:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 51:12"/>Restore to me the joy of your salvation, and sustain me with a willing spirit.<verse eid="PSA 51:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 51:13"/>Then will I teach transgressors your ways, and sinners will be converted to you.<verse eid="PSA 51:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 51:14"/>Forgive me for shedding blood, God of my salvation, and I will shout for the joy of your righteousness.<verse eid="PSA 51:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 51:15"/>Lord, open my lips, and my mouth will express your praise.<verse eid="PSA 51:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 51:16"/>For you do not delight in sacrifice, or I would give it; you have no pleasure in burnt offerings.<verse eid="PSA 51:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 51:17"/>The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit. You, God, will not despise a broken and a contrite heart.<verse eid="PSA 51:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 51:18"/>Do good in your good pleasure to Zion; rebuild the walls of Jerusalem.<verse eid="PSA 51:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 51:19"/>Then will you delight in the sacrifices of righteousness, in burnt offerings and whole burnt offerings; then our people will offer bulls on your altar.<verse eid="PSA 51:19"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 51"/>
<chapter number="52" style="c" sid="PSA 52"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 52:1"/>For the chief musician. A maschil of David; when Doeg the Edomite came and told Saul, and said to him, “David has come to the house of Ahimelech.” Why are you proud of making trouble, you mighty man? The covenant faithfulness of God comes every day.<verse eid="PSA 52:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 52:2"/>Your tongue plans destruction like a sharp razor, working deceitfully.<verse eid="PSA 52:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 52:3"/>You love evil more than good and lying rather than speaking righteousness. <verse eid="PSA 52:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 52:4"/>You love all words that devour others, you deceitful tongue.<verse eid="PSA 52:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 52:5"/>God will likewise destroy you forever; he will take you up and pluck you out of your tent and root you out of the land of the living. <verse eid="PSA 52:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 52:6"/>The righteous will also see it and fear; they will laugh at him and say,<verse eid="PSA 52:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 52:7"/>“See, this is a man who did not make God his refuge, but he trusted in the abundance of his wealth, and he was strong when he destroyed others.”<verse eid="PSA 52:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 52:8"/>But as for me, I am like a green olive tree in God’s house; I will trust in the covenant faithfulness of God forever and ever.<verse eid="PSA 52:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 52:9"/>I will give you thanks forever for what you have done. I will wait for your name, because it is good, in the presence of your faithful ones.<verse eid="PSA 52:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 52"/>
<chapter number="53" style="c" sid="PSA 53"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 53:1"/>For the chief musician; set to Mahalath. A maschil of David. A fool says in his heart, “There is no God.” They are corrupt and have done abominable iniquity; there is no one who does good.<verse eid="PSA 53:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 53:2"/>God looks down from heaven on the children of mankind to see if there are any who understand, who seek after him.<verse eid="PSA 53:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 53:3"/>They have all turned away. Together they have become corrupt. There is not one who does good, not even one.<verse eid="PSA 53:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 53:4"/>Do those who commit iniquity have no understanding— those who devour my people as if they were eating bread and they do not call on God?<verse eid="PSA 53:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 53:5"/>They were in great fear, although no reason to fear was there; for God will scatter the bones of whoever will camp against you; such people will be put to shame because God has rejected them.<verse eid="PSA 53:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 53:6"/>Oh, that the salvation of Israel would come from Zion! When God brings back his people from the captivity, then Jacob will rejoice and Israel will be glad!<verse eid="PSA 53:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 53"/>
<chapter number="54" style="c" sid="PSA 54"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 54:1"/>For the chief musician; on stringed instruments. A maschil of David; when the Ziphites came and said to Saul, “Does David not hide himself with us?” Save me, God, by your name, and judge me in your might.<verse eid="PSA 54:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 54:2"/>Hear my prayer, God; give ear to the words of my mouth.<verse eid="PSA 54:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 54:3"/>For strangers have risen up against me, and pitiless men have sought after my life; they have not set God before them. Selah<verse eid="PSA 54:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 54:4"/>See, God is my helper; the Lord is the one who upholds me.<verse eid="PSA 54:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 54:5"/>He will repay my enemies with evil; in your faithfulness, destroy them!<verse eid="PSA 54:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 54:6"/>I will sacrifice to you with a freewill offering; I will give thanks to your name, Yahweh, for it is good.<verse eid="PSA 54:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 54:7"/>For he has rescued me from every trouble; my eye has looked in triumph on my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 54:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 54"/>
<chapter number="55" style="c" sid="PSA 55"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 55:1"/>For the chief musician; on stringed instruments. A maschil of David. Give ear to my prayer, God; and do not hide yourself from my plea.<verse eid="PSA 55:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 55:2"/>Pay attention to me and answer me; I have no rest in my troubles<verse eid="PSA 55:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 55:3"/>because of the voice of my enemies, because of the oppression of the wicked; for they bring trouble on me and persecute me in anger.<verse eid="PSA 55:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 55:4"/>My heart trembles within me, and the terrors of death have fallen on me.<verse eid="PSA 55:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 55:5"/>Fearfulness and trembling have come on me, and horror has overwhelmed me.<verse eid="PSA 55:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 55:6"/>I said, “Oh, if only I had wings like a dove! Then would I fly away and be at rest.<verse eid="PSA 55:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 55:7"/>See, then I would wander far away; I would stay in the wilderness. <verse eid="PSA 55:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 55:8"/>I would hurry to a shelter from the stormy wind and tempest.”<verse eid="PSA 55:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 55:9"/>Devour them, Lord, confuse their language! For I have seen violence and strife in the city.<verse eid="PSA 55:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 55:10"/>Day and night they go about on its walls; wickedness and trouble are in the middle of it.<verse eid="PSA 55:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 55:11"/>Wickedness is in the middle of it; oppression and deceit do not leave its streets.<verse eid="PSA 55:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 55:12"/>For it was not an enemy who rebuked me, then I could have borne it; neither was it he who hated me who raised himself up against me, then I would have hidden myself from him.<verse eid="PSA 55:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 55:13"/>But it was you, a man equal to myself, my companion and my close friend.<verse eid="PSA 55:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 55:14"/>We had sweet fellowship together; we walked in the house of God with the throng.<verse eid="PSA 55:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 55:15"/>Let death come suddenly on them; let them go down alive to Sheol, for wickedness is where they live, right among them.<verse eid="PSA 55:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 55:16"/>As for me, I will call on God, and Yahweh will save me.<verse eid="PSA 55:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 55:17"/>In the evening, morning and at noonday I complain and moan; he will hear my voice.<verse eid="PSA 55:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 55:18"/>He will safely rescue my life from the battle that was against me, for those who fought against me were many.<verse eid="PSA 55:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 55:19"/>God, the one who rules from eternity, will hear them and humiliate them.  They never change, and they do not fear God.<verse eid="PSA 55:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 55:20"/>My friend has raised his hands against those who were at peace with him; he has not respected the covenant that he had.<verse eid="PSA 55:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 55:21"/>His mouth was smooth as butter, but his heart was hostile; his words were softer than oil, yet they were actually drawn swords.<verse eid="PSA 55:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 55:22"/>Place your burdens on Yahweh, and he will sustain you; he will never allow a righteous person to totter.<verse eid="PSA 55:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 55:23"/>But you, God, will bring the wicked down into the pit of destruction; bloodthirsty and deceitful men will not live even half as long as others, but I will trust in you.<verse eid="PSA 55:23"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 55"/>
<chapter number="56" style="c" sid="PSA 56"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 56:1"/>For the chief musician; set to Jonath elem rehokim. A psalm of David. A michtam; when the Philistines took him in Gath. Be merciful to me, God, for men are attacking me! All the day long those who fight me press their assault.<verse eid="PSA 56:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 56:2"/>My enemies trample me all day long; for there are many who arrogantly fight against me.<verse eid="PSA 56:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 56:3"/>When I am afraid, I will put my trust in you.<verse eid="PSA 56:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 56:4"/>In God, whose word I praise— in God I have put my trust; I will not be afraid; what can mere man do to me?<verse eid="PSA 56:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 56:5"/>All the day long they twist my words; all their thoughts are against me for evil.<verse eid="PSA 56:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 56:6"/>They gather themselves together, they hide themselves, and they mark my steps, just as they have waited for my life.<verse eid="PSA 56:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 56:7"/>Do not let them escape doing iniquity. Bring down the peoples in your anger, God.<verse eid="PSA 56:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 56:8"/>You number my wanderings and put my tears into your bottle; are they not in your book?<verse eid="PSA 56:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 56:9"/>Then my enemies will turn back on the day that I call to you; this I know, that God is for me.<verse eid="PSA 56:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 56:10"/>In God—whose word I praise, in Yahweh—whose word I praise,<verse eid="PSA 56:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 56:11"/>in God I trust, I will not be afraid. What can anyone do to me?<verse eid="PSA 56:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 56:12"/>The duty to fulfill my vows to you is on me, God; I will give thank offerings to you.<verse eid="PSA 56:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 56:13"/>For you have rescued my life from death; you have kept my feet from falling, so that I may walk before God in the light of the living.<verse eid="PSA 56:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 56"/>
<chapter number="57" style="c" sid="PSA 57"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 57:1"/>For the chief musician; set to Al Tashheth. A psalm of David. A michtam; when he fled from Saul, in the cave. Be merciful to me, God, be merciful to me, for I take refuge in you until these troubles are over. I stay under your wings for protection until this destruction is over.<verse eid="PSA 57:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 57:2"/>I will cry to God Most High, to God, who does all things for me.<verse eid="PSA 57:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 57:3"/>He will send help from heaven and save me, he is angry with those who crush me.  God will send me his loving kindness and his faithfulness.<verse eid="PSA 57:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 57:4"/>My life is among lions; I am among those who are ready to devour me. I am among people whose teeth are spears and arrows, and whose tongues are sharp swords.<verse eid="PSA 57:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 57:5"/>Be exalted, God, above the heavens; let your glory be above all the earth.<verse eid="PSA 57:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 57:6"/>They spread out a net for my feet; I was distressed. They dug a pit in front of me. They themselves have fallen into the middle of it! <verse eid="PSA 57:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 57:7"/>My heart is fixed, God, my heart is fixed; I will sing, yes, I will sing praises.<verse eid="PSA 57:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 57:8"/>Wake up, my honored heart; wake up, lute and harp; I will wake up the dawn.<verse eid="PSA 57:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 57:9"/>I will give thanks to you, Lord, among the peoples; I will sing praises to you among the nations.<verse eid="PSA 57:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 57:10"/>For great is your unfailing love, reaching to the heavens; and your faithfulness to the clouds.<verse eid="PSA 57:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 57:11"/>Be exalted, God, above the heavens; may your glory be exalted over all the earth.<verse eid="PSA 57:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 57"/>
<chapter number="58" style="c" sid="PSA 58"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 58:1"/>For the chief musician; set to Al Tashheth. A psalm of David. A michtam. Do you indeed rulers speak righteousness you silent ones? Do you judge uprightly, you people?<verse eid="PSA 58:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 58:2"/>No, you commit wickedness in your heart; you distribute violence throughout the land with your hands.<verse eid="PSA 58:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 58:3"/>The wicked go astray even when they are in the womb; they go astray from birth, speaking lies.<verse eid="PSA 58:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 58:4"/>Their poison is like a snake’s poison; they are like a deaf adder that stops up its ears,<verse eid="PSA 58:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 58:5"/>that pays no attention to the voice of charmers, no matter how skillful they are.<verse eid="PSA 58:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 58:6"/>Break their teeth in their mouths, God; break out the great teeth of the young lions, Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 58:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 58:7"/>Let them melt away as water that runs off; when they shoot their arrows, let them be as though they had no points.<verse eid="PSA 58:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 58:8"/>Let them be like a snail that melts and passes away, like the untimely-born child of a woman that never sees the sunlight.<verse eid="PSA 58:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 58:9"/>Before your pots can feel the thorn’s burning heat, he will take them away with a whirlwind, the green thorns and the burning thorns alike.<verse eid="PSA 58:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 58:10"/>The righteous will rejoice when he sees God’s vengeance; he will wash his feet in the blood of the wicked,<verse eid="PSA 58:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 58:11"/>so that men will say, “Truly, there is a reward for the righteous person; truly there is a God who judges the earth.”<verse eid="PSA 58:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 58"/>
<chapter number="59" style="c" sid="PSA 59"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 59:1"/>For the chief musician; set to Al Tashheth. A psalm of David. A michtam; when Saul sent, and they watched the house to kill him. Rescue me from my enemies, my God; set me on high away from those who rise up against me.<verse eid="PSA 59:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 59:2"/>Keep me safe from the workers of iniquity, and save me from the bloodthirsty men.<verse eid="PSA 59:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 59:3"/>For, see, they wait in ambush to take my life. The powerful men gather themselves together against me, but not because of my transgression or my sin, Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 59:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 59:4"/>They prepare to run at me although I am without fault; awake and help me and see.<verse eid="PSA 59:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 59:5"/>You, Yahweh God of hosts, the God of Israel, arise and punish all the nations; do not be merciful to any wicked transgressors. <verse eid="PSA 59:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 59:6"/>They return at evening, they howl like dogs and go around the city.<verse eid="PSA 59:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 59:7"/>See, they belch out with their mouths; swords are in their lips, for they say, “Who hears us?”<verse eid="PSA 59:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 59:8"/>But you, Yahweh, laugh at them; you hold all the nations in derision.<verse eid="PSA 59:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 59:9"/>God, my strength, I will pay attention to you; you are my high tower.<verse eid="PSA 59:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 59:10"/>My God will meet me with his covenant faithfulness; God will let me see my desire on my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 59:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 59:11"/>Do not kill them, or my people will forget. Scatter them by your power and make them fall, Lord our shield.<verse eid="PSA 59:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 59:12"/>For the sins of their mouths and the words of their lips, let them be captured in their pride, and for the curses and lies that they express.<verse eid="PSA 59:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 59:13"/>Consume them in wrath, consume them so that they will be no more; let them know that God rules in Jacob and to the ends of the earth. <verse eid="PSA 59:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 59:14"/>At evening they return, howling like dogs going around the city.<verse eid="PSA 59:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 59:15"/>They wander about looking for food and they growl like a dog if they are not satisfied.<verse eid="PSA 59:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 59:16"/>But I will sing about your strength, and in the morning I will sing about your steadfast love! For you have been my high tower and a refuge in the day of my distress.<verse eid="PSA 59:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 59:17"/>To you, my strength, I will sing praises; for God is my high tower, the God of covenant faithfulness.<verse eid="PSA 59:17"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 59"/>
<chapter number="60" style="c" sid="PSA 60"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 60:1"/>For the chief musician; set to Shushan Eduth. A michtam of David, for teaching. When he fought with Aram Naharaim and with Aram Zobah, and Joab returned and killed twelve thousand Edomites in the Valley of Salt. God, you have cast us off; you have broken through our defenses; you have been angry; restore us again.<verse eid="PSA 60:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 60:2"/>You have made the land tremble; you have torn it apart; heal its fissures, for it is shaking.<verse eid="PSA 60:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 60:3"/>You have made your people see difficult things; you have made us drink the wine of staggering.<verse eid="PSA 60:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 60:4"/>For those who honor you, you have set up a banner to be displayed against those who carry the bow. <verse eid="PSA 60:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 60:5"/>So that those you love may be rescued, rescue us with your right hand and answer me.<verse eid="PSA 60:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 60:6"/>God has spoken in his holiness, “I will rejoice; I will divide Shechem and apportion out the Valley of Succoth.<verse eid="PSA 60:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 60:7"/>Gilead is mine, and Manasseh is mine; Ephraim also is my helmet; Judah is my scepter.<verse eid="PSA 60:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 60:8"/>Moab is my washbasin; over Edom I will throw my shoe; I will shout in triumph because of Philistia.”<verse eid="PSA 60:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 60:9"/>Who will bring me into the strong city? Who will lead me to Edom?<verse eid="PSA 60:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 60:10"/>But you, God, have you not rejected us? You do not go into battle with our army.<verse eid="PSA 60:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 60:11"/>Give us help against the enemy, for man’s help is futile.<verse eid="PSA 60:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 60:12"/>We will triumph with God’s help; he will trample down our enemies.<verse eid="PSA 60:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 60"/>
<chapter number="61" style="c" sid="PSA 61"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 61:1"/>For the chief musician; on a stringed instrument. A psalm of David. Hear my cry, God; attend to my prayer.<verse eid="PSA 61:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 61:2"/>From the ends of the earth will I call to you when my heart is faint; lead me to the rock that is higher than I.<verse eid="PSA 61:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 61:3"/>For you have been a refuge for me, a strong tower from the enemy.<verse eid="PSA 61:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 61:4"/>Let me live in your tabernacle forever! Let me take refuge under the shelter of your wings. <verse eid="PSA 61:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 61:5"/>For you, God, have heard my vows, you have given me the inheritance of those who honor your name.<verse eid="PSA 61:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 61:6"/>You will prolong the king’s life; his years will be like many generations.<verse eid="PSA 61:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 61:7"/>Oh prepare mercy and truth which may preserve him. He will remain before God forever.<verse eid="PSA 61:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 61:8"/>I will sing praise to your name forever so that I may perform my vows every day.<verse eid="PSA 61:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 61"/>
<chapter number="62" style="c" sid="PSA 62"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 62:1"/>For the chief musician; after the manner of Jeduthun. A psalm of David. I wait in silence for God alone; my salvation comes from him.<verse eid="PSA 62:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 62:2"/>He alone is my rock and my salvation; he is my high tower; I will not be greatly moved.<verse eid="PSA 62:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 62:3"/>How long, all of you, will you attack a man, that you may tip him over like a leaning wall or a shaky fence?<verse eid="PSA 62:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 62:4"/>They consult with him only to bring him down from his honorable position; they love to tell lies; they bless him with their mouths, but in their hearts they curse him. <verse eid="PSA 62:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 62:5"/>I wait in silence for God alone; for my hope is set on him.<verse eid="PSA 62:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 62:6"/>He alone is my rock and my salvation; he is my high tower; I will not be moved.<verse eid="PSA 62:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 62:7"/>With God is my salvation and my glory; the rock of my strength and my refuge are in God.<verse eid="PSA 62:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 62:8"/>Trust in him at all times, you people; pour out your heart before him; God is a refuge for us. <verse eid="PSA 62:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 62:9"/>Surely men of low standing are vanity, and men of high standing are a lie; they will weigh lightly in the scales; weighed together, they are lighter than nothing.<verse eid="PSA 62:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 62:10"/>Do not trust in oppression or robbery; and do not hope uselessly in riches, for they will bear no fruit; do not fix your heart on them.<verse eid="PSA 62:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 62:11"/>God has spoken once, twice have I heard this: power belongs to God.<verse eid="PSA 62:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 62:12"/>Also to you, Lord, belongs covenant faithfulness, for you pay back every person for what he has done.<verse eid="PSA 62:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 62"/>
<chapter number="63" style="c" sid="PSA 63"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 63:1"/>A psalm of David, when he was in the wilderness of Judah. God, you are my God! I earnestly search for you, my soul thirsts for you, and my flesh longs for you, in a dry and weary land where there is no water.<verse eid="PSA 63:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 63:2"/>So I have looked on you in the sanctuary, to see your power and your glory.<verse eid="PSA 63:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 63:3"/>Because your covenant faithfulness is better than life, my lips will praise you.<verse eid="PSA 63:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 63:4"/>So I will bless you with my life; I will lift up my hands in your name.<verse eid="PSA 63:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 63:5"/>It will be like when my throat is satisfied with fatty meats and rich foods; with joyful lips my mouth will praise you,<verse eid="PSA 63:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 63:6"/>when I remember you on my bed and meditate on you in the night hours.<verse eid="PSA 63:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 63:7"/>For you have been my help, and in the shadow of your wings I rejoice.<verse eid="PSA 63:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 63:8"/>My soul clings to you; your right hand supports me.<verse eid="PSA 63:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 63:9"/>But those who seek to destroy my life will go down into the lowest parts of the earth;<verse eid="PSA 63:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 63:10"/>they will be given over to the power of the sword, and they will become food for the jackals.<verse eid="PSA 63:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 63:11"/>But the king will rejoice in God; everyone who swears by him will exult, but the mouth of those who speak lies will be shut.<verse eid="PSA 63:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 63"/>
<chapter number="64" style="c" sid="PSA 64"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 64:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. Hear my voice, God, listen to my complaint; preserve my life from fear of my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 64:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 64:2"/>Hide me from the secret plotting of evildoers, from the commotion of the doers of iniquity.<verse eid="PSA 64:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 64:3"/>They have sharpened their tongues like swords; they have aimed their arrows, bitter words,<verse eid="PSA 64:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 64:4"/>so that they may shoot from secret places at someone who is innocent; suddenly they shoot at him and fear nothing.<verse eid="PSA 64:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 64:5"/>They encourage themselves in an evil plan; they consult privately together in order to set traps; they say, “Who will see us?”<verse eid="PSA 64:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 64:6"/>They invent sinful plans; “We have finished,” they say, “a careful plan.” The inner thoughts and hearts of man are deep.<verse eid="PSA 64:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 64:7"/>But God will shoot them; suddenly they will be wounded with his arrows.<verse eid="PSA 64:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 64:8"/>They will be made to stumble, since their own tongues are against them; all who see them will wag their heads.<verse eid="PSA 64:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 64:9"/>All people will fear and will declare God’s deeds. They will wisely think about what he has done.<verse eid="PSA 64:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 64:10"/>The righteous will be glad about Yahweh and will take refuge in him; all the upright in heart will take pride in him.<verse eid="PSA 64:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 64"/>
<chapter number="65" style="c" sid="PSA 65"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 65:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm. A song of David. For you, God in Zion, our praise waits; our vows will be carried out to you.<verse eid="PSA 65:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 65:2"/>You who hear prayer, to you all flesh will come.<verse eid="PSA 65:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 65:3"/>Iniquities prevail against us; as for our transgressions, you will forgive them.<verse eid="PSA 65:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 65:4"/>Blessed is the man whom you choose to bring near to you so that he may live in your courts. We will be satisfied with the goodness of your house, your holy temple.<verse eid="PSA 65:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 65:5"/>In righteousness you will answer us by doing amazing things, God of our salvation; you who are hope of all the ends of the earth and of those who are far across the sea.<verse eid="PSA 65:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 65:6"/>For it is you who made the mountains firm, you who are belted with strength.<verse eid="PSA 65:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 65:7"/>It is you who quiet the roaring of the seas, the roaring of their waves, and the commotion of the peoples.<verse eid="PSA 65:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 65:8"/>Those who live in the uttermost parts of the earth are afraid of the evidence of your deeds; you make the east and the west rejoice.<verse eid="PSA 65:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 65:9"/>You come to help the earth; you water it; you greatly enrich it; the river of God is full of water; you provide mankind grain when you have prepared the earth.<verse eid="PSA 65:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 65:10"/>You water its furrows abundantly; you settle down the furrows’ ridges; you make them soft with rain showers; you bless the sprouts between them.<verse eid="PSA 65:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 65:11"/>You crown the year with your goodness, and your wagon tracks overflow with abundance.<verse eid="PSA 65:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 65:12"/>The pastures in the wilderness drip with dew, and the hills are clothed with joy.<verse eid="PSA 65:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 65:13"/>The pastures are clothed with flocks; the valleys also are covered over with grain; they shout for joy, and they sing.<verse eid="PSA 65:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 65"/>
<chapter number="66" style="c" sid="PSA 66"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 66:1"/>For the chief musician. A song, a psalm. To the chief musician. A song. A psalm. Make a joyful noise to God, all the earth;<verse eid="PSA 66:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 66:2"/>Sing out the glory of his name; make his praise glorious.<verse eid="PSA 66:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 66:3"/>Say to God, “How terrifying are your deeds! By the greatness of your power your enemies will submit to you.<verse eid="PSA 66:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 66:4"/>All the earth will worship you and will sing to you; they will sing to your name.” <verse eid="PSA 66:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 66:5"/>Come and see the works of God; he is fearsome in his deeds toward the sons of mankind.<verse eid="PSA 66:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 66:6"/>He turned the sea into dry land; they went through the river on foot; there we rejoiced in him.<verse eid="PSA 66:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 66:7"/>He rules forever by his might; his eyes observe the nations; let not the rebellious exalt themselves. <verse eid="PSA 66:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 66:8"/>Give blessing to God, you people, let the sound of his praise be heard.<verse eid="PSA 66:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 66:9"/>He keeps us among the living, and he does not permit our feet to slip.<verse eid="PSA 66:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 66:10"/>For you, God, have tested us; you have tested us as silver is tested.<verse eid="PSA 66:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 66:11"/>You brought us into a net; you laid a heavy burden on our backs.<verse eid="PSA 66:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 66:12"/>You made people ride over our heads; we went through fire and water, but you brought us out into a spacious place.<verse eid="PSA 66:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 66:13"/>I will come into your house with burnt offerings; I will pay you my vows<verse eid="PSA 66:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 66:14"/>which my lips promised and my mouth spoke when I was in distress.<verse eid="PSA 66:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 66:15"/>I will offer to you burnt offerings of fat animals with the sweet aroma of rams; I will offer bulls and goats. <verse eid="PSA 66:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 66:16"/>Come and listen, all you who fear God, and I will declare what he has done for my soul.<verse eid="PSA 66:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 66:17"/>I cried to him with my mouth, and he was praised with my tongue.<verse eid="PSA 66:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 66:18"/>If I had seen sin within my heart, the Lord would not have listened to me.<verse eid="PSA 66:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 66:19"/>But God has truly heard; he has paid attention to the voice of my prayer.<verse eid="PSA 66:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 66:20"/>Blessed be God, who has not turned away my prayer or his covenant faithfulness from me.<verse eid="PSA 66:20"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 66"/>
<chapter number="67" style="c" sid="PSA 67"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 67:1"/>For the chief musician; on stringed instruments. A psalm, a song. May God be gracious to us and bless us and cause his face to shine on us Selah<verse eid="PSA 67:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 67:2"/>so that your ways may be known on earth, your salvation among all nations.<verse eid="PSA 67:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 67:3"/>Let the peoples praise you, God; let all the peoples praise you.<verse eid="PSA 67:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 67:4"/>Let the nations be glad and sing for joy, for you will judge the peoples with uprightness and govern the nations on earth. <verse eid="PSA 67:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 67:5"/>Let the peoples praise you, God; let all the peoples praise you.<verse eid="PSA 67:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 67:6"/>The earth has yielded its harvest; God, our God, will bless us.<verse eid="PSA 67:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 67:7"/>May God bless us, and may all the ends of the earth fear him.<verse eid="PSA 67:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 67"/>
<chapter number="68" style="c" sid="PSA 68"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 68:1"/>For the chief musician; A psalm of David, a song. Let God arise; let his enemies be scattered; let those also who hate him flee before him.<verse eid="PSA 68:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 68:2"/>As smoke is driven away, so drive them away; as wax melts before the fire, so let the wicked perish in the presence of God.<verse eid="PSA 68:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 68:3"/>But let the righteous be glad; let them exult before God; may they rejoice and be happy.<verse eid="PSA 68:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 68:4"/>Sing to God! Sing praises to his name! Praise the one who rides through the plains of the Jordan River valley! Yahweh is his name! Rejoice before him!<verse eid="PSA 68:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 68:5"/>A father of the fatherless, a judge of the widows, is God in the holy place where he lives.<verse eid="PSA 68:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 68:6"/>God puts the lonely into families; he brings out the prisoners to live in prosperity; but the rebellious live in a parched land.<verse eid="PSA 68:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 68:7"/>God, when you went out before your people, when you marched through the wilderness, <verse eid="PSA 68:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 68:8"/>The earth trembled; the heavens also dropped rain in God’s presence, in the presence of God when he came to Sinai, in the presence of God, the God of Israel.<verse eid="PSA 68:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 68:9"/>You, God, sent a plentiful rain; you strengthened your inheritance when it was weary.<verse eid="PSA 68:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 68:10"/>Your people lived in it; You, God, gave from your goodness to the poor.<verse eid="PSA 68:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 68:11"/>The Lord gave the orders, and those who announced them were a great army.<verse eid="PSA 68:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 68:12"/>Kings of armies flee, they flee, and the women waiting at home divide the plunder:<verse eid="PSA 68:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 68:13"/>Though you lie down among the sheepfolds, You will be like the wings of a dove covered with silver, And her feathers with yellow gold<verse eid="PSA 68:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 68:14"/>The Almighty scattered kings there, it was as when it snowed on Mount Zalmon.<verse eid="PSA 68:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 68:15"/>A mighty mountain is the hill country of Bashan; a high mountain is the hill country of Bashan.<verse eid="PSA 68:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 68:16"/>Why do you look in envy, you high hill country, at the mountain which God desires for the place he will live? Indeed, Yahweh will live in it forever.<verse eid="PSA 68:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 68:17"/>The chariots of God are twenty thousand, thousands upon thousands; the Lord is among them in the holy place, as at Sinai.<verse eid="PSA 68:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 68:18"/>You have ascended on high; you have led away captives; you have received gifts from among men, even from those who fought against you, so that you, Yahweh God, might live there.<verse eid="PSA 68:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 68:19"/>Blessed be the Lord, who daily bears our burdens, the God who is our salvation. <verse eid="PSA 68:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 68:20"/>Our God is a God who saves; Yahweh the Lord is the one who is able to rescue us from death.<verse eid="PSA 68:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 68:21"/>But God will strike through the heads of his enemies, through the hairy scalps of those who walk in offenses against him.<verse eid="PSA 68:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 68:22"/>The Lord said, “I will bring my enemies back from Bashan; I will bring them back from the depths of the sea<verse eid="PSA 68:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 68:23"/>so that you may crush your enemies, dipping your foot in blood, and so that the tongues of your dogs may have their share from your enemies.”<verse eid="PSA 68:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 68:24"/>They have seen your processions, God, the processions of my God, my King, into the holy place.<verse eid="PSA 68:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 68:25"/>The singers went first, the minstrels followed after, and in the middle were the unmarried girls playing tambourines.<verse eid="PSA 68:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 68:26"/>Bless God in the assemblies; praise Yahweh, you who are from the fountain  of Israel.<verse eid="PSA 68:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 68:27"/>There is first Benjamin, the smallest tribe, then the leaders of Judah and their multitudes, the leaders of Zebulun and the leaders of Naphtali.<verse eid="PSA 68:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 68:28"/>Your God, Israel, has decreed your strength; reveal to us your power, God, as you have revealed it in times past.<verse eid="PSA 68:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 68:29"/>Reveal your power to us from your temple at Jerusalem, where kings bring gifts to you.<verse eid="PSA 68:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 68:30"/>Shout in battle against the wild beasts in the reeds, against the peoples, that multitude of bulls and calves. Humiliate them and make them bring you gifts; scatter the peoples who love to wage war.<verse eid="PSA 68:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 68:31"/>Princes will come out of Egypt; Cush will hurry to reach out with her hands to God.<verse eid="PSA 68:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 68:32"/>Sing to God, you kingdoms of the earth; Selah  Sing praises to Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 68:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 68:33"/>To him who rides on the heaven of heavens, which exist from ancient times; see, he lifts up his voice with power.<verse eid="PSA 68:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 68:34"/>Ascribe strength to God; his majesty is over Israel, and his strength is in the skies.<verse eid="PSA 68:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 68:35"/>God, you are fearsome in your holy place; the God of Israel—he gives strength and power to his people. Blessed be God.<verse eid="PSA 68:35"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 68"/>
<chapter number="69" style="c" sid="PSA 69"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 69:1"/>For the chief musician; set to Shoshannim. A psalm of David. Save me, God; for the waters have put my life in danger.<verse eid="PSA 69:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 69:2"/>I sink in deep mire, where there is no place to stand; I have come into deep waters, where the floods flow over me.<verse eid="PSA 69:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 69:3"/>I am weary with my crying; my throat is dry; my eyes fail while I wait for my God.<verse eid="PSA 69:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 69:4"/>Those who hate me without a cause are more than the hairs on my head; those who would cut me off, being my enemies for wrong reasons, are mighty; what I did not steal, I have to give back.<verse eid="PSA 69:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 69:5"/>God, you know my foolishness, and my sins are not hidden from you.<verse eid="PSA 69:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 69:6"/>Let not those who hope in you be put to shame because of me, Lord Yahweh of hosts; let not those who seek you be brought to dishonor because of me, God of Israel.<verse eid="PSA 69:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 69:7"/>For your sake I have borne rebuke; shame has covered my face.<verse eid="PSA 69:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 69:8"/>I have become a stranger to my brothers, an alien to my mother’s children.<verse eid="PSA 69:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 69:9"/>For the zeal of your house has eaten me up, and the rebukes of those who rebuke you have fallen on me.<verse eid="PSA 69:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 69:10"/>When I wept and did not eat food, they insulted me.<verse eid="PSA 69:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 69:11"/>When I made sackcloth my clothing, I became the object of a proverb to them.<verse eid="PSA 69:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 69:12"/>Those who sit in the city gate talk about me; I am a song of drunkards.<verse eid="PSA 69:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 69:13"/>But as for me, my prayer is to you, Yahweh, in the acceptable time; in the multitude of your mercy, hear me in the truth of your salvation.<verse eid="PSA 69:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 69:14"/>Pull me out of the mire, and do not let me sink; let me be taken away from those who hate me and rescued out of the deep waters.<verse eid="PSA 69:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 69:15"/>Do not let the floods of water overwhelm me, neither let the deep swallow me up. Do not let the pit shut its mouth on me.<verse eid="PSA 69:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 69:16"/>Answer me, Yahweh, for your covenant faithfulness is good; because your mercies for me are many, turn to me.<verse eid="PSA 69:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 69:17"/>Do not hide your face from your servant, for I am in distress; answer me quickly.<verse eid="PSA 69:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 69:18"/>Come to me and redeem me. Because of my enemies, ransom me.<verse eid="PSA 69:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 69:19"/>You know my rebuke, my shame, and my dishonor; my adversaries are all before you.<verse eid="PSA 69:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 69:20"/>Rebuke has broken my heart; I am full of heaviness; I looked for someone to take pity, but there was none; I looked for comforters, but I found none.<verse eid="PSA 69:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 69:21"/>They gave me poison for my food; in my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink.<verse eid="PSA 69:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 69:22"/>Let their table before them become a snare; when they think they are in safety, let it become a trap.<verse eid="PSA 69:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 69:23"/>Let their eyes be darkened so that they cannot see; and always make their loins shake.<verse eid="PSA 69:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 69:24"/>Pour out your indignation on them, and let the fierceness of your anger overtake them.<verse eid="PSA 69:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 69:25"/>Let their place be a desolation; let no one live in their tents.<verse eid="PSA 69:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 69:26"/>For they persecuted the one you struck down. They repeated the account of the pain of those you have wounded.<verse eid="PSA 69:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 69:27"/>Accuse them of having committed iniquity after iniquity; do not let them come into your righteous victory.<verse eid="PSA 69:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 69:28"/>Let them be blotted out of the Book of Life and not be written down along with the righteous.<verse eid="PSA 69:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 69:29"/>But I am poor and sorrowful; let your salvation, God, set me up on high.<verse eid="PSA 69:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 69:30"/>I will praise the name of God with a song and will exalt him with thanksgiving.<verse eid="PSA 69:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 69:31"/>That will please Yahweh better than an ox or a bull that has horns and hooves.<verse eid="PSA 69:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 69:32"/>The meek have seen it and are glad; you who seek after God, let your hearts live.<verse eid="PSA 69:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 69:33"/>For Yahweh hears the needy and does not despise his prisoners.<verse eid="PSA 69:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 69:34"/>Let heaven and earth praise him, the seas and everything that moves in them.<verse eid="PSA 69:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 69:35"/>For God will save Zion and will rebuild the cities of Judah; the people will live there and have it as a possession.<verse eid="PSA 69:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 69:36"/>His servants’ descendants will inherit it; and those who love his name will live there.<verse eid="PSA 69:36"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 69"/>
<chapter number="70" style="c" sid="PSA 70"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 70:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David; to bring to remembrance. Save me, God! Yahweh, come quickly and help me.<verse eid="PSA 70:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 70:2"/>Let those who try to take my life be ashamed and humiliated; let them be turned back and brought to dishonor, those who take pleasure in my pain.<verse eid="PSA 70:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 70:3"/>Let them be turned back because of their shame, those who say, “Aha, aha.”<verse eid="PSA 70:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 70:4"/>Let all those who seek you rejoice and be glad in you; let those who love your salvation always say, “May God be praised.”<verse eid="PSA 70:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 70:5"/>But I am poor and needy; hurry to me, God; you are my help and you rescue me. Yahweh, do not delay.<verse eid="PSA 70:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 70"/>
<chapter number="71" style="c" sid="PSA 71"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 71:1"/>In you, Yahweh, I take refuge; let me never be put to shame.<verse eid="PSA 71:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 71:2"/>Rescue me and make me safe in your righteousness; turn your ear to me and save me.<verse eid="PSA 71:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 71:3"/>Be to me a rock for refuge where I may always go; you have given a command to save me, for you are my rock and my fortress.<verse eid="PSA 71:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 71:4"/>Rescue me, my God, out of the hand of the wicked, out of the hand of the unrighteous and cruel.<verse eid="PSA 71:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 71:5"/>For you are my hope, Lord Yahweh. I have trusted in you ever since I was a child.<verse eid="PSA 71:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 71:6"/>By you I have been supported from the womb; you are he who took me out of my mother’s belly; my praise will be always about you.<verse eid="PSA 71:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 71:7"/>I am an example to many people; you are my strong refuge.<verse eid="PSA 71:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 71:8"/>My mouth will be filled with your praise, all the day with your honor.<verse eid="PSA 71:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 71:9"/>Do not throw me away in my time of old age; do not abandon me when my strength fails.<verse eid="PSA 71:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 71:10"/>For my enemies are talking about me; those who watch for my life are plotting together.<verse eid="PSA 71:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 71:11"/>They say, “God has forsaken him; pursue and take him, for there is no one to save him.”<verse eid="PSA 71:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 71:12"/>God, do not be far from me; my God, hurry to help me.<verse eid="PSA 71:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 71:13"/>Let them be put to shame and destroyed, those who are hostile to my life; let them be covered with rebuke and dishonor, those who seek my hurt.<verse eid="PSA 71:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 71:14"/>But I will always hope in you and will praise you more and more.<verse eid="PSA 71:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 71:15"/>My mouth will tell about your righteousness and your salvation all the day, although I cannot understand it.<verse eid="PSA 71:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 71:16"/>I will come with the mighty acts of the Lord Yahweh; I will make mention of your righteousness, yours alone.<verse eid="PSA 71:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 71:17"/>God, you have taught me from my youth; even now I declare your wonderful deeds.<verse eid="PSA 71:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 71:18"/>Indeed, even when I am old and gray-headed, God, do not forsake me, as I have been declaring your strength to the next generation, your power to everyone who is to come.<verse eid="PSA 71:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 71:19"/>Your righteousness also, God, is very high; you who have done great things, God, who is like you?<verse eid="PSA 71:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 71:20"/>You who made me see many troubles will revive us again and will bring us up again from the depths of the earth.<verse eid="PSA 71:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 71:21"/>May you increase my honor; turn again and comfort me.<verse eid="PSA 71:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 71:22"/>I will also give thanks to you with the harp for your trustworthiness, my God; to you I will sing praises with the harp, Holy One of Israel.<verse eid="PSA 71:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 71:23"/>My lips will shout for joy when I sing praises to you— even my soul, which you have redeemed.<verse eid="PSA 71:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 71:24"/>My tongue will also talk about your righteousness all day long; for they have been put to shame and are confused, those who sought my hurt.<verse eid="PSA 71:24"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 71"/>
<chapter number="72" style="c" sid="PSA 72"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 72:1"/>A psalm of Solomon. A Psalm of Solomon Give the king your righteous decrees, God, your righteousness to the king’s son.<verse eid="PSA 72:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 72:2"/>May he judge your people with righteousness and your poor with justice.<verse eid="PSA 72:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 72:3"/>May the mountains produce peace for the people; may the hills produce righteousness.<verse eid="PSA 72:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 72:4"/>May he judge the poor of the people; may he save the children of the needy and break in pieces the oppressor.<verse eid="PSA 72:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 72:5"/>May they honor you while the sun endures, and as long as the moon lasts throughout all generations.<verse eid="PSA 72:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 72:6"/>May he come down like rain on the mown grass, like showers that water the earth.<verse eid="PSA 72:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 72:7"/>May the righteous flourish in his days, and may there be an abundance of peace till the moon is no more.<verse eid="PSA 72:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 72:8"/>May he have dominion from sea to sea, and from the River to the ends of the earth.<verse eid="PSA 72:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 72:9"/>May those who live in the wilderness bow down before him; may his enemies lick the dust.<verse eid="PSA 72:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 72:10"/>May the kings of Tarshish and of the islands render tribute; may the kings of Sheba and Seba offer gifts.<verse eid="PSA 72:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 72:11"/>Indeed, may all kings fall down before him; may all nations serve him.<verse eid="PSA 72:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 72:12"/>For he helps the needy person who cries out and the poor person who has no other helper.<verse eid="PSA 72:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 72:13"/>He has pity on the poor and needy, and he saves the lives of needy people.<verse eid="PSA 72:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 72:14"/>He redeems their lives from oppression and violence, and their blood is precious in his sight.<verse eid="PSA 72:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 72:15"/>May he live! May the gold of Sheba be given to him. May people always pray for him; may God bless him all day long.<verse eid="PSA 72:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 72:16"/>May there be abundance of grain in the land; on the mountaintops may their crops wave. May the fruit of it be like Lebanon; may the people flourish in the cities like the grass of the field.<verse eid="PSA 72:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 72:17"/>May his name endure forever; may his name continue as long as the sun; may people be blessed in him; may all nations call him blessed.<verse eid="PSA 72:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 72:18"/>May Yahweh God, the God of Israel, be blessed, who alone does wonderful things.<verse eid="PSA 72:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 72:19"/>May his glorious name be blessed forever, and may the whole earth be filled with his glory. Amen and Amen.<verse eid="PSA 72:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 72:20"/>The prayers of David son of Jesse are finished.<verse eid="PSA 72:20"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 72"/>
<chapter number="73" style="c" sid="PSA 73"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 73:1"/>A psalm of Asaph. A Psalm of Asaph. Surely God is good to Israel, to those with a pure heart.<verse eid="PSA 73:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 73:2"/>But as for me, my feet almost slipped; my steps almost were caused to slide out {from under me}<verse eid="PSA 73:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 73:3"/>because I was envious of the arrogant {when} I saw the prosperity of the wicked.<verse eid="PSA 73:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 73:4"/>For {they have} no ropes until their death, and their belly is fat.<verse eid="PSA 73:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 73:5"/>They {are} free from the trouble of man; and with {the rest of} man they are not afflicted.<verse eid="PSA 73:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 73:6"/>Therefore pride is a necklace for them; a garment of violence covers them.<verse eid="PSA 73:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 73:7"/>Their eyes bulge out from fatness; the imaginations of {their} heart overflow.<verse eid="PSA 73:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 73:8"/>They mock and speak with evil of oppression; they speak from an elevated place.<verse eid="PSA 73:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 73:9"/>They set their mouth in the heavens, and their tongue goes through the earth.<verse eid="PSA 73:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 73:10"/>Therefore his people turn here, and waters of a full {cup} are drained by them.<verse eid="PSA 73:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 73:11"/>And they say, “How does God know? And is there knowledge in the Most High?”<verse eid="PSA 73:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 73:12"/>Behold, these wicked; they are always at ease, they increase in wealth.<verse eid="PSA 73:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 73:13"/>Surely in vain I have kept my heart clean and washed my hands in innocence.<verse eid="PSA 73:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 73:14"/>For I have been stricken all of the day, and punished every morning.<verse eid="PSA 73:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 73:15"/>If I had said, “I will recount such things,” Behold, I would have betrayed the generation of your children.<verse eid="PSA 73:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 73:16"/>And {when} I thought {how} to understand this, it {was} troublesome in my eyes<verse eid="PSA 73:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 73:17"/>until I went into the sanctuaries of God; {then} I discerned their end.<verse eid="PSA 73:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 73:18"/>Surely you set them in slippery places; you make them fall to destruction.<verse eid="PSA 73:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 73:19"/>How they are {brought} to desolation as in a moment! They come to an end, they perish, by terrors.<verse eid="PSA 73:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 73:20"/>Like a dream after {one} awakes; Lord, when you rouse {yourself}, you will despise their image.<verse eid="PSA 73:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 73:21"/>When my heart was embittered, and I was pierced in my kidneys,<verse eid="PSA 73:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 73:22"/>I {was} stupid and I was not knowing; I was an animal with you.<verse eid="PSA 73:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 73:23"/>Yet I {am} continuously with you; you hold {me} by my right hand.<verse eid="PSA 73:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 73:24"/>You guide me with your counsel, and afterward you will take me {to} glory.<verse eid="PSA 73:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 73:25"/>Whom have I in heaven {but you}? And besides you {there is} nothing on the earth I desire.<verse eid="PSA 73:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 73:26"/>My flesh and my heart fail, {but} God {is} the rock of my heart and my portion forever.<verse eid="PSA 73:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 73:27"/>For behold, those who are far from you will perish; you destroy every one being unfaithful to you.<verse eid="PSA 73:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 73:28"/>But {for} me, the closeness of God for me {is} good. I have made the Lord Yahweh my refuge, in order to recount all your works.<verse eid="PSA 73:28"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 73"/>
<chapter number="74" style="c" sid="PSA 74"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 74:1"/>A maschil of Asaph. A Maskil of Asaph. Why God, have you rejected {us} forever? {Why} does your nose smoke against the sheep of your pasture?<verse eid="PSA 74:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 74:2"/>Remember your congregation, {whom} you aquired in ancient times, {which} you have redeemed to be the tribe of your inheritance; This Mount Zion, where you have dwelt.<verse eid="PSA 74:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 74:3"/>Lift up your feet to the perpetual ruins; all the evil that the enemy has done in the sanctuary.<verse eid="PSA 74:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 74:4"/>Your adversaries have roared in the middle of your meeting place; they have set up their signs as signs.<verse eid="PSA 74:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 74:5"/>It is perceived like one bringing on high, axes against a forest of trees.<verse eid="PSA 74:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 74:6"/>And now, with axe and hammers, they break down all its engravings.<verse eid="PSA 74:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 74:7"/>They have set your sanctuary on fire to the ground; they have profaned the dwelling place of your name.<verse eid="PSA 74:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 74:8"/>They said in their hearts, “We will oppress them altogether.” They have burned all of the meeting places of God in the land.<verse eid="PSA 74:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 74:9"/>We do not see signs for us; {there is} no longer {any} prophet, and {there is} no one among us knowing how long this will last.<verse eid="PSA 74:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 74:10"/>Until when, God, will the adversary reproach? Will the enemy treat your name with contempt forever?<verse eid="PSA 74:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 74:11"/>Why do you withdraw your hand, your right hand? {Take it} from within the fold {of your garment and} destroy {them}.<verse eid="PSA 74:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 74:12"/>Yet God {is} my king from ancient times, working acts of salvation in the midst of the earth.<verse eid="PSA 74:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 74:13"/>You divided the sea by your strength; you smashed the heads of the sea monsters in the waters.<verse eid="PSA 74:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 74:14"/>You crushed the heads of leviathan; you fed him to those living in the wilderness.<verse eid="PSA 74:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 74:15"/>You broke open springs and streams; you dried up flowing rivers.<verse eid="PSA 74:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 74:16"/>The day is yours, and the night is yours also; you set the sun and moon in place.<verse eid="PSA 74:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 74:17"/>You have set all the borders of the earth; you have made summer and winter.<verse eid="PSA 74:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 74:18"/>Call to mind how the enemy hurled insults at you, Yahweh, and that a foolish people has blasphemed your name.<verse eid="PSA 74:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 74:19"/>Do not give the life of your dove to a wild animal. Do not forget forever the life of your oppressed people.<verse eid="PSA 74:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 74:20"/>Remember your covenant, for the dark regions of the land are full of places of violence.<verse eid="PSA 74:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 74:21"/>Do not let the oppressed be turned back in shame; let the poor and oppressed praise your name.<verse eid="PSA 74:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 74:22"/>Arise, God; defend your own honor; call to mind how fools insult you all day long.<verse eid="PSA 74:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 74:23"/>Do not forget the voice of your adversaries or the uproar of those who continually defy you.<verse eid="PSA 74:23"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 74"/>
<chapter number="75" style="c" sid="PSA 75"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 75:1"/>For the chief musician; set to Al Tashheth. A psalm of Asaph, a song. We give thanks to you, God; we give thanks, for you reveal your presence; people tell of your wondrous works.<verse eid="PSA 75:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 75:2"/>At the appointed time I will judge fairly.<verse eid="PSA 75:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 75:3"/>Though the earth and all the inhabitants shake in fear, I make steady the earth’s pillars. Selah<verse eid="PSA 75:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 75:4"/>I said to the arrogant, “Do not be arrogant,” and to the wicked, “Do not lift up the horn.<verse eid="PSA 75:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 75:5"/>Do not lift up your horn to the heights; do not speak with an insolent neck.”<verse eid="PSA 75:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 75:6"/>It is not from the east or from the west, and it is not from the wilderness that lifting up comes.<verse eid="PSA 75:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 75:7"/>But God is the judge; he brings down one and he lifts up another.<verse eid="PSA 75:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 75:8"/>For Yahweh holds in his hand a cup full of foaming wine, which is mixed with spices, and pours it out. Surely all the wicked of the earth will drink it to the last drop.<verse eid="PSA 75:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 75:9"/>But I will continually tell what you have done; I will sing praises to the God of Jacob.<verse eid="PSA 75:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 75:10"/>He says, “I will cut off all the horns of the wicked, but the horns of the righteous will be raised up.”<verse eid="PSA 75:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 75"/>
<chapter number="76" style="c" sid="PSA 76"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 76:1"/>For the chief musician, on stringed instruments. A psalm of Asaph, a song. God has made himself known in Judah; his name is great in Israel.<verse eid="PSA 76:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 76:2"/>His tent is in Salem; his dwelling place is in Zion.<verse eid="PSA 76:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 76:3"/>There he broke the arrows of the bow, the shield, the sword, and the other weapons of war. Selah<verse eid="PSA 76:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 76:4"/>You shine brightly and reveal your glory, as you descend from the mountains, where you killed your victims.<verse eid="PSA 76:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 76:5"/>The bravehearted were plundered; they fell asleep. All the warriors were helpless.<verse eid="PSA 76:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 76:6"/>At your rebuke, God of Jacob, both rider and horse fell asleep.<verse eid="PSA 76:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 76:7"/>You, yes you, are to be feared; who can stand in your sight when you are angry?<verse eid="PSA 76:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 76:8"/>From heaven you made your judgment heard; the earth was afraid and silent<verse eid="PSA 76:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 76:9"/>when you, God, arose to execute judgment and to save all the oppressed of the earth. <verse eid="PSA 76:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 76:10"/>Surely your angry judgment against humanity will bring you praise; you gird yourself with what is left of your anger.<verse eid="PSA 76:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 76:11"/>Make vows to Yahweh your God and keep them. May all who surround him bring gifts to him who is to be feared.<verse eid="PSA 76:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 76:12"/>He cuts off the spirit of the princes; he is feared by the kings of the earth.<verse eid="PSA 76:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 76"/>
<chapter number="77" style="c" sid="PSA 77"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 77:1"/>For the chief musician; after the manner of Jeduthun. A psalm of Asaph. I will call out with my voice to God; I will call with my voice to God, and my God will hear me.<verse eid="PSA 77:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 77:2"/>In the day of my trouble I sought the Lord; at night I stretched my hands out, and they would not become tired. My soul refused to be comforted.<verse eid="PSA 77:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 77:3"/>I thought of God as I groaned; I thought about him as I grew faint. <verse eid="PSA 77:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 77:4"/>You held my eyes open; I was too troubled to speak.<verse eid="PSA 77:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 77:5"/>I thought about the days of old, about times long past.<verse eid="PSA 77:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 77:6"/>I call to remembrance my song in the night; I meditate within my heart, And my spirit makes diligent search.<verse eid="PSA 77:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 77:7"/>Will the Lord reject me forever? Will he never again show me favor?<verse eid="PSA 77:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 77:8"/>Was his covenant faithfulness gone forever? Had his promise failed forever?<verse eid="PSA 77:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 77:9"/>Had God forgotten to be gracious? Had his anger shut off his compassion? <verse eid="PSA 77:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 77:10"/>I said, “This is my sorrow: the changing of the right hand of the Most High toward us.”<verse eid="PSA 77:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 77:11"/>But I will call to mind your deeds, Yahweh; I will think about your wonderful deeds of old.<verse eid="PSA 77:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 77:12"/>I will ponder all your deeds and will reflect on them.<verse eid="PSA 77:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 77:13"/>Your way, God, is holy; what god compares to our great God?<verse eid="PSA 77:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 77:14"/>You are the God who does wonders; you have revealed your strength among the peoples.<verse eid="PSA 77:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 77:15"/>You gave your people victory by your great power— the descendants of Jacob and Joseph. <verse eid="PSA 77:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 77:16"/>The waters saw you, God; the waters saw you, and they were afraid; the depths trembled.<verse eid="PSA 77:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 77:17"/>The clouds poured down water; the cloudy skies also gave voice; your arrows flew about.<verse eid="PSA 77:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 77:18"/>Your thunderous voice was heard in the wind; the lightning lit up the world; the earth trembled and shook.<verse eid="PSA 77:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 77:19"/>Your path went through the sea and your way through the surging waters, but your footprints were not seen.<verse eid="PSA 77:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 77:20"/>You led your people like a flock by the hand of Moses and Aaron.<verse eid="PSA 77:20"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 77"/>
<chapter number="78" style="c" sid="PSA 78"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 78:1"/>A maschil of Asaph. A writing of Asaph Hear my teaching, my people, listen to the words of my mouth.<verse eid="PSA 78:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 78:2"/>I will open my mouth in parables; I will sing about hidden things about the past.<verse eid="PSA 78:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 78:3"/>These are things that we have heard and learned, things that our ancestors have told us.<verse eid="PSA 78:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 78:4"/>We will not keep them from their descendants. We will tell the next generation about the praiseworthy deeds of Yahweh, his strength, and the wonders that he has done.<verse eid="PSA 78:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 78:5"/>For he established covenant decrees in Jacob and appointed a law in Israel. He commanded our ancestors that they were to teach them to their children.<verse eid="PSA 78:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 78:6"/>He commanded this so that the generation to come might know his decrees, the children not yet born, who should tell them in turn to their own children.<verse eid="PSA 78:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 78:7"/>Then they would place their hope in God and not forget his deeds but keep his commandments.<verse eid="PSA 78:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 78:8"/>Then they would not be like their ancestors, who were a stubborn and rebellious generation, a generation whose hearts were not right, and whose spirits were not committed and faithful to God.<verse eid="PSA 78:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 78:9"/>The Ephraimites were armed with bows, but they turned back on the day of battle.<verse eid="PSA 78:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 78:10"/>They did not keep the covenant with God, and they refused to obey his law.<verse eid="PSA 78:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 78:11"/>They forgot his deeds, the wonderful things that he had shown them.<verse eid="PSA 78:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 78:12"/>They forgot the marvelous things he did in the sight of their ancestors in the land of Egypt, in the land of Zoan.<verse eid="PSA 78:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 78:13"/>He divided the sea and led them across it; he made the waters to stand like walls.<verse eid="PSA 78:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 78:14"/>In the daytime he led them with a cloud and all the night with the light of fire.<verse eid="PSA 78:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 78:15"/>He split the rocks in the wilderness, and he gave them water abundantly, enough to fill the depths of the sea.<verse eid="PSA 78:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 78:16"/>He made streams flow out of the rock and made the water flow like rivers.<verse eid="PSA 78:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 78:17"/>Yet they continued to sin against him, rebelling against the Most High in the wilderness.<verse eid="PSA 78:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 78:18"/>They challenged God in their hearts by asking for food to satisfy their appetites.<verse eid="PSA 78:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 78:19"/>They spoke against God; they said, “Can God really lay out a table for us in the wilderness?<verse eid="PSA 78:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 78:20"/>See, when he struck the rock, waters gushed out and streams overflowed. But can he give bread also? Will he provide meat for his people?”<verse eid="PSA 78:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 78:21"/>When Yahweh heard this, he was angry; so his fire burned against Jacob, and his anger attacked Israel,<verse eid="PSA 78:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 78:22"/>because they did not believe in God and did not trust in his salvation.<verse eid="PSA 78:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 78:23"/>Yet he commanded the skies above and opened the doors of the sky.<verse eid="PSA 78:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 78:24"/>He rained down manna for them to eat, and gave them the grain from heaven.<verse eid="PSA 78:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 78:25"/>People ate the bread of angels. He sent them food in abundance.<verse eid="PSA 78:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 78:26"/>He caused the east wind to blow in the sky, and by his power he guided the south wind.<verse eid="PSA 78:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 78:27"/>He rained down meat on them like dust, birds as numerous as the sands of the sea.<verse eid="PSA 78:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 78:28"/>They fell in the middle of their camp, all around their tents.<verse eid="PSA 78:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 78:29"/>So they ate and were full. He gave them what they craved.<verse eid="PSA 78:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 78:30"/>But they had not yet filled up; their food was still in their mouths.<verse eid="PSA 78:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 78:31"/>Then God’s anger attacked them and killed the strongest of them. He brought down the young men of Israel.<verse eid="PSA 78:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 78:32"/>Despite this, they continued to sin and did not believe his wonderful deeds.<verse eid="PSA 78:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 78:33"/>Therefore God cut short their days; their years were filled with terror.<verse eid="PSA 78:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 78:34"/>Whenever God afflicted them, they would start to seek him, and they would return and look earnestly for him.<verse eid="PSA 78:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 78:35"/>They would call to mind that God was their rock and that the Most High God was their rescuer.<verse eid="PSA 78:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 78:36"/>But they would flatter him with their mouth and lie to him with their words.<verse eid="PSA 78:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 78:37"/>For their hearts were not firmly fixed on him, and they were not faithful to his covenant.<verse eid="PSA 78:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 78:38"/>Yet he, being merciful, forgave their iniquity and did not destroy them. Yes, many times he held back his anger and did not stir up all his wrath.<verse eid="PSA 78:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 78:39"/>He called to mind that they were made of flesh, a wind that passes away and does not return.<verse eid="PSA 78:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 78:40"/>How often they rebelled against him in the wilderness and grieved him in the barren regions!<verse eid="PSA 78:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 78:41"/>Again and again they challenged God and offended the Holy One of Israel.<verse eid="PSA 78:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 78:42"/>They did not think about his power, how he had rescued them from the enemy<verse eid="PSA 78:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 78:43"/>when he performed his terrifying signs in Egypt and his wonders in the region of Zoan.<verse eid="PSA 78:43"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="44" style="v" sid="PSA 78:44"/>He turned the Egyptians’ rivers to blood so that they could not drink from their streams.<verse eid="PSA 78:44"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="45" style="v" sid="PSA 78:45"/>He sent swarms of flies that devoured them and frogs that overran their land.<verse eid="PSA 78:45"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="46" style="v" sid="PSA 78:46"/>He gave their crops to the grasshopper and their labor to the locust.<verse eid="PSA 78:46"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="47" style="v" sid="PSA 78:47"/>He destroyed their vines with hail and their sycamore trees with more hail.<verse eid="PSA 78:47"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="48" style="v" sid="PSA 78:48"/>He rained hail on their cattle and hurled lightning bolts at their livestock.<verse eid="PSA 78:48"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="49" style="v" sid="PSA 78:49"/>The fierceness of his anger lashed out against them. He sent wrath, fury, and trouble like agents who bring disaster.<verse eid="PSA 78:49"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="50" style="v" sid="PSA 78:50"/>He leveled a path for his anger; he did not spare them from death but gave them over to the plague.<verse eid="PSA 78:50"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="51" style="v" sid="PSA 78:51"/>He killed all the firstborn in Egypt, the firstborn of their strength in the tents of Ham.<verse eid="PSA 78:51"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="52" style="v" sid="PSA 78:52"/>He led his own people out like sheep and guided them through the wilderness like a flock.<verse eid="PSA 78:52"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="53" style="v" sid="PSA 78:53"/>He led them secure and unafraid, but the sea overwhelmed their enemies.<verse eid="PSA 78:53"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="54" style="v" sid="PSA 78:54"/>Then he brought them to the border of his holy land, to this mountain that his right hand acquired.<verse eid="PSA 78:54"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="55" style="v" sid="PSA 78:55"/>He drove out the nations from before them and assigned them their inheritance. He settled the tribes of Israel in their tents.<verse eid="PSA 78:55"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="56" style="v" sid="PSA 78:56"/>Yet they challenged and defied the Most High God and did not keep his solemn commands.<verse eid="PSA 78:56"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="57" style="v" sid="PSA 78:57"/>They were unfaithful and acted treacherously like their fathers; they were as undependable as a faulty bow.<verse eid="PSA 78:57"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="58" style="v" sid="PSA 78:58"/>For they made him angry with their high places and provoked him to jealous anger with their idols.<verse eid="PSA 78:58"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="59" style="v" sid="PSA 78:59"/>When God heard this, he was angry and completely rejected Israel.<verse eid="PSA 78:59"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="60" style="v" sid="PSA 78:60"/>He abandoned the sanctuary of Shiloh, the tent where he had lived among people.<verse eid="PSA 78:60"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="61" style="v" sid="PSA 78:61"/>He allowed his strength to be captured and gave his glory into the enemy’s hand.<verse eid="PSA 78:61"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="62" style="v" sid="PSA 78:62"/>He handed his people over to the sword, and he was angry with his heritage.<verse eid="PSA 78:62"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="63" style="v" sid="PSA 78:63"/>Fire devoured their young men, and their young women had no wedding songs.<verse eid="PSA 78:63"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="64" style="v" sid="PSA 78:64"/>Their priests fell by the sword, and their widows could not weep.<verse eid="PSA 78:64"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="65" style="v" sid="PSA 78:65"/>Then the Lord awakened as one from sleep, like a warrior who shouts because of wine.<verse eid="PSA 78:65"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="66" style="v" sid="PSA 78:66"/>He drove his adversaries back; he put them to everlasting shame.<verse eid="PSA 78:66"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="67" style="v" sid="PSA 78:67"/>He rejected the tent of Joseph, and he did not chose the tribe of Ephraim.<verse eid="PSA 78:67"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="68" style="v" sid="PSA 78:68"/>He chose the tribe of Judah and Mount Zion that he loved.<verse eid="PSA 78:68"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="69" style="v" sid="PSA 78:69"/>He built his sanctuary like the heavens, like the earth that he has established forever.<verse eid="PSA 78:69"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="70" style="v" sid="PSA 78:70"/>He chose David, his servant, and took him from the sheepfolds.<verse eid="PSA 78:70"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="71" style="v" sid="PSA 78:71"/>He took him from following the ewes with their young, and he brought him to be shepherd of Jacob, his people, and of Israel, his heritage.<verse eid="PSA 78:71"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="72" style="v" sid="PSA 78:72"/>David shepherded them with the integrity of his heart, and he guided them with the skill of his hands.<verse eid="PSA 78:72"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 78"/>
<chapter number="79" style="c" sid="PSA 79"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 79:1"/>A psalm of Asaph. A Psalm of Asaph God, foreign nations have come into your inheritance; they have defiled your holy temple; they have turned Jerusalem into a heap of ruins.<verse eid="PSA 79:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 79:2"/>They have given the dead bodies of your servants as food to the birds of the skies, the bodies of your faithful ones to the beasts of the earth.<verse eid="PSA 79:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 79:3"/>They have shed their blood like water around Jerusalem, and there was none to bury them.<verse eid="PSA 79:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 79:4"/>We have become a reproach for our neighbors, mocking and derision to those who are around us.<verse eid="PSA 79:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 79:5"/>How long, Yahweh? Will you stay angry forever? How long will your jealous anger burn like fire?<verse eid="PSA 79:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 79:6"/>Pour out your wrath on the nations that do not know you and on the kingdoms that do not call upon your name.<verse eid="PSA 79:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 79:7"/>For they have devoured Jacob and destroyed his villages.<verse eid="PSA 79:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 79:8"/>Do not hold the sins of our forefathers against us; may your merciful actions come to us, for we are very low.<verse eid="PSA 79:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 79:9"/>Help us, God of our salvation, for the sake of the glory of your name; save us and forgive our sins for your name’s sake.<verse eid="PSA 79:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 79:10"/>Why should the nations say, “Where is their God?” May the blood of your servants that was shed be avenged on the nations before our eyes.<verse eid="PSA 79:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 79:11"/>May the groans of the prisoners come before you; with the greatness of your power keep the children of death alive.<verse eid="PSA 79:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 79:12"/>Pay back into the laps of our neighboring countries seven times as much as the insults with which they have insulted you, Lord.<verse eid="PSA 79:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 79:13"/>So we your people and sheep of your pasture will give you thanks forever. We will tell your praises to all generations.<verse eid="PSA 79:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 79"/>
<chapter number="80" style="c" sid="PSA 80"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 80:1"/>For the chief musician, set to the Shoshannim Eduth style. A psalm of Asaph. Pay attention, Shepherd of Israel, you who lead Joseph like a flock; you who sit above the cherubim, shine on us!<verse eid="PSA 80:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 80:2"/>In the sight of Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh, stir up your power; come and save us.<verse eid="PSA 80:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 80:3"/>God, restore us; make your face shine on us, and we will be saved.<verse eid="PSA 80:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 80:4"/>Yahweh God of hosts, how long will you be angry at your people when they pray?<verse eid="PSA 80:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 80:5"/>You have fed them with the bread of tears and given them tears to drink in great quantities.<verse eid="PSA 80:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 80:6"/>You make us something for our neighbors to argue over, and our enemies laugh about us among themselves.<verse eid="PSA 80:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 80:7"/>God of hosts, restore us; make your face shine on us, and we will be saved.<verse eid="PSA 80:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 80:8"/>You brought a vine out of Egypt; you drove out nations and transplanted it.<verse eid="PSA 80:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 80:9"/>You cleared the land for it; it took root and filled the land.<verse eid="PSA 80:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 80:10"/>The mountains were covered with its shade, the cedars of God by its branches.<verse eid="PSA 80:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 80:11"/>It sent out its branches as far as the sea and its shoots to the Euphrates River.<verse eid="PSA 80:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 80:12"/>Why have you broken down its walls so that all who pass by along the road pluck its fruit?<verse eid="PSA 80:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 80:13"/>The boars out of the forest ruin it, and the beasts of the field feed on it.<verse eid="PSA 80:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 80:14"/>Turn back, God of hosts; look down from heaven and take notice and take care of this vine.<verse eid="PSA 80:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 80:15"/>This is the root that your right hand planted, the shoot that you made to grow.<verse eid="PSA 80:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 80:16"/>It has been burned and cut down; they perish because of your rebuke.<verse eid="PSA 80:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 80:17"/>May your hand be on the man of your right hand, on the son of man whom you made strong for yourself.<verse eid="PSA 80:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 80:18"/>Then we will not turn away from you; revive us, and we will call on your name.<verse eid="PSA 80:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 80:19"/>Yahweh God of hosts, restore us; make your face shine on us, and we will be saved.<verse eid="PSA 80:19"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 80"/>
<chapter number="81" style="c" sid="PSA 81"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 81:1"/>For the chief musician; set to the Gittith style. A psalm of Asaph. Sing aloud to God our strength; shout out for joy to the God of Jacob.<verse eid="PSA 81:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 81:2"/>Sing a song and play the tambourine, the pleasant lyre with the harp.<verse eid="PSA 81:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 81:3"/>Blow the trumpet on the day of the new moon, on the day of the full moon, when our feast day begins.<verse eid="PSA 81:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 81:4"/>For it is a statute for Israel, a decree given by the God of Jacob.<verse eid="PSA 81:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 81:5"/>He issued it as a regulation in Joseph when he went against the land of Egypt, where I heard a voice that I did not recognize:<verse eid="PSA 81:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 81:6"/>“I removed the burden from his shoulder; his hands were freed from holding the basket.<verse eid="PSA 81:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 81:7"/>In your distress you called out, and I helped you; I answered you from a dark thundercloud. I tested you at the waters of Meribah. <verse eid="PSA 81:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 81:8"/>Listen, my people, for I will warn you, Israel, if you would only listen to me!<verse eid="PSA 81:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 81:9"/>There must be no foreign god among you; you must not worship any foreign god.<verse eid="PSA 81:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 81:10"/>I am Yahweh your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt. Open your mouth wide, and I will fill it.<verse eid="PSA 81:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 81:11"/>But my people did not listen to my words; Israel did not obey me.<verse eid="PSA 81:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 81:12"/>So I gave them over to their own stubborn way so that they might do what seemed right to them.<verse eid="PSA 81:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 81:13"/>Oh, that my people would listen to me; oh, that my people would walk in my paths.<verse eid="PSA 81:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 81:14"/>Then I would quickly subdue their enemies and turn my hand against their oppressors.<verse eid="PSA 81:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 81:15"/>May those who hate Yahweh cringe in fear before him! May they be humiliated forever.<verse eid="PSA 81:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 81:16"/>I would feed Israel with the finest wheat; I would satisfy you with honey out of the rock.”<verse eid="PSA 81:16"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 81"/>
<chapter number="82" style="c" sid="PSA 82"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 82:1"/>A psalm of Asaph. A Psalm of Asaph God stands in the divine assembly; in the midst of the gods he renders judgment.<verse eid="PSA 82:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 82:2"/>How long will you judge unjustly and show favoritism to the wicked? Selah<verse eid="PSA 82:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 82:3"/>Defend the poor and fatherless; maintain the rights of the afflicted and destitute.<verse eid="PSA 82:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 82:4"/>Rescue the poor and needy; take them out of the hand of the wicked.<verse eid="PSA 82:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 82:5"/>They neither know nor understand; they wander around in the darkness; all the foundations of the earth crumble.<verse eid="PSA 82:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 82:6"/>I said, “You are gods, and all of you sons of the Most High.<verse eid="PSA 82:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 82:7"/>Nevertheless you will die like men and fall like one of the princes.”<verse eid="PSA 82:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 82:8"/>Arise, God, judge the earth, for you have an inheritance in all the nations.<verse eid="PSA 82:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 82"/>
<chapter number="83" style="c" sid="PSA 83"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 83:1"/>A song. A psalm of Asaph. God, do not be silent! Do not ignore us and remain unmoved, God.<verse eid="PSA 83:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 83:2"/>Look, your enemies are making a commotion, and those who hate you have raised their heads.<verse eid="PSA 83:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 83:3"/>They conspire against your people and plan together against your protected ones.<verse eid="PSA 83:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 83:4"/>They have said, “Come, and let us destroy them as a nation. Then the name of Israel will no longer be remembered.”<verse eid="PSA 83:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 83:5"/>They schemed together with one strategy; they made an alliance against you—<verse eid="PSA 83:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 83:6"/>the tents of Edom and the Ishmaelites, of Moab and the Hagrites,<verse eid="PSA 83:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 83:7"/>Gebal, Ammon, Amalek; and also Philistia and the inhabitants of Tyre.<verse eid="PSA 83:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 83:8"/>Assyria also has joined with them; they have become an arm for the descendants of Lot. <verse eid="PSA 83:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 83:9"/>Do to them as you did to Midian, as you did to Sisera and to Jabin at the Kishon River.<verse eid="PSA 83:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 83:10"/>They perished at Endor and became like manure for the earth.<verse eid="PSA 83:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 83:11"/>Make their nobles like Oreb and Zeeb, and all their princes like Zebah and Zalmunna.<verse eid="PSA 83:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 83:12"/>They said, “Let us take for ourselves the pastures of God.”<verse eid="PSA 83:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 83:13"/>My God, make them like the whirling dust, like chaff before the wind,<verse eid="PSA 83:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 83:14"/>like the fire that burns the forest, and like the flame that sets the mountains on fire.<verse eid="PSA 83:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 83:15"/>Chase them with your strong wind, and terrify them with your windstorm.<verse eid="PSA 83:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 83:16"/>Fill their faces with shame so that they might seek your name, Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 83:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 83:17"/>May they be put to shame and be terrified forever; may they perish in disgrace.<verse eid="PSA 83:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 83:18"/>Then they will know that you alone, Yahweh, are honored as the Most High over all the earth.<verse eid="PSA 83:18"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 83"/>
<chapter number="84" style="c" sid="PSA 84"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 84:1"/>For the chief musician; set to the Gittith style. A psalm of the sons of Korah. How lovely is the place where you live, Yahweh of hosts!<verse eid="PSA 84:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 84:2"/>I long for the courts of Yahweh, my desire for it has made me exhausted. My heart and all of my being call out to the living God.<verse eid="PSA 84:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 84:3"/>Even the sparrow has found her a house and the swallow a nest for herself where she may lay her young near your altars, Yahweh of hosts, my King, and my God.<verse eid="PSA 84:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 84:4"/>Blessed are they who live in your house; they praise you continually. <verse eid="PSA 84:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 84:5"/>Blessed is the man whose strength is in you, in whose heart are the highways up to Zion.<verse eid="PSA 84:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 84:6"/>Passing through the Valley of Tears, they find springs of water to drink. The early rains cover it with blessings.<verse eid="PSA 84:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 84:7"/>They go from strength to strength; every one of them appears before God in Zion.<verse eid="PSA 84:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 84:8"/>Yahweh God of hosts, hear my prayer; God of Jacob, listen to what I am saying! <verse eid="PSA 84:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 84:9"/>God, watch over our shield; show concern for your anointed.<verse eid="PSA 84:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 84:10"/>For one day in your courts is better than a thousand elsewhere. I would rather be a doorkeeper in the house of my God, than to live within the tents of the wicked.<verse eid="PSA 84:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 84:11"/>For Yahweh God is our sun and shield; Yahweh will give grace and glory; he does not withhold any good thing from those who walk in integrity.<verse eid="PSA 84:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 84:12"/>Yahweh of hosts, blessed is the man who trusts in you.<verse eid="PSA 84:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 84"/>
<chapter number="85" style="c" sid="PSA 85"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 85:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of the sons of Korah. Yahweh, you have showed favor to your land; you have restored the well-being of Jacob.<verse eid="PSA 85:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 85:2"/>You have forgiven the sin of your people; you have covered all their sin. Selah<verse eid="PSA 85:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 85:3"/>You have withdrawn all your wrath; you have turned back from your hot anger.<verse eid="PSA 85:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 85:4"/>Restore us, God of our salvation, and let go of your displeasure with us.<verse eid="PSA 85:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 85:5"/>Will you be angry with us forever? Will you remain angry throughout future generations?<verse eid="PSA 85:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 85:6"/>Will you not revive us again? Then your people will rejoice in you.<verse eid="PSA 85:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 85:7"/>Show us your covenant faithfulness, Yahweh, grant us your salvation.<verse eid="PSA 85:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 85:8"/>I will listen to what Yahweh God says, for he will make peace with his people, his faithful ones. Yet they must not turn again to foolish ways.<verse eid="PSA 85:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 85:9"/>Surely his salvation is near to those who fear him; then glory will remain in our land.<verse eid="PSA 85:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 85:10"/>Covenant faithfulness and trustworthiness have met together; righteousness and peace have kissed each other.<verse eid="PSA 85:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 85:11"/>Trustworthiness springs up from the ground, and righteousness looks down from the sky.<verse eid="PSA 85:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 85:12"/>Yes, Yahweh will give his good blessings, and our land will yield its crops.<verse eid="PSA 85:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 85:13"/>Righteousness will go before him and make a way for his footsteps.<verse eid="PSA 85:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 85"/>
<chapter number="86" style="c" sid="PSA 86"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 86:1"/>A prayer of David. A Prayer of David. Incline your ear and listen, Yahweh, and answer me, for I am poor and needy.<verse eid="PSA 86:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 86:2"/>Protect me, for I am faithful; my God, save your servant who trusts in you.<verse eid="PSA 86:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 86:3"/>Be merciful to me, Lord, for I cry out to you all day long.<verse eid="PSA 86:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 86:4"/>Make your servant glad, for to you, Lord, I lift up my soul.<verse eid="PSA 86:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 86:5"/>You, Lord, are good, and ready to forgive, and you show great mercy to all those who cry out to you.<verse eid="PSA 86:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 86:6"/>Yahweh, listen to my prayer; hear the sound of my pleas.<verse eid="PSA 86:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 86:7"/>In the day of my trouble I call on you, for you will answer me.<verse eid="PSA 86:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 86:8"/>There is no one who compares to you among the gods, Lord. There are no deeds like your deeds.<verse eid="PSA 86:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 86:9"/>All the nations that you have made will come and bow before you, Lord. They will honor your name.<verse eid="PSA 86:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 86:10"/>For you are great and do wonderful things; you only are God.<verse eid="PSA 86:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 86:11"/>Teach me your ways, Yahweh. Then I will walk in your truth. Unite my heart to reverence you.<verse eid="PSA 86:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 86:12"/>Lord my God, I will praise you with my whole heart; I will glorify your name forever.<verse eid="PSA 86:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 86:13"/>For great is your covenant faithfulness toward me; you have rescued my life from the depths of Sheol.<verse eid="PSA 86:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 86:14"/>God, the arrogant have risen up against me. A gang of violent men seek my life. They have no regard for you.<verse eid="PSA 86:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 86:15"/>But you, Lord, are a merciful and gracious God, slow to anger, and abundant in covenant faithfulness and trustworthiness.<verse eid="PSA 86:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 86:16"/>Turn toward me and have mercy on me; give your strength to your servant; save the son of your servant woman.<verse eid="PSA 86:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 86:17"/>Show me a sign of your favor. Then those who hate me will see it and be put to shame because you, Yahweh, have helped me and comforted me.<verse eid="PSA 86:17"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 86"/>
<chapter number="87" style="c" sid="PSA 87"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 87:1"/>A psalm of the sons of Korah; a song. A Psalm of the sons of Korah A Song On the holy mount stands the city he founded;<verse eid="PSA 87:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 87:2"/>Yahweh loves the gates of Zion more than all the tents of Jacob.<verse eid="PSA 87:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 87:3"/>Glorious things are said of you, city of God. Selah<verse eid="PSA 87:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 87:4"/>“I mention Rahab and Babylon to my followers. See, there are Philistia, and Tyre, along with Cush— and will say, ‘This one was born there.’”<verse eid="PSA 87:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 87:5"/>Of Zion it will be said, “Each of these was born in her; and the Most High himself will establish her.”<verse eid="PSA 87:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 87:6"/>Yahweh writes in the census book of the nations, “This one was born there.” <verse eid="PSA 87:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 87:7"/>So also the singers and the dancers say together, “All my fountains are in you.”<verse eid="PSA 87:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 87"/>
<chapter number="88" style="c" sid="PSA 88"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 88:1"/>A song, a psalm of the sons of Korah; for the chief musician; set to the Mahalath Leannoth style. A maschil of Heman the Ezrahite. Yahweh, God of my salvation, I cry out day and night before you.<verse eid="PSA 88:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 88:2"/>Let my prayer come before you; pay attention to my cry.<verse eid="PSA 88:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 88:3"/>For I am filled with troubles, and my life has reached Sheol.<verse eid="PSA 88:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 88:4"/>People treat me like those who go down into the pit; I am a man with no strength.<verse eid="PSA 88:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 88:5"/>I am abandoned among the dead; I am like the dead who lie in the grave, about whom you care no more because they are cut off from your power.<verse eid="PSA 88:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 88:6"/>You place me in the lowest part of the pit, in the dark and deep places.<verse eid="PSA 88:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 88:7"/>Your wrath lies heavy on me, and all your waves crash over me. <verse eid="PSA 88:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 88:8"/>Because of you, my acquaintances avoid me. You have made me a shocking sight to them. I am hemmed in and I cannot escape.<verse eid="PSA 88:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 88:9"/>My eyes grow weary from trouble; All day long I call out to you, Yahweh; I spread out my hands to you.<verse eid="PSA 88:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 88:10"/>Will you do wonders for the dead? Will those who have died rise and praise you? <verse eid="PSA 88:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 88:11"/>Will your covenant faithfulness be proclaimed in the grave, your loyalty in the place of the dead?<verse eid="PSA 88:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 88:12"/>Will your wonderful deeds be known in the darkness, or your righteousness in the place of forgetfulness?<verse eid="PSA 88:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 88:13"/>But I cry to you, Yahweh; in the morning my prayer comes before you.<verse eid="PSA 88:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 88:14"/>Yahweh, why do you reject me? Why do you hide your face from me?<verse eid="PSA 88:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 88:15"/>I have always been afflicted and on the verge of death since my youth. I have suffered from your terrors; I am in despair.<verse eid="PSA 88:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 88:16"/>Your angry actions have passed over me, and your terrifying deeds have annihilated me.<verse eid="PSA 88:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 88:17"/>They surround me like water all the day long; they have all encircled me.<verse eid="PSA 88:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 88:18"/>You have removed every friend and acquaintance from me. My only acquaintance is the darkness.<verse eid="PSA 88:18"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 88"/>
<chapter number="89" style="c" sid="PSA 89"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 89:1"/>A maschil of Ethan the Ezrahite. I will sing of Yahweh’s acts of covenant faithfulness forever. I will proclaim your truthfulness to future generations.<verse eid="PSA 89:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 89:2"/>For I have said, “Covenant faithfulness has been established forever; your truthfulness you have established in the heavens.”<verse eid="PSA 89:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 89:3"/>“I have made a covenant with my chosen one, I have made an oath to David my servant.<verse eid="PSA 89:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 89:4"/>I will establish your descendants forever, and I will establish your throne through all generations.” <verse eid="PSA 89:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 89:5"/>The heavens praise your wonders, Yahweh; your truthfulness is praised in the assembly of the holy ones.<verse eid="PSA 89:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 89:6"/>For who in the skies can be compared to Yahweh? Who among the sons of the gods is like Yahweh?<verse eid="PSA 89:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 89:7"/>He is a God who is greatly honored in the council of the holy ones and is awesome among all who surround him.<verse eid="PSA 89:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 89:8"/>Yahweh God of hosts, who is strong like you, Yahweh? Your truthfulness surrounds you.<verse eid="PSA 89:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 89:9"/>You rule the raging sea; when the waves surge, you calm them.<verse eid="PSA 89:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 89:10"/>You crushed Rahab as one who is killed. You scattered your enemies with your strong arm.<verse eid="PSA 89:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 89:11"/>The heavens belong to you, and the earth also. You made the world and all it contains.<verse eid="PSA 89:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 89:12"/>You created the north and the south. Tabor and Hermon rejoice in your name.<verse eid="PSA 89:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 89:13"/>You have a mighty arm and a strong hand, and your right hand is high.<verse eid="PSA 89:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 89:14"/>Righteousness and justice are the foundation of your throne. Covenant faithfulness and trustworthiness come before you.<verse eid="PSA 89:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 89:15"/>Blessed are the people who know the joyful sound! Yahweh, they walk in the light of your face.<verse eid="PSA 89:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 89:16"/>They rejoice in your name all day long, and in your righteousness they exalt you.<verse eid="PSA 89:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 89:17"/>You are their majestic strength, and by your favor our strength is made victorious.<verse eid="PSA 89:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 89:18"/>For our shield belongs to Yahweh; our king belongs to the Holy One of Israel.<verse eid="PSA 89:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 89:19"/>Long ago you spoke in a vision to your faithful ones; I have raised up one chosen from among the people.<verse eid="PSA 89:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 89:20"/>I have chosen David my servant; with my holy oil have I anointed him.<verse eid="PSA 89:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 89:21"/>My hand will support him. Also my arm will be with him to strengthen him.<verse eid="PSA 89:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 89:22"/>No enemy will deceive him; no son of wickedness will oppress him.<verse eid="PSA 89:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 89:23"/>I will crush his enemies before him; I will kill those who hate him.<verse eid="PSA 89:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 89:24"/>My truth and my covenant faithfulness will be with him; by my name he will win victories.<verse eid="PSA 89:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 89:25"/>I will place his hand over the sea and his right hand over the rivers.<verse eid="PSA 89:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 89:26"/>He will call out to me, ‘You are my Father, my God, and the rock of my salvation.’<verse eid="PSA 89:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 89:27"/>I also will place him as my firstborn son, the most exalted of the kings of the earth.<verse eid="PSA 89:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 89:28"/>I will extend my covenant faithfulness to him forever; and my covenant with him will be secure.<verse eid="PSA 89:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 89:29"/>I will make his descendants endure forever and his throne as enduring as the skies above.<verse eid="PSA 89:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 89:30"/>If his children forsake my law and do not walk in my regulations,<verse eid="PSA 89:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 89:31"/>if they break my rules and do not keep my commands,<verse eid="PSA 89:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 89:32"/>then will I punish their rebellion with a rod and their iniquity with blows.<verse eid="PSA 89:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 89:33"/>But I will not remove my steadfast love from him or be unfaithful to my promise.<verse eid="PSA 89:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 89:34"/>I will not break my covenant or change the words of my lips.<verse eid="PSA 89:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 89:35"/>Once and for all I have sworn by my holiness— I will not lie to David:<verse eid="PSA 89:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 89:36"/>his descendants will continue forever and his throne as long as the sun before me.<verse eid="PSA 89:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 89:37"/>It will be established forever like the moon, the faithful witness in the sky.” <verse eid="PSA 89:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 89:38"/>But you have refused and rejected; you have been angry with your anointed king.<verse eid="PSA 89:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 89:39"/>You have renounced the covenant of your servant. You have desecrated his crown on the ground.<verse eid="PSA 89:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 89:40"/>You have broken down all his walls. You have ruined his strongholds.<verse eid="PSA 89:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 89:41"/>All who pass by have robbed him. He has become an object of disgust to his neighbors.<verse eid="PSA 89:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 89:42"/>You have raised the right hand of his enemies; you have made all his enemies rejoice.<verse eid="PSA 89:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 89:43"/>You turn back the edge of his sword and have not made him stand when in battle.<verse eid="PSA 89:43"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="44" style="v" sid="PSA 89:44"/>You have brought his splendor to an end; you have brought down his throne to the ground.<verse eid="PSA 89:44"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="45" style="v" sid="PSA 89:45"/>You have shortened the days of his youth. You have covered him with shame. <verse eid="PSA 89:45"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="46" style="v" sid="PSA 89:46"/>How long, Yahweh? Will you hide yourself, forever? How long will your anger burn like fire?<verse eid="PSA 89:46"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="47" style="v" sid="PSA 89:47"/>Oh, think about how short my time is, and for what uselessness you have created all the children of mankind!<verse eid="PSA 89:47"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="48" style="v" sid="PSA 89:48"/>Who can live and not see death, or rescue his own life from the hand of Sheol? <verse eid="PSA 89:48"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="49" style="v" sid="PSA 89:49"/>Lord, where are your former acts of covenant faithfulness that you swore to David in your truthfulness?<verse eid="PSA 89:49"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="50" style="v" sid="PSA 89:50"/>Call to mind, Lord, the mocking directed against your servants and how I bear in my heart so many insults from the nations.<verse eid="PSA 89:50"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="51" style="v" sid="PSA 89:51"/>Your enemies hurl insults, Yahweh; they mock the footsteps of your anointed one.<verse eid="PSA 89:51"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="52" style="v" sid="PSA 89:52"/>Blessed be Yahweh forever. Amen and Amen.<verse eid="PSA 89:52"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 89"/>
<chapter number="90" style="c" sid="PSA 90"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 90:1"/>A prayer of Moses the man of God. A Prayer of Moses a man of God Lord, you have been our refuge throughout all generations.<verse eid="PSA 90:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 90:2"/>Before the mountains were formed, or you formed the earth and the world, from everlasting to everlasting, you are God.<verse eid="PSA 90:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 90:3"/>You return man to dust, and you say, “Return, you descendants of mankind.”<verse eid="PSA 90:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 90:4"/>For a thousand years in your sight are as yesterday when it is past, and as a watch in the night.<verse eid="PSA 90:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 90:5"/>You sweep them away as with a flood and they sleep; in the morning they are like the grass that sprouts up.<verse eid="PSA 90:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 90:6"/>In the morning it blooms and grows up; in the evening it withers and dries up.<verse eid="PSA 90:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 90:7"/>Truly, we are consumed in your anger, and in your wrath we are terrified.<verse eid="PSA 90:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 90:8"/>You have set our iniquities before you, our hidden sins in the light of your presence.<verse eid="PSA 90:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 90:9"/>For our life passes away under your wrath; our years quickly pass like a sigh.<verse eid="PSA 90:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 90:10"/>Our years are seventy, or even eighty if we are healthy; but even our best years are marked by trouble and sorrow. Yes, they pass quickly, and we fly away.<verse eid="PSA 90:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 90:11"/>Who knows the intensity of your anger, and your wrath that is equal to the fear of you?<verse eid="PSA 90:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 90:12"/>So teach us to consider our life so that we might live wisely.<verse eid="PSA 90:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 90:13"/>Turn back, Yahweh! How long will it be? Have pity on your servants.<verse eid="PSA 90:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 90:14"/>Satisfy us in the morning with your covenant faithfulness so that we may rejoice and be glad all our days.<verse eid="PSA 90:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 90:15"/>Make us glad in proportion to the days you afflicted us and to the years we have experienced trouble.<verse eid="PSA 90:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 90:16"/>Let your servants see your work, and let our children see your majesty.<verse eid="PSA 90:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 90:17"/>May the favor of the Lord our God be ours; prosper the work of our hands; indeed, prosper the work of our hands.<verse eid="PSA 90:17"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 90"/>
<chapter number="91" style="c" sid="PSA 91"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 91:1"/>He who lives in the shelter of the Most High will stay in the shadow of the Almighty.<verse eid="PSA 91:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 91:2"/>I will say of Yahweh, “He is my refuge and my fortress, my God, in whom I trust.”<verse eid="PSA 91:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 91:3"/>For he will rescue you from the snare of the hunter and from the deadly plague.<verse eid="PSA 91:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 91:4"/>He will cover you with his wings, and under his wings you will find refuge. His trustworthiness is a shield and protection.<verse eid="PSA 91:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 91:5"/>You will not be afraid of terror in the night, or of the arrow that flies by day,<verse eid="PSA 91:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 91:6"/>or of the plague that roams around in the darkness, or of the disease that comes at noontime.<verse eid="PSA 91:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 91:7"/>A thousand may fall at your side and ten thousand at your right hand, but it will not reach you.<verse eid="PSA 91:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 91:8"/>You will only observe and see the punishment of the wicked.<verse eid="PSA 91:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 91:9"/>For Yahweh is my refuge! Make the Most High your refuge also.<verse eid="PSA 91:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 91:10"/>No evil will overtake you; no affliction will come near your home.<verse eid="PSA 91:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 91:11"/>For he will direct his angels to protect you, to guard you in all your ways.<verse eid="PSA 91:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 91:12"/>They will lift you up with their hand so that you will not hit your foot on a stone.<verse eid="PSA 91:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 91:13"/>You will crush lions and adders under your feet; you will trample on young lions and serpents.<verse eid="PSA 91:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 91:14"/>Because he is devoted to me, I will rescue him. I will protect him because he is loyal to me.<verse eid="PSA 91:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 91:15"/>When he calls to me, I will answer him. I will be with him in trouble; I will give him victory and will honor him.<verse eid="PSA 91:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 91:16"/>I will satisfy him with the length of his days, and show him my salvation.<verse eid="PSA 91:16"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 91"/>
<chapter number="92" style="c" sid="PSA 92"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 92:1"/>A psalm, a song for the Sabbath day. It is a good thing to give thanks to Yahweh and to sing praises to your name, Most High,<verse eid="PSA 92:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 92:2"/>to proclaim your covenant faithfulness in the morning and your truthfulness every night,<verse eid="PSA 92:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 92:3"/>with a harp of ten strings and with the melody of the lyre.<verse eid="PSA 92:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 92:4"/>For you, Yahweh, have made me glad through your deeds. I will sing for joy because of the deeds of your hands.<verse eid="PSA 92:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 92:5"/>How great are your deeds, Yahweh! Your thoughts are very deep.<verse eid="PSA 92:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 92:6"/>A brutish person does not know, nor does a fool understand this:<verse eid="PSA 92:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 92:7"/>When the wicked sprout like the grass, and even when all the evildoers thrive, still they are doomed to eternal destruction.<verse eid="PSA 92:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 92:8"/>But you, Yahweh, will reign forever.<verse eid="PSA 92:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 92:9"/>Indeed, look at your enemies, Yahweh! Indeed, look at your enemies. They will perish! All those who do evil will be scattered.<verse eid="PSA 92:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 92:10"/>You have lifted up my horn like the horn of the wild ox; I am anointed with fresh oil.<verse eid="PSA 92:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 92:11"/>My eyes have seen the downfall of my enemies; my ears have heard of the doom of my evil foes.<verse eid="PSA 92:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 92:12"/>The righteous will flourish like the palm tree; they will grow like a cedar in Lebanon.<verse eid="PSA 92:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 92:13"/>They are planted in the house of Yahweh; they flourish in the courts of our God.<verse eid="PSA 92:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 92:14"/>They bear fruit even when they are old; they stay fresh and green,<verse eid="PSA 92:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 92:15"/>to proclaim that Yahweh is just. He is my rock, and there is no unrighteousness in him.<verse eid="PSA 92:15"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 92"/>
<chapter number="93" style="c" sid="PSA 93"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 93:1"/>Yahweh reigns; he is robed in majesty; Yahweh has clothed and girded himself with strength. The world is firmly established; it cannot be moved.<verse eid="PSA 93:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 93:2"/>Your throne is established from ancient times; you are from everlasting.<verse eid="PSA 93:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 93:3"/>The oceans rise, Yahweh; they have lifted up their voice; the oceans’ waves crash and roar.<verse eid="PSA 93:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 93:4"/>Above the crashing of many waves, the mighty breakers of the sea, Yahweh on high is mighty.<verse eid="PSA 93:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 93:5"/>Your solemn commands are very trustworthy; holiness adorns your house, Yahweh, for the length of your days.<verse eid="PSA 93:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 93"/>
<chapter number="94" style="c" sid="PSA 94"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 94:1"/>Yahweh, God who avenges, God who avenges, shine over us.<verse eid="PSA 94:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 94:2"/>Rise up, judge of the earth, give to the proud what they deserve.<verse eid="PSA 94:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 94:3"/>How long will the wicked, Yahweh, how long will the wicked rejoice?<verse eid="PSA 94:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 94:4"/>They pour out their arrogant words; all those who do evil boast.<verse eid="PSA 94:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 94:5"/>They crush your people, Yahweh; they afflict the nation that belongs to you.<verse eid="PSA 94:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 94:6"/>They kill the widow and foreigner who lives in their country, and they murder the fatherless.<verse eid="PSA 94:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 94:7"/>They say, “Yahweh will not see, the God of Jacob does not take notice of it.”<verse eid="PSA 94:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 94:8"/>Understand, you stupid people! You fools, when will you ever learn?<verse eid="PSA 94:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 94:9"/>He who made the ear, does he not hear? He who formed the eye, does he not see?<verse eid="PSA 94:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 94:10"/>He who disciplines the nations, does he not correct? He is the one who gives knowledge to man.<verse eid="PSA 94:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 94:11"/>Yahweh knows the thoughts of men, that they are vapor.<verse eid="PSA 94:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 94:12"/>Blessed is the one whom you instruct, Yahweh, the one whom you teach from your law.<verse eid="PSA 94:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 94:13"/>You give him rest in times of trouble until a pit is dug for the wicked.<verse eid="PSA 94:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 94:14"/>For Yahweh will not forsake his people or abandon his inheritance.<verse eid="PSA 94:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 94:15"/>For judgment will again be righteous; and all the upright in heart will follow it.<verse eid="PSA 94:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 94:16"/>Who will rise up to defend me against the evildoers? Who will stand up for me against the wicked?<verse eid="PSA 94:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 94:17"/>Unless Yahweh had been my help, I would soon be lying down in the place of silence.<verse eid="PSA 94:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 94:18"/>When I said, “My foot is slipping,” Your covenant faithfulness, Yahweh, held me up.<verse eid="PSA 94:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 94:19"/>When cares within me are many, your consolations make me happy.<verse eid="PSA 94:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 94:20"/>Can a throne of destruction be allied with you, one who creates injustice by statute?<verse eid="PSA 94:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 94:21"/>They conspire together to take the life of the righteous and they condemn the innocent to death.<verse eid="PSA 94:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 94:22"/>But Yahweh has been my high tower, and my God has been the rock of my refuge.<verse eid="PSA 94:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 94:23"/>He will bring on them their own iniquity and will cut them off in their own wickedness. Yahweh our God will cut them off.<verse eid="PSA 94:23"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 94"/>
<chapter number="95" style="c" sid="PSA 95"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 95:1"/>Oh come, let us sing to Yahweh; let us sing joyfully to the rock of our salvation.<verse eid="PSA 95:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 95:2"/>Let us enter his presence with thanksgiving; let us sing to him with psalms of praise.<verse eid="PSA 95:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 95:3"/>For Yahweh is a great God and a great King superior to all gods.<verse eid="PSA 95:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 95:4"/>In his hand are the depths of the earth; the heights of the mountains are his.<verse eid="PSA 95:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 95:5"/>The sea is his, for he made it, and his hands formed the dry land.<verse eid="PSA 95:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 95:6"/>Oh come, let us worship and bow down; let us kneel before Yahweh, our Creator:<verse eid="PSA 95:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 95:7"/>For he is our God, and we are the people of his pasture and the sheep of his hand. Today—oh, that you would hear his voice!<verse eid="PSA 95:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 95:8"/>“Do not harden your heart, as at Meribah, or as on the day of Massah in the wilderness,<verse eid="PSA 95:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 95:9"/>where your forefathers tested me and tried me, though they had seen my deeds.<verse eid="PSA 95:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 95:10"/>For forty years I was angry with that generation and said, ‘This is a people whose hearts wander astray; they have not known my ways.’<verse eid="PSA 95:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 95:11"/>Therefore I vowed in my anger that they would never enter into my resting place.”<verse eid="PSA 95:11"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 95"/>
<chapter number="96" style="c" sid="PSA 96"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 96:1"/>Oh, sing to Yahweh a new song; sing to Yahweh, all the earth.<verse eid="PSA 96:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 96:2"/>Sing to Yahweh, bless his name; announce his salvation day after day.<verse eid="PSA 96:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 96:3"/>Declare his glory among the nations, his marvelous deeds among all the nations.<verse eid="PSA 96:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 96:4"/>For Yahweh is great and is to be praised greatly. He is to be feared above all other gods.<verse eid="PSA 96:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 96:5"/>For all the gods of the nations are idols, but it is Yahweh who made the heavens.<verse eid="PSA 96:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 96:6"/>Splendor and majesty are in his presence. Strength and beauty are in his sanctuary.<verse eid="PSA 96:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 96:7"/>Ascribe to Yahweh, you clans of peoples, ascribe praise to Yahweh for his glory and strength.<verse eid="PSA 96:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 96:8"/>Give to Yahweh the glory that his name deserves. Bring an offering and come into his courts.<verse eid="PSA 96:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 96:9"/>Bow down to Yahweh in the splendor of holiness; tremble before him, all the earth.<verse eid="PSA 96:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 96:10"/>Say among the nations, “Yahweh reigns.” The world also is established; it cannot be shaken. He judges the peoples fairly.<verse eid="PSA 96:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 96:11"/>Let the heavens be glad, and let the earth rejoice; let the sea roar and that which fills it shout with joy.<verse eid="PSA 96:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 96:12"/>Let the fields rejoice and all that is in them. Then let all the trees in the forest shout for joy<verse eid="PSA 96:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 96:13"/>before Yahweh, for he is coming. He is coming to judge the earth. He will judge the world with righteousness and the peoples with his faithfulness.<verse eid="PSA 96:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 96"/>
<chapter number="97" style="c" sid="PSA 97"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 97:1"/>Yahweh reigns; let the earth rejoice; let the many coastlands be glad.<verse eid="PSA 97:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 97:2"/>Clouds and darkness surround him. Righteousness and justice are the foundation of his throne.<verse eid="PSA 97:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 97:3"/>Fire goes before him and consumes his adversaries on every side.<verse eid="PSA 97:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 97:4"/>His lightning lights up the world; the earth sees and trembles.<verse eid="PSA 97:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 97:5"/>The mountains melt like wax before Yahweh, the Lord of the whole earth.<verse eid="PSA 97:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 97:6"/>The skies declare his justice, and all the nations see his glory.<verse eid="PSA 97:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 97:7"/>All those who worship carved figures will be shamed, those who boast in worthless idols— bow down to him, all you gods!<verse eid="PSA 97:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 97:8"/>Zion heard and was glad, and the towns of Judah rejoiced because of your righteous decrees, Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 97:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 97:9"/>For you, Yahweh, are most high above all the earth. You are exalted far above all gods.<verse eid="PSA 97:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 97:10"/>You who love Yahweh, hate evil! He protects the lives of his faithful ones, and he takes them out of the hand of the wicked.<verse eid="PSA 97:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 97:11"/>Light is sown for the righteous and gladness for those with honest hearts.<verse eid="PSA 97:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 97:12"/>Be glad in Yahweh, you righteous; and give thanks when you remember his holiness.<verse eid="PSA 97:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 97"/>
<chapter number="98" style="c" sid="PSA 98"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 98:1"/>A psalm. Oh, sing to Yahweh a new song, for he has done marvelous things; his right hand and his holy arm have given him victory.<verse eid="PSA 98:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 98:2"/>Yahweh has made known his salvation; he has openly showed his justice to all the nations.<verse eid="PSA 98:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 98:3"/>He calls to mind his covenant loyalty and faithfulness for the house of Israel; all the ends of the earth will see the victory of our God.<verse eid="PSA 98:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 98:4"/>Shout for joy to Yahweh, all the earth; burst into song, sing for joy, and sing praises.<verse eid="PSA 98:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 98:5"/>Sing praises to Yahweh with the harp, with the harp and melodious song.<verse eid="PSA 98:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 98:6"/>With trumpets and the sound of the horn, make a joyful noise before the King, Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 98:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 98:7"/>Let the sea shout and everything in it, the world and those who live in it!<verse eid="PSA 98:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 98:8"/>Let the rivers clap their hands, and let the mountains shout for joy.<verse eid="PSA 98:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 98:9"/>Yahweh is coming to judge the earth; he will judge the world with righteousness and the nations with fairness.<verse eid="PSA 98:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 98"/>
<chapter number="99" style="c" sid="PSA 99"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 99:1"/>Yahweh reigns; let the nations tremble. He sits enthroned above the cherubim; the earth quakes.<verse eid="PSA 99:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 99:2"/>Yahweh is great in Zion; he is exalted above all the nations.<verse eid="PSA 99:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 99:3"/>Let them praise your great and awesome name; he is holy.<verse eid="PSA 99:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 99:4"/>The king is strong, and he loves justice. You have established fairness; you have done righteousness and justice in Jacob.<verse eid="PSA 99:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 99:5"/>Praise Yahweh our God and worship at his footstool. He is holy.<verse eid="PSA 99:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 99:6"/>Moses and Aaron were among his priests, and Samuel was among those who called on his name. They called to Yahweh, and he answered them.<verse eid="PSA 99:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 99:7"/>He spoke to them from the pillar of cloud. They kept his solemn commands and the statutes that he gave them.<verse eid="PSA 99:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 99:8"/>You answered them, Yahweh our God. A forgiving God you were to them, but one who punished their sinful deeds.<verse eid="PSA 99:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 99:9"/>Praise Yahweh our God, and worship at his holy hill, for Yahweh our God is holy.<verse eid="PSA 99:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 99"/>
<chapter number="100" style="c" sid="PSA 100"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 100:1"/>A psalm of thanksgiving. Shout joyfully to Yahweh, all the earth.<verse eid="PSA 100:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 100:2"/>Serve Yahweh with gladness; come before his presence with joyful singing.<verse eid="PSA 100:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 100:3"/>Know that Yahweh is God; he made us, and we are his. We are his people and the sheep of his pasture.<verse eid="PSA 100:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 100:4"/>Enter into his gates with thanksgiving and into his courts with praise. Give thanks to him and bless his name.<verse eid="PSA 100:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 100:5"/>For Yahweh is good; his covenant faithfulness endures forever and his truthfulness through all generations.<verse eid="PSA 100:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 100"/>
<chapter number="101" style="c" sid="PSA 101"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 101:1"/>A psalm of David. A Psalm of David I will sing of covenant faithfulness and justice; to you, Yahweh, I will sing praises.<verse eid="PSA 101:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 101:2"/>I will walk in the way of integrity. Oh, when will you come to me? I will walk with integrity within my house.<verse eid="PSA 101:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 101:3"/>I will not put wrongdoing before my eyes; I hate worthless evil; it will not cling to me.<verse eid="PSA 101:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 101:4"/>Perverse people will leave me; I am not loyal to evil.<verse eid="PSA 101:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 101:5"/>I will destroy whoever secretly slanders his neighbor. I will not tolerate anyone who has a proud demeanor and an arrogant attitude.<verse eid="PSA 101:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 101:6"/>I will look to the faithful of the land to sit at my side. Those who walk in the way of integrity may serve me.<verse eid="PSA 101:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 101:7"/>Deceitful people will not remain within my house; liars will not be welcome before my eyes.<verse eid="PSA 101:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 101:8"/>Morning by morning I will destroy all the wicked from the land; I will remove all evildoers from the city of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 101:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 101"/>
<chapter number="102" style="c" sid="PSA 102"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 102:1"/>A prayer of the afflicted when he is faint and pours out his lament before Yahweh. Hear my prayer, Yahweh; let my cry come near to you.<verse eid="PSA 102:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 102:2"/>Do not hide your face from me in my time of trouble. Listen to me. When I call out to you, answer me quickly.<verse eid="PSA 102:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 102:3"/>For my days pass away like smoke, and my bones burn like fire.<verse eid="PSA 102:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 102:4"/>My heart is crushed, and I am like grass that has withered. I forget to eat any food.<verse eid="PSA 102:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 102:5"/>With my continual groaning, I have become very thin.<verse eid="PSA 102:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 102:6"/>I am like a pelican of the wilderness; I have become like an owl in the ruins.<verse eid="PSA 102:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 102:7"/>I lie awake like a solitary bird, alone on the housetop.<verse eid="PSA 102:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 102:8"/>My enemies taunt me all day long; those who mock me use my name in curses.<verse eid="PSA 102:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 102:9"/>I eat ashes like bread and mix my drink with tears.<verse eid="PSA 102:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 102:10"/>Because of your raging anger, you have lifted me up to throw me down.<verse eid="PSA 102:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 102:11"/>My days are like a shadow that fades, and I have withered like grass.<verse eid="PSA 102:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 102:12"/>But you, Yahweh, live forever, and your fame is for all generations.<verse eid="PSA 102:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 102:13"/>You will rise up and have mercy on Zion. Now is the time to have mercy upon her; the appointed time has come.<verse eid="PSA 102:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 102:14"/>For your servants hold her stones dear and feel compassion for the dust of her ruins.<verse eid="PSA 102:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 102:15"/>The nations will respect your name, Yahweh, and all the kings of the earth will honor your glory.<verse eid="PSA 102:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 102:16"/>Yahweh will rebuild Zion and will appear in his glory.<verse eid="PSA 102:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 102:17"/>At that time, he will respond to the prayer of the destitute; he will not reject their prayer.<verse eid="PSA 102:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 102:18"/>This will be written for future generations, and a people not yet born will praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 102:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 102:19"/>For he has looked down from the holy heights; from heaven Yahweh has viewed the earth,<verse eid="PSA 102:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 102:20"/>to hear the groaning of the prisoners, to release those who were condemned to death.<verse eid="PSA 102:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 102:21"/>Then men will proclaim the name of Yahweh in Zion and his praise in Jerusalem<verse eid="PSA 102:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 102:22"/>when the peoples and kingdoms gather together to serve Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 102:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 102:23"/>He has taken away my strength in the middle of life. He has shortened my days.<verse eid="PSA 102:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 102:24"/>I said, “My God, do not take me away in the middle of life; you are here throughout all generations.<verse eid="PSA 102:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 102:25"/>In ancient times you set the earth in place; the heavens are the work of your hands.<verse eid="PSA 102:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 102:26"/>They will perish, but you will remain; they will all grow old like a garment; like clothing, you will remove them, and they will disappear.<verse eid="PSA 102:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 102:27"/>But you are the same, and your years will have no end.<verse eid="PSA 102:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 102:28"/>The children of your servants will live on, and their descendants will live in your presence.”<verse eid="PSA 102:28"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 102"/>
<chapter number="103" style="c" sid="PSA 103"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 103:1"/>A psalm of David. Of David Bless Yahweh, my inner being! and all that is within me, bless his holy name.<verse eid="PSA 103:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 103:2"/>Bless Yahweh, my soul! and do not forget all of his rewards.<verse eid="PSA 103:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 103:3"/>He pardons all your sins; he heals all your diseases.<verse eid="PSA 103:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 103:4"/>He redeems your life from destruction; he crowns you with steadfastness and mercy.<verse eid="PSA 103:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 103:5"/>He satisfies you with good things; your youth is renewed like the eagle.<verse eid="PSA 103:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 103:6"/>Yahweh does what is right and what is just for all the oppressed.<verse eid="PSA 103:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 103:7"/>He made known his ways to Moses, his deeds to the children of Israel.<verse eid="PSA 103:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 103:8"/>Yahweh is gracious and merciful, slow to anger, and abounding in steadfast love.<verse eid="PSA 103:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 103:9"/>He will not always discipline, and he will not keep his anger forever.<verse eid="PSA 103:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 103:10"/>He does not deal with us according to our sins, and he does not treat us according to our iniquities.<verse eid="PSA 103:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 103:11"/>For as the skies are high above the earth, so great is his steadfast love toward those who fear him.<verse eid="PSA 103:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 103:12"/>As far as the east is from the west, this is how far he has removed our transgressions from us.<verse eid="PSA 103:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 103:13"/>As a father has compassion on his children, so Yahweh has compassion on those who fear him.<verse eid="PSA 103:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 103:14"/>For he knows our form; remembering that we are dust.<verse eid="PSA 103:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 103:15"/>As for man, his days are like grass; like the flower of the field he flourishes so.<verse eid="PSA 103:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 103:16"/>For the wind blows over it, and it is no more, and its place does not acknowledge it again.<verse eid="PSA 103:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 103:17"/>But the covenant faithfulness of Yahweh is from everlasting to everlasting on those who honor him, and His righteousness is to their children's children.<verse eid="PSA 103:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 103:18"/>To the ones who keep his covenant, and to the ones who remember his precepts in order to do them.<verse eid="PSA 103:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 103:19"/>Yahweh has established his throne in the heavens, and his kingdom rules over all.<verse eid="PSA 103:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 103:20"/>Bless Yahweh, you his angels, you mighty warriors who do his word, obeying the voice of his word.<verse eid="PSA 103:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 103:21"/>Bless Yahweh, all his hosts, his ministers who do his pleasure.<verse eid="PSA 103:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 103:22"/>Bless Yahweh, all his works, in all the places where he reigns. Bless Yahweh, my inner being!<verse eid="PSA 103:22"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 103"/>
<chapter number="104" style="c" sid="PSA 104"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 104:1"/>I give praise to Yahweh with all my life, Yahweh my God, you are very magnificent; you are clothed with splendor and majesty.<verse eid="PSA 104:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 104:2"/>You cover yourself with light as with a garment; you spread out the heavens like a tent curtain.<verse eid="PSA 104:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 104:3"/>You lay the beams of your chambers on the clouds; you make the clouds your chariot; you walk on the wings of the wind.<verse eid="PSA 104:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 104:4"/>He makes the winds his messengers, flames of fire his servants.<verse eid="PSA 104:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 104:5"/>He laid the foundations of the earth, and it will never be moved.<verse eid="PSA 104:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 104:6"/>You covered the earth with water like a garment; the water covered the mountains.<verse eid="PSA 104:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 104:7"/>Your rebuke made the waters recede; at the sound of your thunderous voice they fled.<verse eid="PSA 104:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 104:8"/>The mountains rose, and the valleys spread out into the places that you had appointed for them.<verse eid="PSA 104:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 104:9"/>You have set a boundary for them that they will not cross; they will not cover the earth again.<verse eid="PSA 104:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 104:10"/>He made springs flow into the valleys; the streams flow between the mountains.<verse eid="PSA 104:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 104:11"/>They supply water for all the animals of the field; the wild donkeys quench their thirst.<verse eid="PSA 104:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 104:12"/>By the heavens the birds build their nests; they sing among the branches.<verse eid="PSA 104:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 104:13"/>He waters the mountains from his water chambers in the sky. The earth is filled with the fruit of his labor.<verse eid="PSA 104:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 104:14"/>He makes the grass grow for the cattle and plants for man to cultivate so that man may produce food from the earth.<verse eid="PSA 104:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 104:15"/>He makes wine to make man happy, oil to make his face shine, and food to sustain his life.<verse eid="PSA 104:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 104:16"/>The trees of Yahweh get plenty of rain; the cedars of Lebanon which he planted.<verse eid="PSA 104:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 104:17"/>There the birds make their nests. The stork makes the cypress tree her home.<verse eid="PSA 104:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 104:18"/>The wild goats live on the high mountains; the mountain heights are a refuge for the hyraxes.<verse eid="PSA 104:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 104:19"/>He appointed the moon to mark the seasons; the sun knows its time for setting.<verse eid="PSA 104:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 104:20"/>You make the darkness of the night when all the beasts of the forest come out.<verse eid="PSA 104:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 104:21"/>The young lions roar for their prey and seek their food from God.<verse eid="PSA 104:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 104:22"/>When the sun rises, they retreat and sleep in their dens.<verse eid="PSA 104:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 104:23"/>Meanwhile, people go out to their work and labor away until the evening.<verse eid="PSA 104:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 104:24"/>Yahweh, how many and varied are your works! With wisdom you made them all; the earth overflows with your works.<verse eid="PSA 104:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 104:25"/>Over there is the sea, deep and wide, teeming with innumerable creatures, both small and great.<verse eid="PSA 104:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 104:26"/>The ships travel there, and Leviathan is also there, which you formed to play in the sea.<verse eid="PSA 104:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 104:27"/>All these look to you to give them their food on time.<verse eid="PSA 104:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 104:28"/>When you give to them, they gather; when you open your hand, they are satisfied.<verse eid="PSA 104:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 104:29"/>When you hide your face, they are troubled; if you take away their breath, they die and return to dust.<verse eid="PSA 104:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 104:30"/>When you send out your Spirit, they are created, and you renew the countryside.<verse eid="PSA 104:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 104:31"/>May the glory of Yahweh last forever; may Yahweh enjoy his creation.<verse eid="PSA 104:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 104:32"/>He looks down on the earth, and it shakes; he touches the mountains, and they smoke.<verse eid="PSA 104:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 104:33"/>I will sing to Yahweh all my life; I will sing praise to my God as long as I live.<verse eid="PSA 104:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 104:34"/>May my thoughts be sweet to him; I will rejoice in Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 104:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 104:35"/>May sinners vanish from the earth, and let the wicked be no more. I give praise to Yahweh with all my life. Praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 104:35"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 104"/>
<chapter number="105" style="c" sid="PSA 105"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 105:1"/>Give thanks to Yahweh, call on his name; make known his deeds among the nations.<verse eid="PSA 105:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 105:2"/>Sing to him, sing praises to him; speak of all his marvelous deeds.<verse eid="PSA 105:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 105:3"/>Boast in his holy name; let the heart of those who seek Yahweh rejoice.<verse eid="PSA 105:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 105:4"/>Seek Yahweh and his strength; seek his presence continually.<verse eid="PSA 105:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 105:5"/>Recall the marvelous things he has done, his miracles and the decrees from his mouth,<verse eid="PSA 105:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 105:6"/>you descendants of Abraham his servant, you people of Jacob, his chosen ones.<verse eid="PSA 105:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 105:7"/>He is Yahweh, our God. His decrees are on all the earth.<verse eid="PSA 105:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 105:8"/>He keeps in mind his covenant forever, the word that he commanded for a thousand generations.<verse eid="PSA 105:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 105:9"/>He calls to mind the covenant that he made with Abraham and his oath to Isaac.<verse eid="PSA 105:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 105:10"/>This is what he confirmed to Jacob as a statute and to Israel as an everlasting covenant.<verse eid="PSA 105:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 105:11"/>He said, “I will give you the land of Canaan as your share of your inheritance.”<verse eid="PSA 105:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 105:12"/>He said this when they were only few in number, so very few, and were strangers in the land.<verse eid="PSA 105:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 105:13"/>They went from nation to nation and from one kingdom to another.<verse eid="PSA 105:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 105:14"/>He did not allow anyone to oppress them; he rebuked kings for their sakes.<verse eid="PSA 105:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 105:15"/>He said, “Do not touch my anointed ones, and do not harm my prophets.”<verse eid="PSA 105:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 105:16"/>He called for a famine on the land; he cut off the whole supply of bread.<verse eid="PSA 105:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 105:17"/>He sent a man ahead of them; Joseph was sold as a servant.<verse eid="PSA 105:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 105:18"/>His feet were bound by shackles; on his neck was put an iron collar,<verse eid="PSA 105:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 105:19"/>until what he had said came to pass. The word of Yahweh tested him.<verse eid="PSA 105:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 105:20"/>The king sent servants to release him; the ruler of the people set him free.<verse eid="PSA 105:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 105:21"/>He put him in charge of his house as ruler of all his possessions<verse eid="PSA 105:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 105:22"/>to instruct his princes as he wished and to teach his elders wisdom.<verse eid="PSA 105:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 105:23"/>Then Israel came into Egypt, and Jacob lived for a time in the land of Ham.<verse eid="PSA 105:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 105:24"/>Yahweh made his people fruitful, and made them stronger greatly than their enemies.<verse eid="PSA 105:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 105:25"/>He caused their enemies to hate his people, to mistreat his servants.<verse eid="PSA 105:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 105:26"/>He sent Moses, his servant, and Aaron, whom he had chosen.<verse eid="PSA 105:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 105:27"/>They performed his signs among the Egyptians, his wonders in the land of Ham.<verse eid="PSA 105:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 105:28"/>He sent darkness and made that land dark, but its people did not obey his commands.<verse eid="PSA 105:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 105:29"/>He turned their water into blood and killed their fish.<verse eid="PSA 105:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 105:30"/>Their land swarmed with frogs, even in the rooms of their rulers.<verse eid="PSA 105:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 105:31"/>He spoke, and swarms of flies and gnats came throughout their country.<verse eid="PSA 105:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 105:32"/>He turned their rain into hail, with fire flaming on their land.<verse eid="PSA 105:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 105:33"/>He destroyed their vines and fig trees; he broke the trees of their country.<verse eid="PSA 105:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 105:34"/>He spoke, and the locusts came, young locusts, without number.<verse eid="PSA 105:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 105:35"/>The locusts ate up all of the vegetation in their land; They ate up all the crops of the ground.<verse eid="PSA 105:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 105:36"/>He killed every firstborn in their land, the firstfruits of all their strength.<verse eid="PSA 105:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 105:37"/>He brought the Israelites out with silver and gold; none of his tribes stumbled on the way.<verse eid="PSA 105:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 105:38"/>Egypt was glad when they went away, for the fear of them had fallen upon them.<verse eid="PSA 105:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 105:39"/>He spread a cloud for a covering and made a fire to light up the night.<verse eid="PSA 105:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 105:40"/>The Israelites asked for food, and he brought quail and satisfied them with bread from heaven.<verse eid="PSA 105:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 105:41"/>He split the rock, and waters gushed from it; they flowed in the wilderness like a river.<verse eid="PSA 105:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 105:42"/>For he called to mind his holy promise that he made to Abraham his servant.<verse eid="PSA 105:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 105:43"/>He led his people out with joy, his chosen with shouts of triumph.<verse eid="PSA 105:43"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="44" style="v" sid="PSA 105:44"/>He gave them the lands of the nations; they took possession of the wealth of the peoples<verse eid="PSA 105:44"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="45" style="v" sid="PSA 105:45"/>so that they might keep his statutes and obey his laws. Praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 105:45"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 105"/>
<chapter number="106" style="c" sid="PSA 106"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 106:1"/>Praise Yahweh. Give thanks to Yahweh, for he is good, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 106:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 106:2"/>Who can recount the mighty acts of Yahweh or proclaim in full all his praiseworthy deeds?<verse eid="PSA 106:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 106:3"/>Blessed are those who do what is right, and whose deeds are always just.<verse eid="PSA 106:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 106:4"/>Call me to mind, Yahweh, when you show favor to your people; help me when you save them.<verse eid="PSA 106:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 106:5"/>Then I will see the prosperity of your chosen, rejoice in the gladness of your nation, and glory with your inheritance.<verse eid="PSA 106:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 106:6"/>We have sinned like our ancestors; we have done wrong, and we have done evil.<verse eid="PSA 106:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 106:7"/>Our fathers did not appreciate your marvelous deeds in Egypt; they ignored your many acts of covenant faithfulness; they were rebellious at the sea, the Sea of Reeds.<verse eid="PSA 106:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 106:8"/>Nevertheless, he saved them for his name’s sake so that he might reveal his power.<verse eid="PSA 106:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 106:9"/>He rebuked the Sea of Reeds, and it dried up. Then he led them through the depths, as through a wilderness.<verse eid="PSA 106:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 106:10"/>He saved them from the hand of those who hated them, and he rescued them from the hand of the enemy.<verse eid="PSA 106:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 106:11"/>But the waters covered their adversaries; not one of them survived.<verse eid="PSA 106:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 106:12"/>Then they believed his words, and they sang his praise.<verse eid="PSA 106:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 106:13"/>But they quickly forgot what he had done; they did not wait for his instructions.<verse eid="PSA 106:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 106:14"/>They had insatiable cravings in the wilderness, and they challenged God in the desert.<verse eid="PSA 106:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 106:15"/>So he gave them what they requested, but he sent a horrible disease upon them.<verse eid="PSA 106:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 106:16"/>In the camp they became jealous of Moses and Aaron, the holy priest of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 106:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 106:17"/>The earth opened and swallowed up Dathan and covered the followers of Abiram.<verse eid="PSA 106:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 106:18"/>Fire broke out among them; the fire consumed the wicked.<verse eid="PSA 106:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 106:19"/>They made a calf at Horeb and worshiped a cast metal figure.<verse eid="PSA 106:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 106:20"/>They traded the glory of God for the image of a bull that eats grass.<verse eid="PSA 106:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 106:21"/>They forgot God their Savior, who had done great deeds in Egypt.<verse eid="PSA 106:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 106:22"/>He had done wonderful things in the land of Ham and mighty acts at the Sea of Reeds.<verse eid="PSA 106:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 106:23"/>So he said he would destroy them— had not Moses, his chosen one, stood in the breach before him, to turn away his anger from destroying them.<verse eid="PSA 106:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 106:24"/>Then they despised the fruitful land; they did not believe his promise,<verse eid="PSA 106:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 106:25"/>but grumbled in their tents, and did not obey Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 106:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 106:26"/>Therefore he raised his hand and swore to them that he would let them die in the desert,<verse eid="PSA 106:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 106:27"/>scatter their descendants among the nations, and scatter them in foreign lands.<verse eid="PSA 106:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 106:28"/>They worshiped the Baal of Peor and ate the sacrifices offered to the dead.<verse eid="PSA 106:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 106:29"/>They provoked him to anger with their actions, and a plague broke out among them.<verse eid="PSA 106:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 106:30"/>Then Phinehas rose to intervene, and the plague subsided.<verse eid="PSA 106:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 106:31"/>It was counted to him as a righteous deed to all generations forever.<verse eid="PSA 106:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 106:32"/>They also angered Yahweh at the waters of Meribah, and Moses suffered because of them.<verse eid="PSA 106:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 106:33"/>They made Moses bitter, and he spoke rashly.<verse eid="PSA 106:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 106:34"/>They did not destroy the nations as Yahweh had commanded them,<verse eid="PSA 106:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 106:35"/>but they mingled with the nations and learned their ways<verse eid="PSA 106:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 106:36"/>and worshiped their idols, which became a snare to them.<verse eid="PSA 106:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 106:37"/>They sacrificed their sons and their daughters to demons.<verse eid="PSA 106:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 106:38"/>They shed innocent blood, the blood of their sons and of their daughters, whom they sacrificed to the idols of Canaan, desecrating the land with blood.<verse eid="PSA 106:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 106:39"/>They were defiled by their deeds; in their actions they were like prostitutes.<verse eid="PSA 106:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 106:40"/>So Yahweh was angry with his people, and he despised his own people.<verse eid="PSA 106:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 106:41"/>He gave them into the hand of the nations, and those who hated them ruled over them.<verse eid="PSA 106:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 106:42"/>Their enemies oppressed them, and they were brought into subjection to their authority.<verse eid="PSA 106:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 106:43"/>Many times he came to help them, but they kept rebelling and were brought low by their own sin.<verse eid="PSA 106:43"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="44" style="v" sid="PSA 106:44"/>Nevertheless, he paid attention to their distress when he heard their cry for help.<verse eid="PSA 106:44"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="45" style="v" sid="PSA 106:45"/>He called to mind his covenant with them and relented because of his steadfast love.<verse eid="PSA 106:45"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="46" style="v" sid="PSA 106:46"/>He caused all their conquerers to have pity on them.<verse eid="PSA 106:46"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="47" style="v" sid="PSA 106:47"/>Save us, Yahweh, our God. Gather us from among the nations so that we may give thanks to your holy name and glory in your praises.<verse eid="PSA 106:47"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="48" style="v" sid="PSA 106:48"/>May Yahweh, the God of Israel, be praised from everlasting to everlasting. All the people said, “Amen.” Praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 106:48"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 106"/>
<chapter number="107" style="c" sid="PSA 107"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 107:1"/>Give thanks to Yahweh, for he is good, and his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 107:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 107:2"/>Let the redeemed of Yahweh speak out, those he has rescued from the hand of the enemy.<verse eid="PSA 107:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 107:3"/>He has gathered them out of foreign lands, from the east and from the west, from the north and from the south.<verse eid="PSA 107:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 107:4"/>They wandered in the wilderness on a desert road and found no city in which to live.<verse eid="PSA 107:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 107:5"/>Because they were hungry and thirsty, they fainted from exhaustion.<verse eid="PSA 107:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 107:6"/>Then they called out to Yahweh in their trouble, and he rescued them out of their distress.<verse eid="PSA 107:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 107:7"/>He led them by a direct path so that they would go to a city to live in.<verse eid="PSA 107:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 107:8"/>Oh that people would praise Yahweh for his covenant faithfulness and for the amazing things he has done for humanity!<verse eid="PSA 107:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 107:9"/>For he satisfies the longings of those who are thirsty, and the desires of those who are hungry he fills up with good things.<verse eid="PSA 107:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 107:10"/>Some sat in darkness and in gloom, prisoners in affliction and chains.<verse eid="PSA 107:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 107:11"/>This was because they had rebelled against God’s word and rejected the instruction of the Most High.<verse eid="PSA 107:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 107:12"/>He humbled their hearts through hardship; they stumbled and there was no one to help them up.<verse eid="PSA 107:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 107:13"/>Then they called out to Yahweh in their trouble, and he brought them out of their distress.<verse eid="PSA 107:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 107:14"/>He brought them out of darkness and gloom and broke their bonds.<verse eid="PSA 107:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 107:15"/>Oh that people would praise Yahweh for his covenant faithfulness and for the amazing things he has done for humanity!<verse eid="PSA 107:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 107:16"/>For he has broken the gates of bronze and cut through the bars of iron.<verse eid="PSA 107:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 107:17"/>They were foolish in their rebellious ways and afflicted because of their sins.<verse eid="PSA 107:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 107:18"/>They lost their desire to eat any food, and they came close to the gates of death.<verse eid="PSA 107:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 107:19"/>Then they called out to Yahweh in their trouble, and he brought them out of their distress.<verse eid="PSA 107:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 107:20"/>He sent his word and healed them, and he rescued them from their destruction.<verse eid="PSA 107:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 107:21"/>Oh that people would praise Yahweh for his covenant faithfulness and for the amazing things he has done for humanity!<verse eid="PSA 107:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 107:22"/>Let them offer the sacrifices of thanksgiving and proclaim his deeds in singing.<verse eid="PSA 107:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 107:23"/>Some travel on the sea in ships and do business overseas.<verse eid="PSA 107:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 107:24"/>These saw the deeds of Yahweh and his wonders on the seas.<verse eid="PSA 107:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 107:25"/>For he commanded and aroused the windstorm that stirs up the seas.<verse eid="PSA 107:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 107:26"/>They reached up to the sky; they went down to the depths. Their lives melted away in distress.<verse eid="PSA 107:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 107:27"/>They swayed and staggered like drunkards and were at their wits’ end.<verse eid="PSA 107:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 107:28"/>Then they called out to Yahweh in their trouble, and he brought them out of their distress.<verse eid="PSA 107:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 107:29"/>He calmed the storm, and the waves were stilled.<verse eid="PSA 107:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 107:30"/>Then they rejoiced because they are quiet, so he brought them to their desired harbor.<verse eid="PSA 107:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 107:31"/>Oh that people would praise Yahweh for his covenant faithfulness and for the amazing things he has done for humanity!<verse eid="PSA 107:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 107:32"/>Let them exalt him in the assembly of the people and praise him in the council of the elders.<verse eid="PSA 107:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 107:33"/>He turns rivers into a wilderness, springs of water into dry land,<verse eid="PSA 107:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 107:34"/>and a fruitful land into a barren place because of the wickedness of those who dwell in it.<verse eid="PSA 107:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 107:35"/>He turns the wilderness into a pool of water and dry land into springs of water.<verse eid="PSA 107:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 107:36"/>He settles the hungry there, and they build a city to live in.<verse eid="PSA 107:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 107:37"/>They sow fields and plant vineyards, that they may bring in a fruitful harvest.<verse eid="PSA 107:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 107:38"/>He blesses them so they are very numerous. He does not let their cattle decrease in number.<verse eid="PSA 107:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 107:39"/>They were diminished and brought low by painful distress and suffering.<verse eid="PSA 107:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 107:40"/>He pours contempt on the leaders and causes them to wander in the wilderness, where there are no roads.<verse eid="PSA 107:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 107:41"/>But he protects the needy from affliction and cares for his families like a flock.<verse eid="PSA 107:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 107:42"/>The upright will see this and rejoice, and all wickedness shuts its mouth.<verse eid="PSA 107:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 107:43"/>Whoever is wise should take note of these things and meditate on Yahweh’s acts of covenant faithfulness.<verse eid="PSA 107:43"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 107"/>
<chapter number="108" style="c" sid="PSA 108"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 108:1"/>A song, a psalm of David. My heart is fixed, God; I will sing, yes, I will sing praises also with my honored heart.<verse eid="PSA 108:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 108:2"/>Wake up, lute and harp; I will wake up the dawn.<verse eid="PSA 108:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 108:3"/>I will give thanks to you, Yahweh, among the peoples; I will sing praises to you among the nations.<verse eid="PSA 108:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 108:4"/>For your covenant faithfulness is great above the heavens; and your trustworthiness reaches to the skies.<verse eid="PSA 108:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 108:5"/>Be exalted, God, above the heavens, and may your glory be exalted over all the earth.<verse eid="PSA 108:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 108:6"/>So that those you love may be rescued, rescue us with your right hand and answer me.<verse eid="PSA 108:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 108:7"/>God has spoken in his holiness; “I will rejoice; I will divide Shechem and apportion out the Valley of Succoth.<verse eid="PSA 108:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 108:8"/>Gilead is mine, and Manasseh is mine; Ephraim also is my helmet; Judah is my scepter.<verse eid="PSA 108:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 108:9"/>Moab is my washbasin; over Edom I will throw my shoe; I will shout in triumph because of Philistia.<verse eid="PSA 108:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 108:10"/>Who will bring me into the strong city? Who will lead me to Edom?”<verse eid="PSA 108:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 108:11"/>God, have you not rejected us? You do not go into battle with our army.<verse eid="PSA 108:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 108:12"/>Give us help against the enemy, for man’s help is futile.<verse eid="PSA 108:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 108:13"/>We will triumph with God’s help; he will trample down our enemies.<verse eid="PSA 108:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 108"/>
<chapter number="109" style="c" sid="PSA 109"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 109:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. To the chief musician. A Psalm of David. God whom I praise, do not be silent,<verse eid="PSA 109:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 109:2"/>For the wicked and deceitful attack me; they speak lies against me.<verse eid="PSA 109:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 109:3"/>They surround me and say hateful things, and they attack me without cause.<verse eid="PSA 109:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 109:4"/>In return for my love they accuse me, but I pray for them.<verse eid="PSA 109:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 109:5"/>They repay me evil for good, and they hate my love.<verse eid="PSA 109:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 109:6"/>Appoint a wicked man over such an enemy as these people; appoint an accuser to stand at his right hand.<verse eid="PSA 109:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 109:7"/>When he is judged, may he be found guilty; may his prayer be considered sinful.<verse eid="PSA 109:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 109:8"/>May his days be few; may another take his office.<verse eid="PSA 109:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 109:9"/>May his children be fatherless, and may his wife be a widow.<verse eid="PSA 109:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 109:10"/>May his children wander about and beg, asking for handouts as they leave their ruined home.<verse eid="PSA 109:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 109:11"/>May the creditor take all he owns; may strangers plunder what he earns.<verse eid="PSA 109:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 109:12"/>May no one extend any kindness to him; may no one have pity on his fatherless children.<verse eid="PSA 109:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 109:13"/>May his children be cut off; may their name be blotted out in the next generation.<verse eid="PSA 109:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 109:14"/>May his ancestors’ sins be mentioned to Yahweh; and may the sin of his mother not be forgotten.<verse eid="PSA 109:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 109:15"/>May their guilt always be before Yahweh; may Yahweh cut off their memory from the earth.<verse eid="PSA 109:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 109:16"/>May Yahweh do this because this man never bothered to show any covenant faithfulness, but instead harassed the oppressed, the needy, and the disheartened to death.<verse eid="PSA 109:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 109:17"/>He loved cursing; may it come back upon him. He had no desire for blessing; may no blessing come to him.<verse eid="PSA 109:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 109:18"/>He clothed himself with cursing as his garment, and his curse came into his inner being like water, like oil into his bones.<verse eid="PSA 109:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 109:19"/>May his curses be to him like the clothes he wears to cover himself, like the belt he always wears.<verse eid="PSA 109:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 109:20"/>May this be the reward of my accusers from Yahweh, of those who say evil things about me.<verse eid="PSA 109:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 109:21"/>Yahweh my Lord, deal kindly with me for your name’s sake. Because your covenant faithfulness is good, save me.<verse eid="PSA 109:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 109:22"/>For I am oppressed and needy, and my heart is wounded within me.<verse eid="PSA 109:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 109:23"/>I am fading away like the shadow of the evening; I am shaken off like a locust.<verse eid="PSA 109:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 109:24"/>My knees are weak from fasting; My flesh is feeble from lack of fatness.<verse eid="PSA 109:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 109:25"/>I am disdained by my accusers; when they see me, they shake their heads.<verse eid="PSA 109:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 109:26"/>Help me, Yahweh my God; save me by your covenant faithfulness.<verse eid="PSA 109:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 109:27"/>May they know that this is your hand, that you, Yahweh, have done this.<verse eid="PSA 109:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 109:28"/>Though they curse me, please bless me; when they attack, may they be put to shame, but may your servant rejoice.<verse eid="PSA 109:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 109:29"/>May my adversaries be clothed with shame; may they wear their shame like a robe.<verse eid="PSA 109:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 109:30"/>With my mouth I give great thanks to Yahweh; I will praise him in the midst of a crowd.<verse eid="PSA 109:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 109:31"/>For he will stand at the right hand of the one who is needy, to save him from those who judge him.<verse eid="PSA 109:31"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 109"/>
<chapter number="110" style="c" sid="PSA 110"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 110:1"/>A psalm of David. Of David, a song. The declaration of Yahweh to my lord, “Sit at my right hand until I make your enemies a footstool for your feet.”<verse eid="PSA 110:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 110:2"/>Yahweh will stretch out the scepter of your strength from Zion; rule in the midst of your enemies.<verse eid="PSA 110:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 110:3"/>Your people voluntarily follow in holy splendor in the day of your strength; from the womb of the dawn your youth will be to you as dew.<verse eid="PSA 110:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 110:4"/>Yahweh has sworn, and will not change his mind: “You are a priest forever, after the manner of Melchizedek.”<verse eid="PSA 110:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 110:5"/>The Lord is at your right hand. He will crush kings on the day of his anger.<verse eid="PSA 110:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 110:6"/>He will judge the nations; he will fill corpses; he will crush the heads of many lands.<verse eid="PSA 110:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 110:7"/>He will drink from the stream along the path, Therefore, he will lift up the head.<verse eid="PSA 110:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 110"/>
<chapter number="111" style="c" sid="PSA 111"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 111:1"/>Praise Yahweh. I will give thanks to Yahweh with my whole heart in the assembly of the upright, in their gathering.<verse eid="PSA 111:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 111:2"/>The works of Yahweh are great, eagerly awaited by all those who desire them.<verse eid="PSA 111:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 111:3"/>His work is majestic and glorious, and his righteousness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 111:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 111:4"/>He does wonderful things that will be remembered; Yahweh is gracious and merciful.<verse eid="PSA 111:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 111:5"/>He gives food to his faithful followers. He will always call to mind his covenant.<verse eid="PSA 111:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 111:6"/>He showed his powerful works to his people in giving them the inheritance of the nations.<verse eid="PSA 111:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 111:7"/>The works of his hands are trustworthy and just; all his instructions are reliable.<verse eid="PSA 111:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 111:8"/>They are established forever, to be observed faithfully and properly.<verse eid="PSA 111:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 111:9"/>He has sent redemption to his people; he ordained his covenant forever; holy and awesome is his name.<verse eid="PSA 111:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 111:10"/>To honor Yahweh is the beginning of wisdom; those who carry out his instructions have good understanding. His praise endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 111:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 111"/>
<chapter number="112" style="c" sid="PSA 112"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 112:1"/>Praise Yahweh. Blessed is the man who fears Yahweh, who greatly delights in his commandments.<verse eid="PSA 112:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 112:2"/>His descendants will be powerful on earth; the descendants of the godly man will be blessed.<verse eid="PSA 112:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 112:3"/>Wealth and riches are in his house; his righteousness will endure forever.<verse eid="PSA 112:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 112:4"/>Light shines in the darkness for the godly person; he is gracious, merciful, and just.<verse eid="PSA 112:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 112:5"/>It goes well for the man who deals graciously and lends money, who conducts his affairs with honesty.<verse eid="PSA 112:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 112:6"/>For he will never be moved; the righteous person will be remembered forever.<verse eid="PSA 112:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 112:7"/>He does not fear bad news; his heart is sure, trusting in Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 112:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 112:8"/>His heart is tranquil, without fear, until he looks in triumph over his adversaries.<verse eid="PSA 112:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 112:9"/>He generously gives to the poor; his righteousness endures forever; he will be exalted with honor.<verse eid="PSA 112:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 112:10"/>The wicked person will see this and be angry; he will grind his teeth in rage and he will melt away; the desire of the wicked people will perish.<verse eid="PSA 112:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 112"/>
<chapter number="113" style="c" sid="PSA 113"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 113:1"/>Praise Yahweh. Praise him, you servants of Yahweh; praise the name of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 113:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 113:2"/>Blessed be the name of Yahweh, both now and forevermore.<verse eid="PSA 113:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 113:3"/>From the rising of the sun to its setting, Yahweh’s name should be praised.<verse eid="PSA 113:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 113:4"/>Yahweh is exalted above all nations, and his glory reaches above the skies.<verse eid="PSA 113:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 113:5"/>Who is like Yahweh our God, who has his seat on high,<verse eid="PSA 113:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 113:6"/>who looks down at the sky and at the earth?<verse eid="PSA 113:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 113:7"/>He raises up the poor out of the dirt and lifts up the needy from the ash heap,<verse eid="PSA 113:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 113:8"/>so that he may seat him with princes, with the princes of his people.<verse eid="PSA 113:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 113:9"/>He gives a home to the barren woman of the house, he makes her a joyful mother of children. Praise Yahweh!<verse eid="PSA 113:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 113"/>
<chapter number="114" style="c" sid="PSA 114"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 114:1"/>When Israel left Egypt, the house of Jacob from a people who spoke a foreign language,<verse eid="PSA 114:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 114:2"/>Judah became his holy place, Israel his kingdom.<verse eid="PSA 114:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 114:3"/>The sea looked and fled; the Jordan turned back.<verse eid="PSA 114:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 114:4"/>The mountains skipped like rams, the little hills like lambs.<verse eid="PSA 114:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 114:5"/>Why did you flee, sea? Jordan, why did you turn back?<verse eid="PSA 114:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 114:6"/>Mountains, why did you skip like rams? You little hills, why did you skip like lambs?<verse eid="PSA 114:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 114:7"/>Tremble, earth, before the Lord, at the presence of the God of Jacob.<verse eid="PSA 114:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 114:8"/>He turned the rock into a pool of water, the hard rock into a spring of water.<verse eid="PSA 114:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 114"/>
<chapter number="115" style="c" sid="PSA 115"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 115:1"/>Not to us, Yahweh, not to us, but to your name bring honor, for your covenant faithfulness and for your trustworthiness.<verse eid="PSA 115:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 115:2"/>Why should the nations say, “Where is their God?”<verse eid="PSA 115:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 115:3"/>Our God is in heaven; he does whatever he pleases.<verse eid="PSA 115:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 115:4"/>The nations’ idols are silver and gold, the work of men’s hands.<verse eid="PSA 115:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 115:5"/>Those idols have mouths, but they do not speak; they have eyes, but they do not see;<verse eid="PSA 115:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 115:6"/>they have ears, but they do not hear; they have noses, but they do not smell.<verse eid="PSA 115:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 115:7"/>Those idols have hands, but do not feel; they have feet, but they cannot walk; nor do they speak from their mouths.<verse eid="PSA 115:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 115:8"/>Those who make them are like them, as is everyone who trusts in them.<verse eid="PSA 115:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 115:9"/>Israel, trust in Yahweh; he is your help and shield.<verse eid="PSA 115:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 115:10"/>House of Aaron, trust in Yahweh; he is your help and shield.<verse eid="PSA 115:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 115:11"/>You who honor Yahweh, trust in him; he is your help and shield.<verse eid="PSA 115:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 115:12"/>Yahweh takes notice of us and will bless us; he will bless the family of Israel; he will bless the family of Aaron.<verse eid="PSA 115:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 115:13"/>He will bless those who honor him, both young and old.<verse eid="PSA 115:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 115:14"/>May Yahweh increase your numbers more and more, yours and your descendants’.<verse eid="PSA 115:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 115:15"/>May you be blessed by Yahweh, who made heaven and earth.<verse eid="PSA 115:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 115:16"/>The heavens, even the heavens belong to Yahweh; but the earth he has given to the sons of men.<verse eid="PSA 115:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 115:17"/>The dead do not praise Yahweh, nor do any who go down into silence;<verse eid="PSA 115:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 115:18"/>But we will bless Yahweh now and forevermore. Praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 115:18"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 115"/>
<chapter number="116" style="c" sid="PSA 116"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 116:1"/>I love Yahweh because he hears my voice and my pleas for mercy.<verse eid="PSA 116:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 116:2"/>Because he listened to me, I will call on him as long as I live.<verse eid="PSA 116:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 116:3"/>The cords of death surrounded me, and the snares of Sheol confronted me; I felt anguish and sorrow.<verse eid="PSA 116:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 116:4"/>Then I called on the name of Yahweh: “Please Yahweh, rescue my life.”<verse eid="PSA 116:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 116:5"/>Yahweh is merciful and fair; our God is compassionate.<verse eid="PSA 116:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 116:6"/>Yahweh protects the naive; I was brought low, and he saved me.<verse eid="PSA 116:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 116:7"/>My soul can return to its resting place, for Yahweh has been good to me.<verse eid="PSA 116:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 116:8"/>For you rescued my life from death, my eyes from tears, and my feet from stumbling.<verse eid="PSA 116:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 116:9"/>I will walk before Yahweh in the land of the living.<verse eid="PSA 116:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 116:10"/>I believed in him, even when I said, “I am greatly afflicted.”<verse eid="PSA 116:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 116:11"/>In my confusion I said, “All men are liars.”<verse eid="PSA 116:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 116:12"/>How can I repay Yahweh for all his kindnesses to me?<verse eid="PSA 116:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 116:13"/>I will raise the cup of salvation, and call on the name of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 116:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 116:14"/>I will fulfill my vows to Yahweh now in the presence of all his people.<verse eid="PSA 116:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 116:15"/>Precious in the sight of Yahweh is the death of his faithful ones.<verse eid="PSA 116:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 116:16"/>Yahweh, indeed, I am your servant; I am your servant, the son of your servant woman; you have taken away my bonds.<verse eid="PSA 116:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 116:17"/>I will offer to you the sacrifice of thanksgiving and will call on the name of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 116:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 116:18"/>I will fulfill my vows to Yahweh now in the presence of all his people,<verse eid="PSA 116:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 116:19"/>in the courts of Yahweh’s house, in your midst, Jerusalem. Praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 116:19"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 116"/>
<chapter number="117" style="c" sid="PSA 117"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 117:1"/>Praise Yahweh, all you nations; exalt him, all you peoples.<verse eid="PSA 117:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 117:2"/>For his covenant faithfulness is great toward us, and the trustworthiness of Yahweh endures forever. Praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 117:2"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 117"/>
<chapter number="118" style="c" sid="PSA 118"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 118:1"/>Give thanks to Yahweh, for he is good, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 118:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 118:2"/>Let Israel now say, “His covenant faithfulness endures forever.”<verse eid="PSA 118:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 118:3"/>Let the house of Aaron now say, “His covenant faithfulness endures forever.”<verse eid="PSA 118:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 118:4"/>Let the loyal followers of Yahweh say, “His covenant faithfulness endures for ever.”<verse eid="PSA 118:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 118:5"/>In my distress I called out to Yahweh; Yahweh answered me and set me free.<verse eid="PSA 118:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 118:6"/>Yahweh is with me; I will not be afraid; what can man do to me?<verse eid="PSA 118:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 118:7"/>Yahweh is on my side as my helper; I will look in triumph on those who hate me.<verse eid="PSA 118:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 118:8"/>It is better to take shelter in Yahweh than to put confidence in man.<verse eid="PSA 118:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 118:9"/>It is better to take refuge in Yahweh than to put one’s trust in a princes.<verse eid="PSA 118:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 118:10"/>All the nations surrounded me; in Yahweh’s name I cut them off.<verse eid="PSA 118:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 118:11"/>They surrounded me; yes, they surrounded me; in Yahweh’s name I cut them off.<verse eid="PSA 118:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 118:12"/>They surrounded me like bees; they disappeared as quickly as fire among thorns; in Yahweh’s name I cut them off.<verse eid="PSA 118:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 118:13"/>They attacked me to knock me down, but Yahweh helped me.<verse eid="PSA 118:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 118:14"/>Yahweh is my strength and song, and he is the one who rescues me.<verse eid="PSA 118:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 118:15"/>The joyful shout of victory is heard in the tents of the righteous; the right hand of Yahweh does valiantly.<verse eid="PSA 118:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 118:16"/>The right hand of Yahweh is exalted; the right hand of Yahweh does valiantly.<verse eid="PSA 118:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 118:17"/>I will not die, but live and declare the deeds of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 118:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 118:18"/>Yahweh has punished me harshly; but he has not handed me over to death.<verse eid="PSA 118:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 118:19"/>Open to me the gates of righteousness; I will enter them and I will give thanks to Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 118:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 118:20"/>This is the gate of Yahweh; the righteous enter through it.<verse eid="PSA 118:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 118:21"/>I will give thanks to you, for you answered me, and you have become my salvation.<verse eid="PSA 118:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 118:22"/>The stone that the builders rejected has become the chief cornerstone.<verse eid="PSA 118:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 118:23"/>This is Yahweh’s doing; it is marvelous in our eyes.<verse eid="PSA 118:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 118:24"/>This is the day on which Yahweh has acted; we will rejoice and be glad in it.<verse eid="PSA 118:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 118:25"/>Please, Yahweh, give us victory! Please, Yahweh, send now success!<verse eid="PSA 118:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 118:26"/>Blessed is he who comes in the name of Yahweh; we bless you from the house of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 118:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 118:27"/>Yahweh is God, and he has given us light; bind the sacrifice with cords to the horns of the altar.<verse eid="PSA 118:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 118:28"/>You are my God, and I will give thanks to you; you are my God; I will exalt you.<verse eid="PSA 118:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 118:29"/>Oh, give thanks to Yahweh; for he is good; for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 118:29"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 118"/>
<chapter number="119" style="c" sid="PSA 119"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 119:1"/>Blessed are those whose ways are blameless, who walk in the teaching of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 119:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 119:2"/>Blessed are they who keep his testimonies, who seek him with all their heart.<verse eid="PSA 119:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 119:3"/>Surely they do not practice injustice; they walk in his ways.<verse eid="PSA 119:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 119:4"/>You have commanded your instructions so that we should carefully observe them.<verse eid="PSA 119:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 119:5"/>Oh, that my path would be firmly established, keeping your statutes!<verse eid="PSA 119:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 119:6"/>Then I would not be ashamed when I look to all of your commandments.<verse eid="PSA 119:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 119:7"/>I will give thanks to you with an upright heart when I learn the judgments of your righteousness.<verse eid="PSA 119:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 119:8"/>I will keep your statutes; do not utterly leave me.<verse eid="PSA 119:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 119:9"/>How can a young man keep his path pure? By keeping your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 119:10"/>With my whole heart I seek you; Do not let me stray from your commandments.<verse eid="PSA 119:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 119:11"/>I have hidden your word in my heart so that I might not sin against you.<verse eid="PSA 119:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 119:12"/>Blessed you are, Yahweh; teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 119:13"/>With my lips I have announced all the judgments of your mouth.<verse eid="PSA 119:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 119:14"/>I rejoice in the way of your testimonies more than in all riches.<verse eid="PSA 119:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 119:15"/>I will meditate on your instructions and I will consider your paths.<verse eid="PSA 119:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 119:16"/>I delight in your statutes; I will not forget your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 119:17"/>Deal kindly with your servant so that I may live and keep your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 119:18"/>Uncover my eyes so that I may gaze on the marvelous works from your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 119:19"/>I am a foreigner in the land; do not hide your commandments from me.<verse eid="PSA 119:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 119:20"/>My inner being is crushed with longing for your judgments at all times.<verse eid="PSA 119:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 119:21"/>You rebuke the proud, who are cursed, who wander from your commandments.<verse eid="PSA 119:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 119:22"/>Spare me from disgrace and humiliation, for I have kept your testimonies.<verse eid="PSA 119:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 119:23"/>Even though rulers sit against me and slander, your servant meditates on your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 119:24"/>Also, your testimonies are my pleasure. They are my counselors.<verse eid="PSA 119:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 119:25"/>My inner being clings to the dust! Give me life according to your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 119:26"/>I recounted my ways, and you answered me. Teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:26"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="27" style="v" sid="PSA 119:27"/>Make me understand the way of your instructions, so that I can meditate on your wondrous works.<verse eid="PSA 119:27"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="28" style="v" sid="PSA 119:28"/>My inner being melts away from grief Lift me up by your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:28"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="29" style="v" sid="PSA 119:29"/>Turn from me the path of deceit; graciously give me your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:29"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="30" style="v" sid="PSA 119:30"/>I have chosen the way of faithfulness; I have desired your judgments.<verse eid="PSA 119:30"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="31" style="v" sid="PSA 119:31"/>I cling to your testimonies; Yahweh, do not let me be shamed.<verse eid="PSA 119:31"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="32" style="v" sid="PSA 119:32"/>I run in the way of your commandments, for you enlarge my heart.<verse eid="PSA 119:32"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="33" style="v" sid="PSA 119:33"/>Teach me, Yahweh, the way of your statutes, and I will keep it to the end.<verse eid="PSA 119:33"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="34" style="v" sid="PSA 119:34"/>Give me understanding, and I will keep your teaching; I will observe it with all my heart.<verse eid="PSA 119:34"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="35" style="v" sid="PSA 119:35"/>Guide me in the way of your commandments, for I delight in it.<verse eid="PSA 119:35"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="36" style="v" sid="PSA 119:36"/>Incline my heart toward your testimonies and not toward unrighteous gain.<verse eid="PSA 119:36"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="37" style="v" sid="PSA 119:37"/>Turn away my eyes from looking at worthless things; in your ways, revive me.<verse eid="PSA 119:37"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="38" style="v" sid="PSA 119:38"/>Fulfill for your servant your promises. that he may fear you.<verse eid="PSA 119:38"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="39" style="v" sid="PSA 119:39"/>Turn away the reproach that I dread, for your judgments are good.<verse eid="PSA 119:39"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="40" style="v" sid="PSA 119:40"/>Look, I long for your precepts; in your righteousness, revive me.<verse eid="PSA 119:40"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="41" style="v" sid="PSA 119:41"/>May your steadfast love come, oh Yahweh— your salvation, according to your promise;<verse eid="PSA 119:41"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="42" style="v" sid="PSA 119:42"/>then I will answer the one who mocks me with a word, for I trust in your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:42"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="43" style="v" sid="PSA 119:43"/>Do not utterly take the word of truth from my mouth, for I hope in your judgments.<verse eid="PSA 119:43"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="44" style="v" sid="PSA 119:44"/>I will observe your teaching continually, forever and ever.<verse eid="PSA 119:44"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="45" style="v" sid="PSA 119:45"/>I will walk in a broad path, for I seek your precepts.<verse eid="PSA 119:45"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="46" style="v" sid="PSA 119:46"/>I will speak of your testimonies before kings, and I will not be ashamed.<verse eid="PSA 119:46"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="47" style="v" sid="PSA 119:47"/>I delight in your commandments, which I love.<verse eid="PSA 119:47"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="48" style="v" sid="PSA 119:48"/>I will lift up my hands to your commandments, which I love; I will meditate on your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:48"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="49" style="v" sid="PSA 119:49"/>Remember your word to your servant because you have given me hope.<verse eid="PSA 119:49"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="50" style="v" sid="PSA 119:50"/>This is my comfort in my affliction: that your promise keeps me alive.<verse eid="PSA 119:50"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="51" style="v" sid="PSA 119:51"/>The proud utterly scoff at me, from your teaching I do not turned aside.<verse eid="PSA 119:51"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="52" style="v" sid="PSA 119:52"/>I remember your judgments from ancient times, Yahweh, and I comfort myself.<verse eid="PSA 119:52"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="53" style="v" sid="PSA 119:53"/>Hot anger has seized me because of the wicked who reject your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:53"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="54" style="v" sid="PSA 119:54"/>Your statutes are songs for me in the house where I temporarily live.<verse eid="PSA 119:54"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="55" style="v" sid="PSA 119:55"/>I remember your name during the night, Yahweh, and I observe your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:55"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="56" style="v" sid="PSA 119:56"/>This is for me because I keep your precepts.<verse eid="PSA 119:56"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="57" style="v" sid="PSA 119:57"/>Yahweh is my portion; I promise to observe your words.<verse eid="PSA 119:57"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="58" style="v" sid="PSA 119:58"/>I entreat your favor with my whole heart; be merciful to me according to your promises.<verse eid="PSA 119:58"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="59" style="v" sid="PSA 119:59"/>I examine my ways and turn my feet to your testimonies.<verse eid="PSA 119:59"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="60" style="v" sid="PSA 119:60"/>I hurry and do not delay to observe your commandments.<verse eid="PSA 119:60"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="61" style="v" sid="PSA 119:61"/>The cords of the wicked ensnare me; I do not forget your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:61"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="62" style="v" sid="PSA 119:62"/>In the middle of the night I rise to bring praise to you because of the judgments of your righteousness.<verse eid="PSA 119:62"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="63" style="v" sid="PSA 119:63"/>I am a companion to all who fear you, and observe your precepts.<verse eid="PSA 119:63"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="64" style="v" sid="PSA 119:64"/>The earth is full of your steadfast love, Yahweh; teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:64"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="65" style="v" sid="PSA 119:65"/>You do good to your servant, Yahweh, according to your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:65"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="66" style="v" sid="PSA 119:66"/>Teach me good discernment and understanding, for I trust in your commandments.<verse eid="PSA 119:66"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="67" style="v" sid="PSA 119:67"/>Before I was afflicted I went astray, but now I observe your promises.<verse eid="PSA 119:67"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="68" style="v" sid="PSA 119:68"/>You are good, and you do good. Teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:68"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="69" style="v" sid="PSA 119:69"/>The arrogant smear me with lies, but I myself keep your precepts with my whole heart.<verse eid="PSA 119:69"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="70" style="v" sid="PSA 119:70"/>Their hearts are unfeeling like fat, but I myself delight in your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:70"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="71" style="v" sid="PSA 119:71"/>It is good for me that I have suffered so that I would learn your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:71"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="72" style="v" sid="PSA 119:72"/>The teaching of your mouth is good to me, more than thousands of pieces of gold and silver.<verse eid="PSA 119:72"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="73" style="v" sid="PSA 119:73"/>Your hands have made me and fashioned me; give me understanding so that I may learn your commandments.<verse eid="PSA 119:73"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="74" style="v" sid="PSA 119:74"/>May those who fear you see me and rejoice because I hope in your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:74"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="75" style="v" sid="PSA 119:75"/>Yahweh, I know that your judgments are just, and in faithfulness you humble me.<verse eid="PSA 119:75"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="76" style="v" sid="PSA 119:76"/>Let your steadfast love be my comfort, just as your promises to your servant.<verse eid="PSA 119:76"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="77" style="v" sid="PSA 119:77"/>May your grace come to me so that I may live, for your teaching is my delight.<verse eid="PSA 119:77"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="78" style="v" sid="PSA 119:78"/>Let the proud be put to shame, for they have accused me falsely; but as for me, I will meditate on your precepts.<verse eid="PSA 119:78"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="79" style="v" sid="PSA 119:79"/>May those who fear you turn to me, also those who know your testimonies.<verse eid="PSA 119:79"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="80" style="v" sid="PSA 119:80"/>May my heart be blameless with respect to your statutes, so that I may not be put to shame.<verse eid="PSA 119:80"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="81" style="v" sid="PSA 119:81"/>My inner being faints with longing for your salvation! I hope for your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:81"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="82" style="v" sid="PSA 119:82"/>My eyes faint with longing for your promise; saying, "When will you comfort me?"<verse eid="PSA 119:82"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="83" style="v" sid="PSA 119:83"/>For I have become like a wineskin in the smoke; I do not forget your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:83"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="84" style="v" sid="PSA 119:84"/>How long must your servant endure this; when will you act in pursuit of justice for me?<verse eid="PSA 119:84"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="85" style="v" sid="PSA 119:85"/>The proud have dug pits for me, which is not according to your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:85"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="86" style="v" sid="PSA 119:86"/>All your commandments are true; they pursue me deceifully; help me.<verse eid="PSA 119:86"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="87" style="v" sid="PSA 119:87"/>They have almost made an end to me in the land, but as for me, I do not reject your instructions.<verse eid="PSA 119:87"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="88" style="v" sid="PSA 119:88"/>According to your steadfast love, keep me alive, so that I may observe the testimonies of your mouth.<verse eid="PSA 119:88"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="89" style="v" sid="PSA 119:89"/>Forever, Yahweh, your word stands in the heavens.<verse eid="PSA 119:89"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="90" style="v" sid="PSA 119:90"/>Your faithfulness lasts from generation to generation; you have established the earth, and it stands.<verse eid="PSA 119:90"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="91" style="v" sid="PSA 119:91"/>They stand for your judgments today, for all things are your servants.<verse eid="PSA 119:91"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="92" style="v" sid="PSA 119:92"/>If your teaching had not been my delight, then I would have perished in my affliction.<verse eid="PSA 119:92"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="93" style="v" sid="PSA 119:93"/>I will not forget your precepts forever, for through them you have preserved me alive.<verse eid="PSA 119:93"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="94" style="v" sid="PSA 119:94"/>I am yours; save me, for I seek your precepts.<verse eid="PSA 119:94"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="95" style="v" sid="PSA 119:95"/>The wicked wait for me in order to destroy me, but I seek to understand your testimonies.<verse eid="PSA 119:95"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="96" style="v" sid="PSA 119:96"/>I have seen an end for all perfection; your commandments are very broad.<verse eid="PSA 119:96"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="97" style="v" sid="PSA 119:97"/>Oh how I love your teaching! It is my meditation all day long.<verse eid="PSA 119:97"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="98" style="v" sid="PSA 119:98"/>Your commandments make me wiser than my enemies, for it is with me forever.<verse eid="PSA 119:98"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="99" style="v" sid="PSA 119:99"/>I have more understanding than all my teachers, for your testimonies are my meditation.<verse eid="PSA 119:99"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="100" style="v" sid="PSA 119:100"/>I understand more than the elders; for I have kept your precepts.<verse eid="PSA 119:100"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="101" style="v" sid="PSA 119:101"/>I have restrained my feet from every path of evil so that I might observe your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:101"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="102" style="v" sid="PSA 119:102"/>I have not turned aside from your judgments, for you alone have instructed me.<verse eid="PSA 119:102"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="103" style="v" sid="PSA 119:103"/>How sweet are your promises to my taste, yes, sweeter than honey to my mouth!<verse eid="PSA 119:103"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="104" style="v" sid="PSA 119:104"/>Through your precepts I gain understanding; therefore I hate every path of falsehood.<verse eid="PSA 119:104"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="105" style="v" sid="PSA 119:105"/>Your word is a lamp to my feet and a light for my path.<verse eid="PSA 119:105"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="106" style="v" sid="PSA 119:106"/>I have sworn and have confirmed it, that I will observe your righteous judgments.<verse eid="PSA 119:106"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="107" style="v" sid="PSA 119:107"/>I am very afflicted; keep me alive, Yahweh, according to your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:107"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="108" style="v" sid="PSA 119:108"/>Yahweh, please accept the freewill offerings of my mouth, and teach me your judgments.<verse eid="PSA 119:108"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="109" style="v" sid="PSA 119:109"/>My life is in my palm continually, yet I do not forget your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:109"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="110" style="v" sid="PSA 119:110"/>The wicked have set a snare for me, but I have not strayed from your precepts.<verse eid="PSA 119:110"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="111" style="v" sid="PSA 119:111"/>I claim your testimonies as my heritage forever, for they are the joy of my heart.<verse eid="PSA 119:111"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="112" style="v" sid="PSA 119:112"/>I incline my heart to do your statutes forever, to the end!<verse eid="PSA 119:112"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="113" style="v" sid="PSA 119:113"/>I hate double-minded people, but I love your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:113"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="114" style="v" sid="PSA 119:114"/>You are my hiding place and my shield; I hope in your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:114"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="115" style="v" sid="PSA 119:115"/>Get away from me, you evil doers, so that I may observe the commandments of my God.<verse eid="PSA 119:115"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="116" style="v" sid="PSA 119:116"/>Sustain me by your word so that I may live and do not make me ashamed of my expectation.<verse eid="PSA 119:116"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="117" style="v" sid="PSA 119:117"/>Sustain me, and I will be saved; And, I will gaze on your statutes continually.<verse eid="PSA 119:117"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="118" style="v" sid="PSA 119:118"/>You reject all those who stray from your statutes, for their deception is in vain.<verse eid="PSA 119:118"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="119" style="v" sid="PSA 119:119"/>You remove all the wicked of the earth like dross; therefore I love your testimonies.<verse eid="PSA 119:119"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="120" style="v" sid="PSA 119:120"/>My body trembles in fear of you, and I fear of your judgments.<verse eid="PSA 119:120"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="121" style="v" sid="PSA 119:121"/>I do justice and righteousness; do not abandon me to my oppressors.<verse eid="PSA 119:121"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="122" style="v" sid="PSA 119:122"/>Ensure goodness for your servant; do not let the proud oppress me.<verse eid="PSA 119:122"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="123" style="v" sid="PSA 119:123"/>My eyes faint for your salvation and for the promise of your righteousness.<verse eid="PSA 119:123"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="124" style="v" sid="PSA 119:124"/>Deal with your servant according to your steadfast love, and teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:124"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="125" style="v" sid="PSA 119:125"/>I am your servant; give me understanding so that I may know your testimonies.<verse eid="PSA 119:125"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="126" style="v" sid="PSA 119:126"/>It is time for Yahweh to act, they break your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:126"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="127" style="v" sid="PSA 119:127"/>Therefore, I love your commandments more than gold, more than fine gold.<verse eid="PSA 119:127"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="128" style="v" sid="PSA 119:128"/>Therefore I consider all your precepts to be right in everything. I hate every path of falsehood.<verse eid="PSA 119:128"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="129" style="v" sid="PSA 119:129"/>Your testimonies are wonderful. Therefore, I obey them.<verse eid="PSA 119:129"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="130" style="v" sid="PSA 119:130"/>The unfolding of your words gives light; it gives understanding to the untrained.<verse eid="PSA 119:130"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="131" style="v" sid="PSA 119:131"/>I open my mouth and pant, for I long for your commandments.<verse eid="PSA 119:131"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="132" style="v" sid="PSA 119:132"/>Turn to me and be gracious to me according to justice, to those who love your name.<verse eid="PSA 119:132"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="133" style="v" sid="PSA 119:133"/>Establish my footsteps in your promises; and do not let any iniquity rule over me.<verse eid="PSA 119:133"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="134" style="v" sid="PSA 119:134"/>Ransom me from the oppression of man so that I may observe your precepts.<verse eid="PSA 119:134"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="135" style="v" sid="PSA 119:135"/>Let your face shine on your servant, and teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:135"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="136" style="v" sid="PSA 119:136"/>Channels of water run down from my eyes because they do not observe your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:136"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="137" style="v" sid="PSA 119:137"/>You are righteous, Yahweh, and your judgments are upright.<verse eid="PSA 119:137"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="138" style="v" sid="PSA 119:138"/>You command your testimonies righteously and very faithfully.<verse eid="PSA 119:138"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="139" style="v" sid="PSA 119:139"/>My jealousy has destroyed me because my adversaries forget your words.<verse eid="PSA 119:139"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="140" style="v" sid="PSA 119:140"/>Your promise is well refined, and your servant loves it.<verse eid="PSA 119:140"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="141" style="v" sid="PSA 119:141"/>I am little and despised. I do not forget your instructions.<verse eid="PSA 119:141"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="142" style="v" sid="PSA 119:142"/>Your righteousness is right forever, and your instruction is true.<verse eid="PSA 119:142"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="143" style="v" sid="PSA 119:143"/>Distress and anguish have found me. your commandments are my delight.<verse eid="PSA 119:143"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="144" style="v" sid="PSA 119:144"/>Your testimonies are righteous forever; give me understanding that I may live.<verse eid="PSA 119:144"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="145" style="v" sid="PSA 119:145"/>I cried out with my whole heart, “Answer me, Yahweh, I will keep your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:145"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="146" style="v" sid="PSA 119:146"/>I call to you; save me, so that I may observe your testimonies.<verse eid="PSA 119:146"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="147" style="v" sid="PSA 119:147"/>I rise before the dawn and cry for help. I hope in your words.<verse eid="PSA 119:147"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="148" style="v" sid="PSA 119:148"/>My eyes are open during the night watches in order to meditate on your promise.<verse eid="PSA 119:148"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="149" style="v" sid="PSA 119:149"/>Hear my voice according to your steadfast love; Yahweh, according to your judgment preserve my life.<verse eid="PSA 119:149"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="150" style="v" sid="PSA 119:150"/>Those pursuing wickedness are coming near. They wander far from your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:150"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="151" style="v" sid="PSA 119:151"/>You are near, Yahweh, and all your commandments are true.<verse eid="PSA 119:151"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="152" style="v" sid="PSA 119:152"/>Long ago I learned from your testimonies that you had established them forever.<verse eid="PSA 119:152"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="153" style="v" sid="PSA 119:153"/>Look on my affliction and rescue me, for I do not forget your teaching.<verse eid="PSA 119:153"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="154" style="v" sid="PSA 119:154"/>Plead my cause and redeem me; preserve me for your promise.<verse eid="PSA 119:154"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="155" style="v" sid="PSA 119:155"/>Salvation is far from the wicked, for they do not pursue your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:155"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="156" style="v" sid="PSA 119:156"/>Your mercies are many, Yahweh; according to your judgments, preserve me.<verse eid="PSA 119:156"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="157" style="v" sid="PSA 119:157"/>My pursuers and my adversaries are many; from your testimonies I have not turned.<verse eid="PSA 119:157"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="158" style="v" sid="PSA 119:158"/>I see the treacherous and I despise it because they do not observe your promise.<verse eid="PSA 119:158"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="159" style="v" sid="PSA 119:159"/>See that I love your precepts; Yahweh, according to your steadfast love, preserve me.<verse eid="PSA 119:159"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="160" style="v" sid="PSA 119:160"/>The head of your word is truth, and all of your righteous judgments lasts forever.<verse eid="PSA 119:160"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="161" style="v" sid="PSA 119:161"/>Commanders pursue me without cause, but from your word my heart trembles<verse eid="PSA 119:161"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="162" style="v" sid="PSA 119:162"/>I rejoice on account of your promise, like one who finds great plunder.<verse eid="PSA 119:162"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="163" style="v" sid="PSA 119:163"/>I hate falsehood, and I loathe it. I love your instruction.<verse eid="PSA 119:163"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="164" style="v" sid="PSA 119:164"/>Seven times in a day I praise you on account of your righteous judgments.<verse eid="PSA 119:164"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="165" style="v" sid="PSA 119:165"/>Great peace is for those who love your instruction; there is no stumbling for them.<verse eid="PSA 119:165"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="166" style="v" sid="PSA 119:166"/>I wait for your salvation, Yahweh, and I do your commandments.<verse eid="PSA 119:166"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="167" style="v" sid="PSA 119:167"/>My life keeps your testimonies, and I love them greatly.<verse eid="PSA 119:167"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="168" style="v" sid="PSA 119:168"/>I keep your precepts and your testimonies, for all my ways are before you.<verse eid="PSA 119:168"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="169" style="v" sid="PSA 119:169"/>My plea comes near to your face, Yahweh; give me understanding into your word.<verse eid="PSA 119:169"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="170" style="v" sid="PSA 119:170"/>May my supplication come before your face; according to your promise, rescue me.<verse eid="PSA 119:170"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="171" style="v" sid="PSA 119:171"/>May my lips pour out praise, for you teach me your statutes.<verse eid="PSA 119:171"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="172" style="v" sid="PSA 119:172"/>Let my tongue sing about your promise, for all your commandments are right.<verse eid="PSA 119:172"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="173" style="v" sid="PSA 119:173"/>Let your hand be for my help, for I have chosen your precepts.<verse eid="PSA 119:173"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="174" style="v" sid="PSA 119:174"/>I long for your salvation, Yahweh, and your teaching is my delight.<verse eid="PSA 119:174"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="175" style="v" sid="PSA 119:175"/>May I live and praise you, and may your judgments help me.<verse eid="PSA 119:175"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="176" style="v" sid="PSA 119:176"/>I have wandered off like a lost sheep; seek your servant, for I have not forgotten your commandments.”<verse eid="PSA 119:176"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 119"/>
<chapter number="120" style="c" sid="PSA 120"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 120:1"/>A song of ascents. To Yahweh in my distress I called, and he answered me.<verse eid="PSA 120:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 120:2"/>Rescue my life, Yahweh, from a lip of falsehood, from a tongue of deceit.<verse eid="PSA 120:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 120:3"/>What will he give to you, and what will he add to you, tongue of deceit?<verse eid="PSA 120:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 120:4"/>Sharpened arrows of a warrior, along with burning coals of a broom tree.<verse eid="PSA 120:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 120:5"/>Woe to me, for I sojourned in Meshech, I dwelled among the tents of Kedar.<verse eid="PSA 120:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 120:6"/>My life has dwelt for a long time with haters of peace.<verse eid="PSA 120:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 120:7"/>I {am for} peace, but when I speak, they {are} for war.<verse eid="PSA 120:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 120"/>
<chapter number="121" style="c" sid="PSA 121"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 121:1"/>A song of ascents. I lift up my eyes to the mountains, From where does my help come?<verse eid="PSA 121:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 121:2"/>My help is from with Yahweh, who made heaven and earth.<verse eid="PSA 121:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 121:3"/>May he not appoint your foot for slipping. May the one who protects you not slumber.<verse eid="PSA 121:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 121:4"/>Behold, the one who guards Israel will never slumber and will never sleep.<verse eid="PSA 121:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 121:5"/>Yahweh is the one who guards you. Yahweh is your shade at your right hand.<verse eid="PSA 121:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 121:6"/>The sun will not harm you daily, nor the moon during the night.<verse eid="PSA 121:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 121:7"/>Yahweh will protect you from all harm, he will protect your life.<verse eid="PSA 121:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 121:8"/>Yahweh will protect your going and your coming from now and until forever.<verse eid="PSA 121:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 121"/>
<chapter number="122" style="c" sid="PSA 122"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 122:1"/>A song of ascents, of David. I rejoiced when they said to me, “Let us go to the house of Yahweh.”<verse eid="PSA 122:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 122:2"/>Jerusalem, our feet are standing within your gates!<verse eid="PSA 122:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 122:3"/>Jerusalem, which is built as a city bound together,<verse eid="PSA 122:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 122:4"/>which is where the tribes went up to, the tribes of Yah, {because of} the testimony to Israel to give thanks to the name of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 122:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 122:5"/>For there thrones of judgment remained, thrones of the house of David.<verse eid="PSA 122:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 122:6"/>Pray for the peace of Jerusalem! May those who love you have peace.<verse eid="PSA 122:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 122:7"/>May there be peace within your walls, peace within your fortresses.<verse eid="PSA 122:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 122:8"/>For the sake of my brothers and my friends I will say, “May there be peace within you.”<verse eid="PSA 122:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 122:9"/>For the sake of the house of Yahweh our God I will seek your good.<verse eid="PSA 122:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 122"/>
<chapter number="123" style="c" sid="PSA 123"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 123:1"/>A song of ascents. A Song of Ascents To you I lift up my eyes, you who are enthroned in the heavens.<verse eid="PSA 123:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 123:2"/>See, as the eyes of servants look to their master’s hand, as the eyes of a maid look to her mistress’s hand, so our eyes look to Yahweh our God until he has mercy on us.<verse eid="PSA 123:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 123:3"/>Have mercy on us, Yahweh, have mercy on us, for we are exceedingly filled with humiliation.<verse eid="PSA 123:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 123:4"/>We are more than full of the scoffing of the insolent and with the contempt of the proud.<verse eid="PSA 123:4"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 123"/>
<chapter number="124" style="c" sid="PSA 124"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 124:1"/>A song of ascents; of David. A Song of Ascents of David “If Yahweh had not been on our side,” let Israel say now,<verse eid="PSA 124:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 124:2"/>“if it had not been Yahweh who was on our side when men rose up against us,<verse eid="PSA 124:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 124:3"/>then they would have swallowed us up alive when their anger raged against us.<verse eid="PSA 124:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 124:4"/>Then the water would have swept us away; the torrent would have gone over us.<verse eid="PSA 124:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 124:5"/>Then the raging waters would have gone over us.”<verse eid="PSA 124:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 124:6"/>Blessed be Yahweh, who has not allowed us to be torn by their teeth.<verse eid="PSA 124:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 124:7"/>We have escaped like a bird out of the snare of the fowlers; the snare has been broken, and we have escaped.<verse eid="PSA 124:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 124:8"/>Our help is in the name of Yahweh, who made heaven and earth.<verse eid="PSA 124:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 124"/>
<chapter number="125" style="c" sid="PSA 125"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 125:1"/>A song of ascents. A Song of Ascents Those who trust in Yahweh are like Mount Zion, which cannot be shaken, forever enduring.<verse eid="PSA 125:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 125:2"/>As the mountains surround Jerusalem, so the Lord surrounds his people now and forever.<verse eid="PSA 125:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 125:3"/>The scepter of wickedness must not rest on the land alloted to the righteous. Otherwise the righteous might reach out their hands to do what is wrong.<verse eid="PSA 125:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 125:4"/>Do good, Yahweh, to those who are good and to those who are upright in their hearts.<verse eid="PSA 125:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 125:5"/>But as for those who turn aside to their crooked ways, Yahweh will lead them away with those who do evil. May peace be on Israel.<verse eid="PSA 125:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 125"/>
<chapter number="126" style="c" sid="PSA 126"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 126:1"/>A song of ascents. A Song of Ascents When Yahweh restored the fortunes of Zion, we were like those who dream.<verse eid="PSA 126:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 126:2"/>Then our mouths were filled with laughter and our tongues with singing. Then they said among the nations, “Yahweh has done great things for them.”<verse eid="PSA 126:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 126:3"/>Yahweh did great things for us; how glad we were!<verse eid="PSA 126:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 126:4"/>Restore our fortunes, Yahweh, like the streams in the Negev.<verse eid="PSA 126:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 126:5"/>Those who sow in tears will reap with shouts of joy.<verse eid="PSA 126:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 126:6"/>He who goes out weeping, carrying seed for sowing, will return again with shouts of joy, bringing his bundles of grain with him.<verse eid="PSA 126:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 126"/>
<chapter number="127" style="c" sid="PSA 127"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 127:1"/>A song of ascents, of Solomon. A Song of Ascents of Solomon If Yahweh is not the builder of the house, they work uselessly, those who build it. If it is not Yahweh who guards the city, the watchman stands guard uselessly.<verse eid="PSA 127:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 127:2"/>It is useless for you to rise up early, to come home late, or to eat the bread of hard work, for Yahweh provides for his beloved as they sleep.<verse eid="PSA 127:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 127:3"/>See, children are a heritage from Yahweh, and the fruit of the womb is a reward.<verse eid="PSA 127:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 127:4"/>Like arrows in the hand of a warrior, so are the children of one’s youth.<verse eid="PSA 127:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 127:5"/>How blessed is the man that has his quiver full of them. He will not be put to shame when he confronts his enemies in the gate.<verse eid="PSA 127:5"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 127"/>
<chapter number="128" style="c" sid="PSA 128"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 128:1"/>A song of ascents. A Song of Ascents Blessed is everyone who honors Yahweh, who walks in his ways.<verse eid="PSA 128:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 128:2"/>When you eat the labor of your hands, you will enjoy; you will be blessed and prosper.<verse eid="PSA 128:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 128:3"/>Your wife will be like a fruitful vine in your house; your children will be like olive plants as they sit around your table.<verse eid="PSA 128:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 128:4"/>Yes, indeed, the man will be blessed who honors Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 128:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 128:5"/>May Yahweh bless you from Zion; may you see the prosperity of Jerusalem all the days of your life.<verse eid="PSA 128:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 128:6"/>May you live to see your children’s children. May peace be on Israel.<verse eid="PSA 128:6"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 128"/>
<chapter number="129" style="c" sid="PSA 129"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 129:1"/>A song of ascents. A Song of Ascents “Often since my youth they have attacked me,” let Israel say.<verse eid="PSA 129:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 129:2"/>“Often since my youth they have attacked me, yet they have not defeated me.<verse eid="PSA 129:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 129:3"/>The plowers plowed on my back; they made their furrows long.<verse eid="PSA 129:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 129:4"/>Yahweh is righteous; he has cut the ropes of the wicked.”<verse eid="PSA 129:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 129:5"/>May they all be put to shame and turned back, those who hate Zion.<verse eid="PSA 129:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 129:6"/>May they be like the grass on the housetops that withers before it grows up,<verse eid="PSA 129:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 129:7"/>that cannot fill the reaper’s hand or the chest of the one who binds bundles of grain together.<verse eid="PSA 129:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 129:8"/>May those who pass by not say, “May the blessing of Yahweh be on you; we bless you in the name of Yahweh.”<verse eid="PSA 129:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 129"/>
<chapter number="130" style="c" sid="PSA 130"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 130:1"/>A song of ascents. A Song of Ascents Out of the depths I cry to you, Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 130:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 130:2"/>Lord, hear my voice; let your ears be attentive to my pleas for mercy.<verse eid="PSA 130:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 130:3"/>If you, Yahweh, would mark iniquities, Lord, who could stand?<verse eid="PSA 130:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 130:4"/>But there is forgiveness with you, that you may be revered.<verse eid="PSA 130:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 130:5"/>I wait for Yahweh, my soul waits, and in his word I hope.<verse eid="PSA 130:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 130:6"/>My soul waits for the Lord more than watchmen wait for the morning.<verse eid="PSA 130:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 130:7"/>Israel, hope in Yahweh. Yahweh is merciful, for with Yahweh is abundant redemption.<verse eid="PSA 130:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 130:8"/>It is he who will redeem Israel from all his sins.<verse eid="PSA 130:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 130"/>
<chapter number="131" style="c" sid="PSA 131"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 131:1"/>A song of ascents; of David. [A Song of the Ascents, of David] Yahweh, my heart does not boast nor do my eyes look too high, nor do I walk in great and marvelous things beyond me.<verse eid="PSA 131:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 131:2"/>Have I not stilled and quieted my inner being like a weaned child with his mother, my inner being within me is like a weaned child.<verse eid="PSA 131:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 131:3"/>Israel, hope in Yahweh from now on and forevermore.<verse eid="PSA 131:3"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 131"/>
<chapter number="132" style="c" sid="PSA 132"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 132:1"/>A song of ascents. A Song of Ascents Yahweh, for David’s sake, remember all his afflictions.<verse eid="PSA 132:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 132:2"/>how he swore to Yahweh, how he vowed to the Mighty One of Jacob.<verse eid="PSA 132:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 132:3"/>Surely I will not enter the tent of my house nor go up to the spread of my bed,<verse eid="PSA 132:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 132:4"/>Nor will I give sleep to my eyes or rest to my eyelids<verse eid="PSA 132:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 132:5"/>until I find a place for Yahweh, a tabernacle for the Mighty One of Jacob.”<verse eid="PSA 132:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 132:6"/>Look, we heard about it in Ephrathah; we found it in the fields of Jaar.<verse eid="PSA 132:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 132:7"/>We will go into his tabernacle; we will worship at the footstool of his feet.<verse eid="PSA 132:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 132:8"/>Arise, Yahweh, to your resting place, you and the ark of your strength!<verse eid="PSA 132:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 132:9"/>May your priests be clothed with righteousness; may your faithful ones shout for joy.<verse eid="PSA 132:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 132:10"/>For your servant David’s sake, do not turn away from the face of your anointed one.<verse eid="PSA 132:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 132:11"/>Yahweh swore a sure oath to David, he will not turn from it: “From the fruit of your belly I will set on your throne.<verse eid="PSA 132:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 132:12"/>If your sons keep my covenant and the laws that I will teach them, their children also will sit on your throne forevermore.”<verse eid="PSA 132:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 132:13"/>For Yahweh has chosen Zion, he has desired her as a dwelling for him.<verse eid="PSA 132:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 132:14"/>“This is my resting place forever. I will dwell here, for I desire her.<verse eid="PSA 132:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 132:15"/>With wild game I will abundantly bless her. I will satisfy her poor with bread.<verse eid="PSA 132:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 132:16"/>I will clothe her priests with salvation, her faithful ones will shout aloud for joy.<verse eid="PSA 132:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 132:17"/>There I will make a horn to sprout for David and set up a lamp for my anointed one.<verse eid="PSA 132:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 132:18"/>I will clothe his enemies with shame, but on him his crown will shine.”<verse eid="PSA 132:18"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 132"/>
<chapter number="133" style="c" sid="PSA 133"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 133:1"/>A song of ascents, of David. [A Song of the Ascents, Of David] Behold, how good and how pleasant it is for brothers to live together!<verse eid="PSA 133:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 133:2"/>It is like fine oil on the head pouring down on the beard— Aaron’s beard, which pours down on the collar of his robes.<verse eid="PSA 133:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 133:3"/>It is like the dew of Hermon which falls on the mountains of Zion. For there Yahweh commanded the blessing— life forevermore.<verse eid="PSA 133:3"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 133"/>
<chapter number="134" style="c" sid="PSA 134"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 134:1"/>A song of ascents. A Song of the Ascents Behold, bless Yahweh, all you servants of Yahweh, you who stand in the night in the house of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 134:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 134:2"/>Lift up your hands to the holy place and bless Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 134:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 134:3"/>May Yahweh bless you from Zion, he who made heaven and earth.<verse eid="PSA 134:3"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 134"/>
<chapter number="135" style="c" sid="PSA 135"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 135:1"/>Praise Yahweh. Praise the name of Yahweh. Praise him, you servants of Yahweh,<verse eid="PSA 135:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 135:2"/>you who stand in the house of Yahweh, in the courtyards of the house of our God.<verse eid="PSA 135:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 135:3"/>Praise Yahweh, for Yahweh is good; sing praises to his name, for it is pleasant.<verse eid="PSA 135:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 135:4"/>For Yahweh has chosen Jacob for himself, Israel as his possession.<verse eid="PSA 135:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 135:5"/>For I myself know that Yahweh is great, and our Lord is greater than all other gods.<verse eid="PSA 135:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 135:6"/>All that Yahweh desires, he does in the heavens and on the earth, in the seas and all the ocean depths.<verse eid="PSA 135:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 135:7"/>Causing the clouds to rise from the end of the earth, he makes lightning accompany the rain and bringing the wind out of his storehouse.<verse eid="PSA 135:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 135:8"/>He struck the firstborn of Egypt, from man to beast.<verse eid="PSA 135:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 135:9"/>He sent signs and wonders into your midst, Egypt, against Pharaoh and all his servants.<verse eid="PSA 135:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 135:10"/>He struck many nations and killed mighty kings,<verse eid="PSA 135:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 135:11"/>Sihon king of the Amorites and Og king of Bashan and all the kingdoms of Canaan.<verse eid="PSA 135:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 135:12"/>And he gave their land as an inheritance, an inheritance to Israel his people.<verse eid="PSA 135:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 135:13"/>Your name, Yahweh, endures forever; your renown, Yahweh, endures from generation to generation.<verse eid="PSA 135:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 135:14"/>For Yahweh judges his people, and he shows compassion on his servants.<verse eid="PSA 135:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 135:15"/>The nations’ idols are silver and gold, the work of men’s hands.<verse eid="PSA 135:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 135:16"/>Those idols have mouths, but they do not speak; they have eyes, but they do not see;<verse eid="PSA 135:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 135:17"/>they have ears, but they do not hear, nor is there breath in their mouths.<verse eid="PSA 135:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 135:18"/>Those who make them are like them, as is everyone who trusts in them.<verse eid="PSA 135:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 135:19"/>House of Israel, bless Yahweh; house of Aaron, bless Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 135:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 135:20"/>House of Levi, bless Yahweh; you who fear Yahweh, bless Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 135:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 135:21"/>Blessed be Yahweh in Zion, he who lives in Jerusalem. Praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 135:21"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 135"/>
<chapter number="136" style="c" sid="PSA 136"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 136:1"/>Oh, give thanks to Yahweh; for he is good, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 136:2"/>Oh, give thanks to the God of gods, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 136:3"/>Oh, give thanks to the Lord of lords, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 136:4"/>To him who alone does great wonders, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 136:5"/>to him who by wisdom made the heavens, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 136:6"/>To him who spread out the earth above the waters, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 136:7"/>to him who made great lights, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 136:8"/>the sun to rule by day, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 136:9"/>the moon and stars to rule by night, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 136:10"/>to him who struck Egypt in their firstborn, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 136:11"/>and brought out Israel from among them, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 136:12"/>with a strong hand and a raised arm, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 136:13"/>to him who divided the Sea of Reeds into parts, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 136:14"/>and made Israel to pass through the middle of it, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 136:15"/>and threw down Pharaoh and his army in the Sea of Reeds, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 136:16"/>to him who led his people through the wilderness, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 136:17"/>to him who struck down great kings, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 136:18"/>to him who killed powerful kings, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 136:19"/>Sihon king of the Amorites, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 136:20"/>and Og king of Bashan, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 136:21"/>to him who gave their land as an inheritance, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 136:22"/>an inheritance to Israel his servant, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 136:23"/>who remembered us in our low estate, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 136:24"/>and he rescued us from our adversaries, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever—<verse eid="PSA 136:24"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="25" style="v" sid="PSA 136:25"/>giving bread to all flesh, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:25"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="26" style="v" sid="PSA 136:26"/>Oh, give thanks to the God of heaven, for his covenant faithfulness endures forever.<verse eid="PSA 136:26"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 136"/>
<chapter number="137" style="c" sid="PSA 137"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 137:1"/>Beside the rivers of Babylon there we sat and wept when we remembered Zion.<verse eid="PSA 137:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 137:2"/>On the poplars there we hung our harps.<verse eid="PSA 137:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 137:3"/>For there our captors demanded that we sing songs, and those who relentlessly mocked us said, “Sing to us from the songs of Zion.”<verse eid="PSA 137:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 137:4"/>How could we sing a song about Yahweh in a foreign land?<verse eid="PSA 137:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 137:5"/>If I forget you, Jerusalem, let my right hand forget<verse eid="PSA 137:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 137:6"/>Let my tongue cling to my palate if I do not remember you, if I do not lift up Jerusalem over my chief pleasure.<verse eid="PSA 137:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 137:7"/>Remember, Yahweh, the sons of Edom, on the day of Jerusalem, saying, “Tear it down, tear it down to its foundations.”<verse eid="PSA 137:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 137:8"/>Daughter of Babylon, who will be destroyed— blessed be the one who repays you for what you have done to us.<verse eid="PSA 137:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 137:9"/>Blessed be the one who seizes and dashes your little ones against the rocks.<verse eid="PSA 137:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 137"/>
<chapter number="138" style="c" sid="PSA 138"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 138:1"/>A psalm of David. Of David I will give you thanks with my whole heart; before the gods I will sing praises to you.<verse eid="PSA 138:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 138:2"/>I will bow down toward the temple of your holiness, and I will give thanks to your name for your covenant faithfulness and for your trustworthiness. For you have exalted above all things your name and your word.<verse eid="PSA 138:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 138:3"/>On the day that I called and you answered me; you emboldened my life with power.<verse eid="PSA 138:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 138:4"/>All the kings of the earth will give you thanks, Yahweh, for they will hear the words from your mouth.<verse eid="PSA 138:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 138:5"/>Indeed, they will sing of the ways of Yahweh, for great is the glory of Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 138:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 138:6"/>For though Yahweh is high, yet he sees the lowly, but the proud he knows from far off.<verse eid="PSA 138:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 138:7"/>Though I walk in the middle of danger, you will preserve my life; you will reach out with your hand against the anger of my enemies, and your right hand will save me.<verse eid="PSA 138:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 138:8"/>Yahweh is with me to the end; your covenant faithfulness, Yahweh, endures forever. Do not forsake the ones whom your hands have made.<verse eid="PSA 138:8"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 138"/>
<chapter number="139" style="c" sid="PSA 139"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 139:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. For the choir director, a psalm of David. Yahweh, you have examined me, and you know.<verse eid="PSA 139:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 139:2"/>You know when I sit and when I rise; you understand my thoughts from far away.<verse eid="PSA 139:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 139:3"/>You have measured my path and my resting places; and you are familiar with all my ways.<verse eid="PSA 139:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 139:4"/>For there is not a word on my tongue ..., See, you know it completely, Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 139:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 139:5"/>Behind and before you encircle me and you place your hand upon me.<verse eid="PSA 139:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 139:6"/>Such knowledge is too wonderful for me! it is high; I cannot reach it.<verse eid="PSA 139:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 139:7"/>Where can I go from your Spirit? Where can I flee from your presence?<verse eid="PSA 139:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 139:8"/>If I ascend up to the heavens, you are there; if I make my bed in Sheol, behold, you are there.<verse eid="PSA 139:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 139:9"/>If I rise on the wings of the morning or dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea,<verse eid="PSA 139:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 139:10"/>even there your hand will lead me, your right hand will hold on to me.<verse eid="PSA 139:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 139:11"/>If I said, “Surely the darkness will cover me, and the light will become night around me,”<verse eid="PSA 139:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 139:12"/>even the darkness would not be dark to you, and night would shine like the day. The darkness is like the light to you!<verse eid="PSA 139:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 139:13"/>For You created my inner parts; you wove me together in my mother’s womb.<verse eid="PSA 139:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 139:14"/>I will praise you because I am fearfully and wonderfully made. Your works are wonderful. My inner being knows this very well.<verse eid="PSA 139:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 139:15"/>My bones were not hidden from you when I was made in private, when I was woven together in the depths of the earth.<verse eid="PSA 139:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 139:16"/>Your eyes saw my unformed body; all the days formed for me were recorded in your book even before the first of them was.<verse eid="PSA 139:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 139:17"/>How precious are your thoughts to me, God! How vast is their sum!<verse eid="PSA 139:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 139:18"/>If I counted them, they would be more numberous than the sand. When I awake, I am still with you.<verse eid="PSA 139:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 139:19"/>If only you would kill the wicked, God; and you men of bloodshed, get away from me.<verse eid="PSA 139:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 139:20"/>For they speak against you with evil intent; your enemies abuse your character<verse eid="PSA 139:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 139:21"/>Do I not hate those, Yahweh, who hate you? Do I not despise those who rise up against you?<verse eid="PSA 139:21"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="22" style="v" sid="PSA 139:22"/>I hate them completely; they have become my enemies.<verse eid="PSA 139:22"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="23" style="v" sid="PSA 139:23"/>Examine me, God, and know my heart; test me and know my thoughts.<verse eid="PSA 139:23"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="24" style="v" sid="PSA 139:24"/>See if there is any wicked way in me, and lead me in the path of forever.<verse eid="PSA 139:24"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 139"/>
<chapter number="140" style="c" sid="PSA 140"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 140:1"/>For the chief musician. A psalm of David. Yahweh, rescue me from men of wickedness; preserve me from men of violence.<verse eid="PSA 140:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 140:2"/>For they plan evil in their hearts; they assemble for battles every day.<verse eid="PSA 140:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 140:3"/>Their tongues pierce like a serpent; vipers’ poison is on their lips. Selah<verse eid="PSA 140:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 140:4"/>Keep me from the hands of the wicked, Yahweh; preserve me from men of violence who plan to push down my step.<verse eid="PSA 140:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 140:5"/>The proud have set a trap for me; and with ropes they have spread a net by hand along the path; they have set snares for me. <verse eid="PSA 140:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 140:6"/>I said to Yahweh, “You are my God; Yahweh, give ear to my cries for mercy.”<verse eid="PSA 140:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 140:7"/>Yahweh, my Lord, you are the strength of my salvation; you shield my head in the day of battle.<verse eid="PSA 140:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 140:8"/>Yahweh, do not grant the desires of the wicked; do not promote their plots, they rise up <verse eid="PSA 140:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 140:9"/>Those who surround me raise their heads; let the mischief of their own lips cover them.<verse eid="PSA 140:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 140:10"/>Let burning coals fall on them; throw them into the fire, into bottomless pits, never again will they rise.<verse eid="PSA 140:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 140:11"/>May men of tongues not be established in the land; may evil hunt down the man of violence speedily.<verse eid="PSA 140:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 140:12"/>I know that Yahweh will act with favor for the poor, justice to the needy.<verse eid="PSA 140:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 140:13"/>Surely the righteous will praise your name; the upright will dwell before your face.<verse eid="PSA 140:13"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 140"/>
<chapter number="141" style="c" sid="PSA 141"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 141:1"/>A psalm of David. A song of David Yahweh, I called out to you, "Come quickly to me. Give ear to my voice when I call to you."<verse eid="PSA 141:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 141:2"/>May my prayer rise like incense to your face; may my lifted hands be like the evening sacrifice.<verse eid="PSA 141:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 141:3"/>Yahweh, place a guard over my mouth; guard the door of my lips.<verse eid="PSA 141:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 141:4"/>Do not let my heart bend toward any evil thing or participate in sinful activities with men who behave wickedly. May I not eat any of their delicacies.<verse eid="PSA 141:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 141:5"/>Let a righteous person hit me; it will be a kindness. Let him correct me; it will be like oil on my head. May my head not refuse. For my prayer is always against their wicked deeds.<verse eid="PSA 141:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 141:6"/>Their judges will stumble into the hands of craggy rocks; they will hear that my own words are pleasant.<verse eid="PSA 141:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 141:7"/>“As when one plows and breaks up the ground, so our bones have been scattered at the mouth of Sheol.”<verse eid="PSA 141:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 141:8"/>For my eyes are on you, Yahweh, Lord; in you I take refuge; do not abandon my life.<verse eid="PSA 141:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 141:9"/>Keep me from the hands of the snare that they have laid for me, from the traps of evildoers.<verse eid="PSA 141:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 141:10"/>Let the wicked fall into their own nets while I escape.<verse eid="PSA 141:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 141"/>
<chapter number="142" style="c" sid="PSA 142"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 142:1"/>A maschil of David, when he was in the cave; a prayer. With my voice I cry out to Yahweh; with my voice I plead to Yahweh for favor.<verse eid="PSA 142:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 142:2"/>I pour out my lament before him; I declare my troubles before him.<verse eid="PSA 142:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 142:3"/>When my spirit is weak within me, you yourself know my path. Along this path I walk they have hidden a trap for me.<verse eid="PSA 142:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 142:4"/>I look to my right and see that there is no one who cares for me. there is no refuge for me; no one looks after my life.<verse eid="PSA 142:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 142:5"/>I called out to you, Yahweh; I said, “You are my refuge, my portion in the land of the living.<verse eid="PSA 142:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 142:6"/>Listen to my cries, for I have been brought very low; rescue me from my pursuers, for they are stronger than I.<verse eid="PSA 142:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 142:7"/>Bring my life out of prison in order to praise your name. The righteous will gather around me because you have been good to me.”<verse eid="PSA 142:7"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 142"/>
<chapter number="143" style="c" sid="PSA 143"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 143:1"/>A psalm of David. A song of David Hear my prayer, Yahweh; listen to my pleas. On account of your faithfulness answer me in your righteousness!<verse eid="PSA 143:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 143:2"/>Do not enter into judgment with your servant, for no one living is righteous before you.<verse eid="PSA 143:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 143:3"/>For the enemy has pursued my being; he has crushed my life to the ground; he has made me to live in dark places like those dead a long time.<verse eid="PSA 143:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 143:4"/>My breath is faint in me; my heart despairs within me.<verse eid="PSA 143:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 143:5"/>I remember days from old; I meditate on all your works; I reflect on the works of your hands.<verse eid="PSA 143:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 143:6"/>I spread my hands out to you; my soul thirsts for you as in a parched land. <verse eid="PSA 143:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 143:7"/>Answer me quickly, Yahweh, because my spirit faints. Do not hide your face from me, or I will become like those who go down into the pit.<verse eid="PSA 143:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 143:8"/>Let me hear your covenant faithfulness in the morning, for I trust in you. Make known to me the way where I should walk, for I lift up my soul to you.<verse eid="PSA 143:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 143:9"/>Rescue me from my enemies, Yahweh; I hide in you.<verse eid="PSA 143:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 143:10"/>Teach me to do your good pleasures, for you are my God. May your spirit of goodness lead me in the land of uprightness.<verse eid="PSA 143:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 143:11"/>Yahweh, for the sake of your name, keep me alive; in your righteousness bring my life out of trouble.<verse eid="PSA 143:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 143:12"/>In your covenant faithfulness cut off my enemies and destroy all the enemies of my life, for I am your servant.<verse eid="PSA 143:12"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 143"/>
<chapter number="144" style="c" sid="PSA 144"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 144:1"/>A psalm of David. Of David. Blessed be Yahweh, my rock, who trains my hands for war and my fingers for battle.<verse eid="PSA 144:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 144:2"/>You are my steadfast love and my fortress, my high tower and the one who rescues me, my shield and the one in whom I take refuge, the one who subdues nations under me.<verse eid="PSA 144:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 144:3"/>Yahweh, what is man that you take notice of him, the son of man that you think about him?<verse eid="PSA 144:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 144:4"/>Man is like a breath; his days are like a passing shadow.<verse eid="PSA 144:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 144:5"/>Yahweh, cause your sky to spread wide and come down; touch the mountains and make them smoke.<verse eid="PSA 144:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 144:6"/>Shoot lightning and scatter them; send your bolts and disturb them.<verse eid="PSA 144:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 144:7"/>Reach out your hand from above, deliver me and rescue me out of many waters, from the hand of sons of foreigners.<verse eid="PSA 144:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 144:8"/>For their mouths speak lies, and their right hand is a right hand of falsehood.<verse eid="PSA 144:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 144:9"/>I will sing a new song to you, God; on a lute of ten strings I will play for you,<verse eid="PSA 144:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 144:10"/>who gives salvation to kings, who rescues David your servant from an evil sword.<verse eid="PSA 144:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 144:11"/>Rescue me and deliver me from the hand of sons of foreigners. For their mouths speak lies, and their right hand is a right hand of falsehood.<verse eid="PSA 144:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 144:12"/>May our sons be like plants who grow large in their youth and our daughters like carved corner pillars, resembling a palace.<verse eid="PSA 144:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 144:13"/>May our storehouses be full with every kind of produce, and may our sheep produce thousands and ten thousands in our fields.<verse eid="PSA 144:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 144:14"/>May our oxen have many young. No one will break through, no one will go out, and no one will cry in our streets.<verse eid="PSA 144:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 144:15"/>Blessed is the people for whom this is so; blessed is the people for whom Yahweh is his God.<verse eid="PSA 144:15"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 144"/>
<chapter number="145" style="c" sid="PSA 145"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 145:1"/>A psalm of praise. Of David. A song of David I will extol you, my God, the King; I will bless your name forever and ever.<verse eid="PSA 145:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 145:2"/>Every day will I bless you; I will praise your name forever and ever.<verse eid="PSA 145:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 145:3"/>Great is Yahweh and greatly to be praised; and his greatness cannot be measured.<verse eid="PSA 145:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 145:4"/>Generation to generation will rejoice because of your deeds and they will proclaim your mighty actions.<verse eid="PSA 145:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 145:5"/>On the glorious splendor of your majesty and on your marvelous deeds, I will meditate.<verse eid="PSA 145:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 145:6"/>They will speak of the power of your awesome works, and I will declare your greatness.<verse eid="PSA 145:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 145:7"/>They will celebrate the fame of your abounding goodness, and they will sing about your righteousness.<verse eid="PSA 145:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 145:8"/>Yahweh is gracious and merciful, slow to anger and great in steadfast love.<verse eid="PSA 145:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 145:9"/>Yahweh is good to all; and his abundant mercies are over all his works.<verse eid="PSA 145:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 145:10"/>All you have made will give thanks to you, Yahweh; your faithful ones will bless you.<verse eid="PSA 145:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 145:11"/>They will speak of the glory of your kingdom, and they will tell of your power.<verse eid="PSA 145:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 145:12"/>Making known to the children of mankind his mighty deeds and the glorious splendor of his kingdom.<verse eid="PSA 145:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 145:13"/>Your kingdom is an everlasting kingdom, and your dominion endures throughout all generations.<verse eid="PSA 145:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 145:14"/>Yahweh supports all who are falling and raises up all who are bent over.<verse eid="PSA 145:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 145:15"/>The eyes of all wait for you; you give them their food in its time.<verse eid="PSA 145:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 145:16"/>You open your hand and satisfy the desire of every living thing.<verse eid="PSA 145:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 145:17"/>Yahweh is righteous in all his ways and faithful in all he does.<verse eid="PSA 145:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 145:18"/>Yahweh is near to all who call to him, to all who call to him in truth.<verse eid="PSA 145:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 145:19"/>He does the desire of those who fear him, and he hears their cry and saves them.<verse eid="PSA 145:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 145:20"/>Yahweh keeps all those who love him, but he will destroy all the wicked.<verse eid="PSA 145:20"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="21" style="v" sid="PSA 145:21"/>My mouth speaks the praise of Yahweh; let all flesh bless his holy name forever and ever.<verse eid="PSA 145:21"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 145"/>
<chapter number="146" style="c" sid="PSA 146"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 146:1"/>Praise Yahweh. Praise Yahweh, my soul.<verse eid="PSA 146:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 146:2"/>I will praise Yahweh with my life; I will sing praises to my God as long as I live.<verse eid="PSA 146:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 146:3"/>Do not trust in nobles Nor in men, in whom there is no salvation.<verse eid="PSA 146:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 146:4"/>When his breath ceases, he returns to the ground; on that day his plans perish.<verse eid="PSA 146:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 146:5"/>Blessed is the one who has the God of Jacob for his help, whose hope is in Yahweh his God.<verse eid="PSA 146:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 146:6"/>The one who made heaven and earth, the sea, and all that is in them; The one who keeps faithfulness forever.<verse eid="PSA 146:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 146:7"/>The one who executes justice for the oppressed The one who gives bread to the hungry. Yahweh liberates the prisoners;<verse eid="PSA 146:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 146:8"/>Yahweh opens the eyes of the blind; Yahweh raises up those who are bowed down; Yahweh loves those who are righteous.<verse eid="PSA 146:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 146:9"/>Yahweh guards the refugees; he sustains the orphan and the widow, but he subverts the way of the wicked.<verse eid="PSA 146:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 146:10"/>Yahweh reigns forever, your God, Zion, reigns from generation to generation. Praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 146:10"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 146"/>
<chapter number="147" style="c" sid="PSA 147"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 147:1"/>Praise Yahweh! How good it is to sing praises to our God, how pleasant and suitable is a song of praise.<verse eid="PSA 147:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 147:2"/>Yahweh builds up Jerusalem, he gathers the scattered people of Israel.<verse eid="PSA 147:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 147:3"/>He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds.<verse eid="PSA 147:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 147:4"/>He counts the number of the stars; he gives names to all of them.<verse eid="PSA 147:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 147:5"/>Great is our Lord and abounding in power, his understanding is without measure.<verse eid="PSA 147:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 147:6"/>Yahweh lifts up the oppressed, he brings the wicked down to the ground.<verse eid="PSA 147:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 147:7"/>Sing to Yahweh with thanksgiving, sing praises to our God with a harp.<verse eid="PSA 147:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 147:8"/>He is the one who covers the heavens with clouds; he is the one who prepares rain for the earth; he is the one who causes the mountains to sprout with grass.<verse eid="PSA 147:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 147:9"/>He gives food to the animals and to the children of the ravens when they call.<verse eid="PSA 147:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 147:10"/>He does not delight in the strength of a horse, he does not enjoy the strong legs of a man.<verse eid="PSA 147:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 147:11"/>Yahweh enjoys those who fear him, those who hope for his steadfast love.<verse eid="PSA 147:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 147:12"/>Extol Yahweh, Jerusalem, praise your God, Zion.<verse eid="PSA 147:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 147:13"/>For he strengthens the bars of your gates, he blesses your children in your midst.<verse eid="PSA 147:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 147:14"/>He sets your borders with peace, he satisfies you with the finest of wheat.<verse eid="PSA 147:14"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="15" style="v" sid="PSA 147:15"/>He sends out his word to the land, his command runs with swiftness.<verse eid="PSA 147:15"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="16" style="v" sid="PSA 147:16"/>He makes the snow like wool, he scatters the frost like ashes.<verse eid="PSA 147:16"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="17" style="v" sid="PSA 147:17"/>He sends out his hail like crumbs, who can stand before his cold?<verse eid="PSA 147:17"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="18" style="v" sid="PSA 147:18"/>He sends out his command and melts them; he makes his wind blow, and the waters flow.<verse eid="PSA 147:18"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="19" style="v" sid="PSA 147:19"/>He proclaimed his word to Jacob, his statutes and his righteous decrees to Israel.<verse eid="PSA 147:19"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="20" style="v" sid="PSA 147:20"/>He has not done so with any other nation, and as for his judgments, they do not know them. Praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 147:20"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 147"/>
<chapter number="148" style="c" sid="PSA 148"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 148:1"/>Praise Yahweh. Praise Yahweh from the heavens; praise him in the heights.<verse eid="PSA 148:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 148:2"/>Praise him, all his angels; praise him, all his hosts.<verse eid="PSA 148:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 148:3"/>Praise him, sun and moon; praise him, all you shining stars.<verse eid="PSA 148:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 148:4"/>Praise him, highest heavens and the waters that are above the heavens.<verse eid="PSA 148:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 148:5"/>Let them praise the name of Yahweh, for he commanded, and they were created.<verse eid="PSA 148:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 148:6"/>He has established them forever and ever; he given a decree and it will not pass away.<verse eid="PSA 148:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 148:7"/>Praise Yahweh from the earth, sea monsters and all ocean depths,<verse eid="PSA 148:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 148:8"/>fire and hail, snow and clouds, stormy winds doing his word.<verse eid="PSA 148:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 148:9"/>The mountains and all the hills, The fruit trees and all the cedars,<verse eid="PSA 148:9"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="10" style="v" sid="PSA 148:10"/>animals and all the beasts, reptiles and winged birds.<verse eid="PSA 148:10"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="11" style="v" sid="PSA 148:11"/>kings of the earth and all the peoples, princes and all judges of the earth,<verse eid="PSA 148:11"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="12" style="v" sid="PSA 148:12"/>Young men and also young women, the elderly along with the children.<verse eid="PSA 148:12"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="13" style="v" sid="PSA 148:13"/>let them all praise the name of Yahweh, for his name alone is exalted; his glory extends over the earth and the heavens.<verse eid="PSA 148:13"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="14" style="v" sid="PSA 148:14"/>He has raised up the horn of his people praise from all his faithful ones, from the children of Israel, the people near to him. Praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 148:14"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 148"/>
<chapter number="149" style="c" sid="PSA 149"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 149:1"/>Praise Yahweh. Sing to Yahweh a new song – his praise in the assembly of the faithful ones.<verse eid="PSA 149:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 149:2"/>Let Israel rejoice in the one who made them; let the children of Zion rejoice in their king.<verse eid="PSA 149:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 149:3"/>Let them praise his name with dancing; let them play for him with tambourine and harp.<verse eid="PSA 149:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 149:4"/>For Yahweh takes pleasure in his people; he glorifies the humble with salvation.<verse eid="PSA 149:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 149:5"/>Let the faithful ones rejoice in this honor; let them shout for joy on their beds.<verse eid="PSA 149:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 149:6"/>May the exaltation of God be in their throats and two-edged swords in their hands<verse eid="PSA 149:6"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="7" style="v" sid="PSA 149:7"/>to do vengeance on the nations – acts of punishment on the peoples.<verse eid="PSA 149:7"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="8" style="v" sid="PSA 149:8"/>to bind their kings with chains and their honored ones with iron shackles.<verse eid="PSA 149:8"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="9" style="v" sid="PSA 149:9"/>to do the judgment against them that is written. This will be an honor for all his faithful ones. Praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 149:9"/></para>
<chapter eid="PSA 149"/>
<chapter number="150" style="c" sid="PSA 150"/>
<para style="p"><verse number="1" style="v" sid="PSA 150:1"/>Praise Yahweh. Praise God in his holy place; praise him in the mighty heavens.<verse eid="PSA 150:1"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="2" style="v" sid="PSA 150:2"/>Praise him for his mighty acts; praise him for his surpassing greatness.<verse eid="PSA 150:2"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="3" style="v" sid="PSA 150:3"/>Praise him with the blast of the horn; praise him with lute and harp.<verse eid="PSA 150:3"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="4" style="v" sid="PSA 150:4"/>Praise him with tambourines and dancing; praise him with stringed instruments and wind instruments.<verse eid="PSA 150:4"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="5" style="v" sid="PSA 150:5"/>Praise him with loud cymbals; praise him with high sounding cymbals.<verse eid="PSA 150:5"/></para>
<para style="p"><verse number="6" style="v" sid="PSA 150:6"/>Let everything that has breath praise Yahweh. Praise Yahweh.<verse eid="PSA 150:6"/></para>
